der-box; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.1px; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">ធ្វើរបាយការណ៍ជូនប្រធាន ប្រចាំសប្តាហ៍ ប្រចាំខែស្តីពីសមិទ្ធិផល និងការងារប្រឈម ។</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; line-height: 14.95px;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.1px; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">មានកម្រិតសញ្ញាបត្របរិញ្ញាបត្ររង ឬបរិញ្ញាបត្រជំនាញ ធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ គណនេយ្យ សេដ្ឋកិច្ច ឬជំនាញដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធ (បេក្ខជនឆ្នាំទី៤ ឬទើបបញ្ចប់ការសិក្សា​ត្រូវបានលើកទឹកចិត្ត)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; line-height: 14.95px;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.1px; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">មានបទពិសោធន៍ក្នុងការផ្តល់កម្ចី ទីផ្សារ ឬការងារពាក់ព័ន្ធ មានគំនិតច្នៃប្រឌិត ​ចេះដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា មានឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ក្នុង ការបំពេញការងារ</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; line-height: 14.95px;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.1px; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">មានគំនិតចូលរួមការងារជាក្រុម មានទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ និងមានភាពបត់បែន</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; text-align: justify; line-height: 14.95px;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 16.1px; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">អាចបំពេញ<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">ការងារនៅ</span>ទីតាំងឆ្ងាយៗ</span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,7,28,'10','06/26/2018',1,9,3,5,9,'English','2018-06-15 09:25:42','2020-05-31 20:41:49'),
	(226,20,'Supervisor, Nano Credit - 13 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Define the potential market segmentation of Nano Credit Customers (small unsecured credit customers);</li>\r\n<li>Supervise team by providing guidance, training, coaching, motivating, recognizing, and building the Nano Credit Team&rsquo;s competencies to ensure their high performance quality for their jobs, tasks and compensation;</li>\r\n<li>Build the customers&rsquo; pipelines and explore the potential customers of the minor unsecured loan known as a Nano Credit;</li>\r\n<li>Regularly monitor the performance of Nano Credit portfolio to ensure that credit quality, pricing, loan outstanding in order to meet the Nano Credit (small unsecured loan) target annually;</li>\r\n<li>Review Nano loan&rsquo;s assessment before submit to CAD (Credit Approval Discretion) approval;</li>\r\n<li>Monthly follow up trend of the loan repayment of the Nano Credit Customers; and</li>\r\n<li>All other matters ancillary to the above-mentioned and to perform any others related duties that management may require.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least holding a Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Finance &amp; Banking, Business Administration, or relevant qualification;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years of work experience in rural credit operator, minor unsecured credit sales management, Microfinance Institution, or Banking sector;</li>\r\n<li>Good at sales management skill, sales strategic and planning, people management, initiatives, marketing and integrity;</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical, problem-solving and critical thinking skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good communication, interpersonal skills, networking and the attitude of working under pressure;</li>\r\n<li>Good oral and written communication in both Khmer and English;</li>\r\n<li>Be willing to travel to fields or branch networks in rural areas when required.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,28,'13','06/26/2018',1,3,9,5,4,'English','2018-06-15 09:29:05','2020-05-29 04:39:23'),
	(227,20,'IT EOD Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Fix issue in core banking system and reporting system;</li>\r\n<li>Perform database backup and restore core banking system;</li>\r\n<li>Perform end of day operation and produce the daily report;</li>\r\n<li>Develop reports for other departments, NBC, CMA, and CBC; and</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and upload data to the data warehouse.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent;</li>\r\n<li>Fresh graduates are encouraged to apply;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in VB.Net or C# programming;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in Microsoft SQL Server or Oracle database;</li>\r\n<li>Good oral and written communication in Khmer and English;</li>\r\n<li>Have good teamwork and highly responsible;</li>\r\n<li>Able to travel in the province and work overtime.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','07/15/2018',1,6,7,5,9,'English','2018-06-15 09:31:15','2020-05-30 04:17:50'),
	(228,20,'Trainee - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist Executive Assistant in developing marketing strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Assist to collect MFIs/Bank related information and market economic overview to collate the report;</li>\r\n<li>Assist Executive Assistant to develop the new project design; conducting feasibilities studies and collation;</li>\r\n<li>Participate in checking and reviewing the update of related laws and regulator&rsquo;s requirement then compile the report; and</li>\r\n<li>Perform other specific projects assigned by Head of HR.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Freshly graduated or at least year III in University of Business Management or related fields;</li>\r\n<li>Good computer literary, familiar with core MS Office;</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of core MS Office;</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English communication;</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn and grow in to the new role; and</li>\r\n<li>Competent Trainee has opportunity to be promoted to permanent staff.</li>\r\n</ul>',3,39,7,17,'2','07/15/2018',1,6,10,5,1,'English','2018-06-19 06:18:55','2020-05-29 02:32:58'),
	(229,20,'Trainee - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist Executive Assistant in developing marketing strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Assist to collect MFIs/Bank related information and market economic overview to collate the report;</li>\r\n<li>Assist Executive Assistant to develop the new project design; conducting feasibilities studies and collation;</li>\r\n<li>Participate in checking and reviewing the update of related laws and regulator&rsquo;s requirement then compile the report; and</li>\r\n<li>Perform other specific projects assigned by Head of HR.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Freshly graduated or at least year III in University of Business Management or related fields;</li>\r\n<li>Good computer literary, familiar with core MS Office;</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of core MS Office;</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English communication;</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn and grow in to the new role; and</li>\r\n<li>Competent Trainee has opportunity to be promoted to permanent staff.</li>\r\n</ul>',3,39,7,17,'2','07/15/2018',1,14,10,5,1,'English','2018-06-19 06:18:56','2020-05-31 19:51:24'),
	(230,20,'Senior Credit Assessment Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist in reviewing and assessing loan applications and its supporting documents submitted by branches;</li>\r\n<li>Assist in developing all related risk policies and procedures to ensure that all business lines are well operated on a very conservative way;</li>\r\n<li>Prepare daily/weekly/monthly portfolio management report and approval tracking reports and submitting them for management review;</li>\r\n<li>Visit and check all Ly Hour&rsquo;s branches in term of compliance aspect to ensure that there is an effective and efficient control/management of the branch operations regarding all risk perspective including operational risk, credit risk and financial risk;</li>\r\n<li>Assist in monitoring credit risk and make sure that the risk is under control;</li>\r\n<li>Build concept of credit risk to branch staff;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that all business lines are well operated on a very conservative way; and</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks as requested by Head of Credit.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree of Business Management, Banking and Finance or related field;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 3 years working experience in banking industry; especially, credit skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English communication both in writing and speaking;</li>\r\n<li>Good Computer literacy (Word, Excel, Power point)</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical mind and can work under pressure;</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Having high integrity and team work oriented.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','06/26/2018',1,4,7,5,4,'English','2018-06-19 06:21:26','2020-05-29 05:25:32'),
	(231,20,'MIS Unit Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide management and leadership role for MIS Unit.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare strategy and roll out the plan for system development.</li>\r\n<li>Develop software for the computer, smartphone, and web.</li>\r\n<li>Develop report and manage business intelligence tool.</li>\r\n<li>Manage data warehouse and database system.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and perform system integration.</li>\r\n<li>Oversea project with software supplier.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in new IT project.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in computer science or master degree.</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years of work experience in software development.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in web, IOS, and Android development.</li>\r\n<li>Very creative and strongly willing to learn new things.</li>\r\n<li>Good oral and written communication in Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li>Able to travel in the province.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','06/26/2018',1,8,9,5,4,'English','2018-06-19 06:23:33','2020-05-31 09:34:53'),
	(232,20,'Deputy Head of Finance - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Supervise the produce the company&rsquo;s financial reports: NBC&rsquo;s reports, BoD and lender &lsquo;s reports, monthly and annual tax return report, and other stakeholder&rsquo;s report;</li>\r\n<li>Being a focal person in managing the processes of preparing financial projection, annual budget and consolidation, and reporting to the organization;</li>\r\n<li>Participate and support line manager in providing training on financial performance analysis to branches</li>\r\n<li>Develop policy and procedure and propose acceptable internal control tools.</li>\r\n<li>Evaluate staff performance based on clear KPIs and prepare development and succession plan.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree of Finance and Banking,</li>\r\n<li>At least four-year experience in Accounting and finance field with MFIs or Bank;</li>\r\n<li>Good understand of Cambodian banking rules and regulation, accounting legislation, and the Core banking system;</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of core MS Office (include word, Excel and PowerPoint);</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English communication;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to handle sensitive information with high level of confidentiality and discretion;</li>\r\n<li>Service-oriented and team player; display positive &ldquo;can-do&rdquo; attitude; and</li>\r\n<li>Work well under pressure; detail-oriented; strong multitasking and proactive.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,17,'1','06/26/2018',1,4,9,5,5,'English','2018-06-19 06:26:59','2020-05-28 22:41:10'),
	(233,20,'Executive Assistant - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Review the related financial documents and relevant governmental policies or regulations to identify the critical points to be highlighted to CEO;</li>\r\n<li>Verify all documents submitted to CEO such as policies, procedures, guidelines, strategies to ensure that the documents are consistent with existing strategies, policies and procedures;</li>\r\n<li>Support CEO in developing new projects design; conducting feasibility studies, roll out, sales promotion and conducting assessment on the project performance; and</li>\r\n<li>Follows up the progress action plans delivered by CEO to senior management in order to ensure good implementation; and</li>\r\n<li>Any other task as deemed necessary and requested by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree of Finance and Banking, Economics or related field;</li>\r\n<li>Sound knowledge on financial aspect;</li>\r\n<li>MFIs or Bank experience is preferred;</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of core MS Office;</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English communication;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to handle sensitive information with high level of confidentiality and discretion;</li>\r\n<li>Service-oriented and team player; display positive &ldquo;can-do&rdquo; attitude; and</li>\r\n<li>Work well under pressure; detail-oriented; strong multitasking and proactive.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,17,'1','06/22/2018',1,6,8,5,10,'English','2018-06-19 06:29:51','2020-05-31 09:16:00'),
	(234,16,'Micro Business Loan Trainee - 60 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Solicits potential and existing clients in accordance with the guidelines stated in the micro business loan policies and procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and interpret financial statements of the business in order to access the repayment capacity and financial soundness of the borrowers.</li>\r\n<li>Receives and screens loan applications.</li>\r\n<li>Conducts sit visit of secure collateral.</li>\r\n<li>Follows up delinquent clients immediately and refers to immediate supervisor.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for the attainment of his/her performance targets.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for processing registration of title deed at local authorities and Land office.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Minimum High School graduated, under graduated, Bachelor Degree of any related fields.</li>\r\n<li>One (1) year working experience in selling/any related fields is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Presents high attention to details.</li>\r\n<li>Has a good understanding of banking products and service/lending part is more preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Hardworking, commitment, ability to communicate and self-motivated person.</li>\r\n<li>Has good interpersonal skill.</li>\r\n<li>Computer skills: MS. Word &amp; Excel.</li>\r\n<li>Language: English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Be able to travel based on location set.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,39,7,28,'60','07/15/2018',1,7,3,1,11,'English','2018-06-20 09:19:09','2020-05-30 23:46:12'),
	(235,16,'Client Service Advisor - 15 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Identify and action on sales opportunity for new business opportunity by responding to inquiries from both new and existing customers.</li>\r\n<li>Provide consultative service in regard to banking products and services which is considered as a good solution to suite the clients&rsquo; needs.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in opening account in system per request from RM or Customers.</li>\r\n<li>Making sure that the documents submitted are accurate and valid.</li>\r\n<li>Take action to follow up in case provided documents are not complete.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to the development of sound profitable business by creating effective referral networks, including internal business relationship and existing customers in order to achieve the targets.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the compliance with ABA&rsquo;s internal policies, processes &amp; procedure, core values, and code of conducts, etc. are maintained.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in business, finance or marketing field.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years working experience in sales &amp; marketing.</li>\r\n<li>Negotiation and internal relationship building.</li>\r\n<li>Organizational and time management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Competent in spoken and written English communication.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,83,7,28,'15','07/15/2018',1,7,7,5,2,'English','2018-06-20 09:21:04','2020-06-01 10:54:39'),
	(236,16,'Branch Operations Officer - 03 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Support the process for account opening and validation in system as effective as possible. Making sure documents submitted by front officers are accurate and valid. Take action to follow up in case provided documents are not complete.</li>\r\n<li>Upload the specimen signature form, signed by proper discretionary holder(s) on timely manner.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to efficient delivery of customer requests, including, issuance of cheques book, cheque activation, bank confirmation (i.e., scheduled account statement printing&hellip;), etc.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain a proper control of sales kits and stock for passbook, FD certificate, blank cheques book, brochures, etc., take action to report and request for the new stock as necessary.</li>\r\n<li>Support and handle complex customer&rsquo;s issues in supporting sales area while executing excellent customer service principles.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor daily account movement in material amount (USD 50K or more) and make necessary reports to DBM/BM.</li>\r\n<li>Work in collaboration with front officers to collect pending fees (i.e., dormant fee) and improve the structure of values account; take action on closure of low value accounts.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains cooperative and productive work atmosphere, including &ldquo;speak-up culture&rdquo; within the branch.</li>\r\n<li>Assist DBM/BM on other operational tasks as assigned by BM/DBMCS.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in business, finance or marketing field.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 1 year of working experience as an operations officer, customer service-related skills.</li>\r\n<li>Organizational and time management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Good internal relationship building.</li>\r\n<li>Good written and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Attention to details and accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,7,28,'3','06/23/2018',1,5,7,5,11,'English','2018-06-20 09:22:30','2020-05-31 19:53:45'),
	(237,16,'ATM/CIM Officer - 06 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Load cash to&nbsp; ATM cassette after verify and run with machine.</li>\r\n<li>All ATM cash refill are recorded serial number and correct amount in hopper.</li>\r\n<li>Manage ATM hopper in transit.</li>\r\n<li>Support to ATM cash management supervisor for verifying actual cash with receipt of ATM remaining.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor ATM error and collect the reason of error, ATM maintenance and ATM removing.</li>\r\n<li>Make sure ATM hopper input with the right position.</li>\r\n<li>Run &amp; verify cash from ATM/cash-in Kiosk machine&nbsp; with senior officer at office.</li>\r\n<li>Collect cash from cash-in Kiosk machine.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Kiosk error and collect the reason of error,&nbsp; maintenance and removing.</li>\r\n<li>Sort new bill for ATM.</li>\r\n<li>Other task assigned by supervisor/ manager.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Completed high school or bachelor degree in Business, Finance and Banking, Accounting or any related fields.</li>\r\n<li>High attention to details and accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Good customer service skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Good organizational skills.</li>\r\n<li>Acceptable written and verbal communication skills (Khmer and English )Good computer literacy.\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Mao Seng tung Branch, Phnom Penh&nbsp; (1 post).&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Toul Kork Branch, Phnom Penh(1 post)</li>\r\n<li>Central Branch, Phnom Penh, (2 posts).&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Head Office Customer Service, (2 posts).&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'6','06/23/2018',1,6,7,5,9,'English','2018-06-20 09:31:13','2020-05-31 03:05:32'),
	(238,16,'Relationship Manager - 02 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Make customer presentations and identify &amp; action sales opportunity for new business from both new and existing customer.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to the development of sound profitable business by creating effective referral networks, including internal business relationship, existing customer and local market activities</li>\r\n<li>Agree challenging daily, weekly, and monthly referral targets for yourself with your branch manager/ Head of Department. Regularly evaluate these targets &ndash; when results fall short of target, understand why and agree what to do differently to improve performance with your line manager.</li>\r\n<li>Keep up to day with ABA&rsquo;s products suite and marketing campaigns to ensure superior product knowledge.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and implement effective customer retention strategies.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Excellent customer services skills.</li>\r\n<li>Time management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Sales, negotiation and relationship building.</li>\r\n<li>Sound written and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>High degree of self-motivation.</li>\r\n<li>Very good interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Complaint resolving.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy.\r\n<h3>Location&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Toul Kork 2 Branch, Phnom Penh (2 posts).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,36,15,17,'2','06/23/2018',1,7,9,5,9,'English','2018-06-20 09:33:33','2020-05-30 21:53:35'),
	(239,16,'Senior Relationship Manager - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Developing and actively seeking referrals from existing and new customers.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to the development of sound profitable business by creating effective referral networks, including internal business relationship, and other local marketing activities.</li>\r\n<li>Meeting/exceeding customer expectations through superior customer service.</li>\r\n<li>Marketing products to increase the lending and deposit portfolio.</li>\r\n<li>Ensuring account strategies and structured call programs are developed and monitored for progress.</li>\r\n<li>Provide coaching and guidance to enable team members to meet agreed goals.</li>\r\n<li>Provide regular feedback, encouragement and maintain open communication.</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing professional, technical development and training of self and team members (if applicable) and provide opportunities to apply new skills.</li>\r\n<li>Agree challenging daily and weekly referral targets for yourself with the Head of Department.</li>\r\n<li>Regularly evaluate these targets &ndash; when results fall short of target, understand why and agree what to do differently to improve performance.</li>\r\n<li>Keep a close eye on your local competitors &ndash; what they do and how they perform. And, plan to gain market share.</li>\r\n<li>Keep up to day with ABA&rsquo;s products suite and marketing campaigns to ensure superior services provided to clients.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and implement effective customer retention strategies.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Organizational and time management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Sound sales and negotiation skills in particular.</li>\r\n<li>Sound written and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Attention to details.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in managing relationship of business customers.</li>\r\n<li>High degree of self-motivation and excellent interpersonal skills.\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n<p class=\"bodytext\">Toul Kork 2 Branch, Phnom Penh (1 post).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','06/23/2018',1,4,9,5,9,'English','2018-06-20 09:43:41','2020-05-29 10:07:20'),
