	(261,15,'Branch Audit Officer for Credit Review - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Establishing the audit planning and budgeting to conduct internal auditing activities at branches of HKL.</li>\r\n<li>Performing the audit procedures and execute the policies and procedures are being followed and properly implemented.</li>\r\n<li>Reviews the existing HKL&rsquo;s policies and procedures, assess the quality of internal controls to ensure that HKL has adequate and prevented the risks fraudulent, and find out the control weakness or shortage.</li>\r\n<li>Prepareing an audit working paper and a draft audit report to team leader or supervisors for reviewing.</li>\r\n<li>Identify the key risks regarding to the Credit review transactions to be included and developed the audit procedures, and participate in developing to improve the quality of internal audit&rsquo;s work.</li>\r\n<li>Preparing pre-audit analysis checklist and posed engagement report.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks as require by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree of Audit, financial, banking, Business Management or Economics.</li>\r\n<li>Honest, reliable people.</li>\r\n<li>Dynamic and pleasant personality</li>\r\n<li>Excellent interpersonal and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Highly acquainted with computer systems and programs, such MS Word, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, Email &amp; Internet and core banking system is an advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Good Command written with English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work in the field (around 80% to 90% in the field work) including weekends.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,7,17,'1','07/16/2018',1,6,3,5,9,'English','2018-07-01 03:18:13','2020-06-01 02:35:47'),
	(262,15,'Core Banking & Solution Officer for Helpdesk Support - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Work as admin on core banking products configuration supports, and Follow Technical SLA on ticket issue assignment from all offices and departments.</li>\r\n<li>Work as admin on answer and question/query from all department and office in Helpdesk Issue Solution System.</li>\r\n<li>Support, Feedback and Facilitate users on their daily functioning and operation of products, functions and business applications faults/results</li>\r\n<li>Prepare report to follow up result and feedback with all users on pending ticket issues.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and investigate, prioritize and Escalate issues to respective technical support team.</li>\r\n<li>Communicate, answer and advice on appropriate actions to users as primary solution.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up supporting result and feedback to respective support team/helpdesk team/business team/ with all users at Head Office and branches.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in contact off-shore team support and document, update and test products.</li>\r\n<li>Report on weekly activities to supervisor or manager.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other task assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Hold a bachelor degree of computer science field.</li>\r\n<li>A 4th Year Student or fresh graduated are encourage applying.</li>\r\n<li>Working experience with microfinance or commercial bank is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Commitment and self-motivated</li>\r\n<li>Good at communication.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn new business applications and new technology.</li>\r\n<li>Be able to under pressure and as a team work.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,7,17,'1','07/15/2018',1,5,3,5,9,'English','2018-07-01 03:21:43','2020-05-30 14:40:24'),
	(263,15,'Corporate Social Responsibility Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Facilitate a corporate culture that promotes ethical practices, encourages individual integrity, and fulfills social responsibility.</li>\r\n<li>Initiate and perform Corporate Social Responsibility projects and programs</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate relevant, reliable monitoring information on corporate social responsibility enable timely and quality decision-making for internal and external stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Lead and coordinate efforts to reduce paper, energy, water, and gasoline.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree of Management, Banking and Finance, Economics, or other related field, English degree is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding and knowledge of loan assessment process in advance.</li>\r\n<li>Self-motivation and able to manage own workload.</li>\r\n<li>Be flexible with working hours.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in MS Office includes Word, Excel, Power Point, Internet and Email.</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Be able to travel to province.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,70,15,17,'1','07/15/2018',1,4,3,5,1,'English','2018-07-01 03:24:24','2020-05-30 18:00:30'),
