	(323,15,'Core Banking and Solution Officer for System Operation - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Control and monitor of business databases, OS, and Storage.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Analyze event logs and report on access to business databases.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Backup business databases to physical storage and to tape library for monthly basic.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Cooperate in IT technical, operation, and finance team.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Monitor archive space and disk space on database servers and storage.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Backup before running End of Day Process (EOD) on banking system.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Work with support team to resolve the error related to core banking system, OS, or storage, and backup data in storage.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Performance other taste assigned by supervisor.&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Bachelor degree or 4th year engineer in Computer Science or related field.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">At least have basic knowledge on Linux, UNIX and Oracle database.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Basic of SQL langu