	(413,15,'Deputy Director of Operational Risk and Fraud Management - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Assist Operational Risk and Fraud Management Director to achieve the annual work plans, Department&rsquo;s objectives and HKL&rsquo;s goals. </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Updating and review operational risk and fraud management policies as well as other supporting guideline and procedure to ensure that the policy procedure are reflect to the best practice for improving the implementation at KHL.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Proactive identifying, tracking and analyzing operational risk incidents and events that may have potential impact to HKL business operation</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Build risk and fraud prevention culture, risk awareness to all HKL&rsquo;s staff &amp; build capacity of staff under supervision to be effectively handle their work more independently. And assist director in setting risk limit, risk appetite and threshold for HKL.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform risk assessment and risk analysis on new product/service, process, etc and provide recommendation to mitigate the risk and support risk owner to conduct Risk Control Self-Assessment (RCSA)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Prepare and verify monthly and quarterly risk management report including operational risk and fraud risk management report and credit risk management.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Perform additional tasks and any duties as required by Operational Risk and Fraud Management Director.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">BBA degree in the field of finance, banking, Business Management or Economics or other related field, master degree is advantage.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Work experience in different areas of bank and financial institution at least 3 years, including experience in management and team building.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Working knowledge/understanding of risk management/ measurement techniques is advantage.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Highly acquainted with computer system and program such as MS Word/ Excel/Power Point, email, internet.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Excellent command Khmer and English</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Excellent analytical, problem solving, communication skill, and relationship skill</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Demonstrable experience with developing or implementing risk management framework, including compliance and monitoring program or related field</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\">Proven ability to work across different areas of banking related field</span>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Content, sans-serif; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.1; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 24px;\">Location</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet-red\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #555555; font-family: Content, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">Head Office, Phnom Penh (1 post).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','10/05/2018',1,6,6,5,12,'Khmer, English','2018-09-25 16:36:33','2020-05-30 05:20:49'),
