e: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"CA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">អាចធ្វើការជាក្រុម និងម្នាក់ឯងបាន</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"CA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">យល់ព្រមបម្រើការងារតាមការចាត់តាំង</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"CA\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Khmer OS Content\'; color: #333333;\">មានម៉ូតូផ្ទាល់ខ្លួន</span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'20','12/31/2018',1,8,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:49:21','2020-05-30 21:56:38'),
	(541,34,'Credit Officer - 150 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>To promote and sell the company&rsquo;s products and services.</li>\r\n<li>To process all new applications within the stipulated turnaround time.</li>\r\n<li>To build a good relationship with all levels of local authorities to get their support on loan documents processing.</li>\r\n<li>To fill in all new loan/existing loan applications with clients, and following up clients&rsquo; repayment on time.</li>\r\n<li>To manage and maintaining clients&rsquo; relationship with clients, to gain more loyalty from clients through high quality services.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least fourth year or Bachelor Degree in Banking, Finance, Management, Marketing or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Good experience in sales (Experience in Credit/ Saving is preferable)</li>\r\n<li>Commit to the core value of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical, attention to details, communication, time management, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of sales, marketing, economic, banking, financial principles, marketing and practices, markets, banking and the analysis data.</li>\r\n<li>Abilities to decision-making and problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English both speaking and writing.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Location: </strong>Main Branch, Russey Keo, Pet Chen/Boeng Trabek, Vimean Ekreach, Oudong, Kompong Chhnang, Olympic, Sovanna, Ou Bek Ka Orm, Cana City, Chbar Ampov, Takmao, Chroy&nbsp; Changva, Kien Svay, Sa Ang, Kampong Spue, Ang Snuol, Tramkork, Takeo, Kampot, Preah&nbsp;&nbsp; Sihanouk, Svay Rieng, Prey Veng, Bavet, Kampong Cham, Chheung Prey, Mukampol, Memot, Kratie, Ponhea Kraek, Kampong Thom, Baray, Stoung, Pursat, Bakan, Battamtang, Krong Battambang, Rotonak Mondol, Thmar Kuol, Sampov Luon, Siem Reap, Siem Reap_Phsar Leu, Pouk, Otdor Meanchey, Banteay Meanchey, Paot Paet, and Pailin Branch.</p>',1,71,15,28,'150','11/30/2018',1,10,3,5,8,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:52:10','2020-06-01 03:55:31'),
	(542,34,'Business Relationship Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide a good hospitality to Bank customers.</li>\r\n<li>Helping and facilitate the customer to complete the forms (Account Opening).</li>\r\n<li>Conduct the direct sales frequently to Bank prospective customers especially on none loan products.</li>\r\n<li>Deliver to customers with effective and efficient banking products and services.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare the necessary daily and monthly reports to Head of Branch Customer Service/BM.</li>\r\n<li>Participating the promotion campaign arrange by Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct KYC/KYCC (Know Your Customers or Know Your Customer&rsquo;s Customer) in order to build list of pipeline for direct sale.</li>\r\n<li>Regular update the Sale Pipeline, activity plan and report to BM and SM on the Sales progress.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for building good relationship to existing customers, customers entertain.</li>\r\n<li>Problem solving with clients and make clients feel confident with the bank especially encourage clients to use our bank products and services.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for promoting and cross-selling banking products and services.</li>\r\n<li>Must perform other duties as assigned</li>\r\n<li>Willing to accept the sales target provide by Bank.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Marketing, Banking, Finance, Management or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Past relevant working experience will be an advantage, but fresh from university are also welcome</li>\r\n<li>Commit to the core value of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical, attention to details, communication, time management, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of sales, marketing, economic, banking, financial principles analysis data.</li>\r\n<li>Abilities to decision-making and problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English both speaking and writing, knowledge of Chinese is more advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment</li>\r\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills and confidence to deal with customers and staff at all levels</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated capacity to work under pressure, delivering work in a timely and accurate in manner</li>\r\n<li>Interest and enthusiasm to understand the activities and operations of the business</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,23,'1','11/30/2018',1,12,3,5,8,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:53:44','2020-06-01 13:44:41'),
	(543,34,'Budgeting Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing and revising annual budget plan;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in producing report on the budget&amp; actual comparison by branch and CP bank as a whole;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing of monthly management accounting reports including a review of the various critical ratios and covenants for management, board of directors, lenders and NBC;</li>\r\n<li>To facilitate and monitor appropriate budget utilization by the departments and branches;</li>\r\n<li>To perform monthly variance analysis and forward looking projections for the businesses as required and investigate reasons for significant variances;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing and updating budget user guideline and template.</li>\r\n<li>To assist in facilitating and training department and branches on how to prepare their annual budget plan</li>\r\n<li>Performs other Tasks as assigned by relevant managers.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance, Accounting, or Business Administration.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work well independently and in a team;</li>\r\n<li>Availability to start as soon as possible;</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical, communication and inter-personal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to work under pressure and deliver outputs in a timely manner;</li>\r\n<li>At least one years of finance and accounting experience preferably in a MFI or Commercial Bank;</li>\r\n<li>Very good in English with good written and oral communication skills;</li>\r\n<li>Strong computer literacy such as Microsoft Offices (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, etc.),</li>\r\n<li>Understanding the Core Banking System, Internet, E-mail, etc;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','11/30/2018',1,8,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:54:57','2020-05-31 12:48:45'),
	(544,34,'Mobile Banking Support Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Configure and setup product parameterization/configuration and testing scenario.</li>\r\n<li>Resolve all issues or inquires raised from customers, agent and branches relevant to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support to all branches, agent/merchant any matter related to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor the performance of Mobile Banking to ensure service up to 24/7 including hardware, up time, and capacity.</li>\r\n<li>Support to onboard Agent and register customer for mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Actively &amp; timely monitor Mobile Banking operations, risk identification and detection as well as prevention.</li>\r\n<li>Periodic or ad-hoc site visits to branch/agent/merchant to identify non-compliance of policies, forms&rsquo; completion, or any other further mistakes in branches/merchant and then take action immediate to solve.</li>\r\n<li>Notify Head of Mobile Banking Unit/E-channel Manager suspicious and fraudulent transactions immediately.</li>\r\n<li>Produce daily, weekly and monthly mobile banking transaction report.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other related duties as assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with mobile Banking &amp; E-Banking is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in a systems administration and support environment</li>\r\n<li>Experience in supervising a team with sound problem solving skills, demonstrated project experience.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of various system architectures including hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in particular Customer database, Mobile Banking System, networking and other Electronic and Mobile banking technology.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with local payments systems and mobile payment.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work in Flexible time environment (night time and holiday)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent Communication and Listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification, analysis and solving problem</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability and Stress tolerance</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','11/30/2018',1,10,7,5,9,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:56:12','2020-06-01 04:50:49'),
	(545,34,'Agri Specialist - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Visiting farms to conduct analyses and collect data, such as crop yield measuring, analyzing and interpreting data, conducting Agri land valuations, advising on probable risk and mitigation.</li>\r\n<li>Clearly understanding on crop cycles of different crops in Cambodia, seasonality, production issues, different diseases and their remedies.</li>\r\n<li>Clearly understanding on the agriculture supply chain and its mechanism, cost of production and income from the products.</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining and creating awareness in the agricultural sector, especially for our financed customers.</li>\r\n<li>Preparing reports, developing and maintaining a set of database to use as reference for financing.</li>\r\n<li>Communicating ideas effectively, and writing clearly and concisely.</li>\r\n<li>Thinking strategically and having a strong sense of realism with regard to Cambodia conditions in Agriculture.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least a Bachelor degree or equivalent in an area relevant to agricultural work</li>\r\n<li>Some relevant work experience in one or more of these areas</li>\r\n<li>Agricultural and Livestock would be an added advantage are encouraged to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical skills with attention to details</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Commit to the core value of the company.</li>\r\n<li>An interested in financial products and markets</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification and analysis</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','11/30/2018',1,8,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:57:47','2020-05-31 18:55:28'),
	(546,34,'Internal Auditor - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist Senior Internal Audit in preparing the internal audit reports,</li>\r\n<li>Performs financial, operational, credit, IT, departments audit and other audits in order to provide assurance to risk department,</li>\r\n<li>Update audit check lists,</li>\r\n<li>Analyze the weakness of operation and management processes, and provide the evidential supports for recommendations in reports,</li>\r\n<li>Develop audit programs and testing procedure relevant to risk and test the objectives,</li>\r\n<li>Obtain and review evidences ensuring audit conclusion are well-documented,</li>\r\n<li>Documents the findings/issues, drafts the recommendations using unbiased opinion to submit to Senior Internal Audit for reviewing,</li>\r\n<li>Builds and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staffs of areas under review,</li>\r\n<li>Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors,</li>\r\n<li>Performs related works as assigned by Senior Internal Audit.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in auditing or related fields,</li>\r\n<li>Good English proficiency, both written and spoken,</li>\r\n<li>One year&rsquo;s experience in related field,</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy (MS, Office, Ms, Excel, Power Point, e-mail etc.),</li>\r\n<li>Plans and organizes workload properly with infrequent exception</li>\r\n<li>Makes good decision; timing and presentation of the decisions are acceptable</li>\r\n<li>Work consistently accurate, complete, and precise; rarely makes errors and/or omissions</li>\r\n<li>Responds to criticism in a constructive fashion; exhibits more initiatives than most in taking steps to correct problem areas as identified</li>\r\n<li>Building relationships &amp; networks</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to support business operations at provinces.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'2','11/30/2018',1,10,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 11:59:06','2020-05-31 22:25:04'),
	(547,34,'Compliance Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Resolve the regulatory issues regarding banking operations (coordinate day- to- day operations) in a real time manner when relevant staff or management are facing non-compliance situation.</li>\r\n<li>Check and verify the legality of the documents of the companies from different jurisdictions to make sure they are completed, acceptable and compliant with local laws and regulations.</li>\r\n<li>Identify the compliance failure/compliance breaches/ compliance risk involved and share recommendation/ corrective step to enhance the effectiveness of the banking operations</li>\r\n<li>Provide support and advice on the implementation of AML-CFT policy &amp; procedure, FATCA compliance, and Whistle Blowing policy &amp; procedure to relevant management and staff of the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct the monitoring and testing of compliance on the business units to make sure they are implementing the bank policy &amp; procedure as well as local laws and regulation</li>\r\n<li>Manage and update on the timely basis, the black list which shall be widely disseminated to relevant staff</li>\r\n<li>Perform Whistle blowing procedure implementation</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in law or equivalent degree.</li>\r\n<li>Good command in English and Khmer (Both speaking and writing).</li>\r\n<li>Ability to think laterally and creatively.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of the regulatory industry.</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Honest, Integrity and professional.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of applicable of law and regulations of Cambodia.</li>\r\n<li>Able to deal with the business and push back where needed.</li>\r\n<li>Grasp of banking operations.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','11/30/2018',1,7,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 12:00:14','2020-05-30 02:53:46'),
	(548,34,'Head of Treasury - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Treasury Management:</li>\r\n<li>Manage the bank&rsquo;s asset and liabilities in line with the Strategic Plan.</li>\r\n<li>Review and manage the balance sheet in terms of size, composition, and liquidity and exposure level to off-balance sheet items ensuring currencies risks are well managed.</li>\r\n<li>Manage daily money market and Foreign Exchange (FX) dealing.</li>\r\n<li>Analyse FX market and develop FX pricing of products.</li>\r\n<li>Identify and manage the market risk embedded in retail products.</li>\r\n<li>Build and maintain banking relationships with local and foreign bankers and FX business partners in coordination with Operations and Sales Teams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Asset Liability Committee (ALCO):</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set up ALCO term of reference and frameworks</li>\r\n<li>Be an active member of ALCO</li>\r\n<li>Develop report pack and present to ALCO</li>\r\n<li>Take action and respond to ALCO&rsquo;s recommendations</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP):</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop FTP policy and procedures to ensure efficient internal price transfer within business and treasury to optimize funding productivity and help track department P/L effectively to drive growth.</li>\r\n<li>Measure the cost of capital in the formulation of the FTP curve for use by the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Take into account for the bank&rsquo;s asset and liability book over different tenors and recognize the issue of interest rate risk in bank&rsquo;s current portfolio.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Investment Management:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop the investment policy and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Invest the surplus funds and capital to enhance yield to achieve a risk/reward ratio acceptable to the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Control the Bank&rsquo;s counterparty, position limits and any excesses.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor balances of Bank&rsquo;s Nostro accounts and optimize the Bank&rsquo;s free capital</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Provide support to ad hoc projects/transactions and other tasks as may be assigned CFO&nbsp;and Senior Management Team.</p>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance, Accounting or Business Administration;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 7 years of experience in bank/MFI; of which 3 to 5 years experiences in treasury, ALCO, FTP and investment function;</li>\r\n<li>A sound knowledge and solid experience of treasury function and reporting techniques in banks/MFI;</li>\r\n<li>Understand Cambodian legal framework including money and capital market in Cambodia;</li>\r\n<li>Sound, strong numeric and analytical skills;</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and negotiating skills combined with the ability to deal with all seniority levels within the line of business. Strong computer literacy such as Microsoft Offices (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, etc.), Core Banking System, Internet, E-mail, etc;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated experience in selecting, managing, and developing a team, and the ability to lead by example;</li>\r\n<li>Self-motivated, self-starter, demonstrated initiative and a strong desire to improve processes;</li>\r\n<li>Fluent in English with good written and oral communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical, communication and inter-personal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to work under pressure and deliver outputs in a timely manner;</li>\r\n<li>Consistently approaches work with energy and a positive, constructive attitude;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrates integrity and ethical standards; and</li>\r\n<li>Promotes the vision, mission, and strategic goals of CPBank.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','11/30/2018',1,8,6,5,7,'Khmer, English','2018-11-10 12:02:10','2020-05-30 12:20:44'),
