	(602,20,'ប្រធានក្រុមគាំទ្រសាខា (Branch Support Supervisor) - ០១នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>រៀបចំនីតិវិធី និងលំហូរកាការងារនានា ដែលទាក់ទងនឹងប្រព័ន្ធ 09 ។</li>\r\n<li>សិក្សា និងស្នើសុំកែលំអរទៅលើលំហូរការងាររបស់ហេរញ្ញិក ។</li>\r\n<li>ជួយសម្របសម្រួលក្នុងការសម្ភាសន៍ វាយតម្លៃការងារ ការតំឡើង និងបញ្ចុះឋានៈរបស់ហេរញ្ញិក ។</li>\r\n<li>វាយតម្លៃសមត្ថភាព និងស្នើសុំការបណ្តុះបណ្តាលទៅលើចំនុចខ្វះខាតរបស់ហេរញ្ញិក ។</li>\r\n<li>សម្របសម្រួលក្នុងការចាត់ចែងផ្ទេរហេរញ្ញិកពីសាខាមួយទៅកាន់សាខាមួយទៀត ។</li>\r\n<li>សម្របសម្រួលការងារជាមួយនឹងនាយកដ្ឋានពាក់ព័ន្ធ ។</li>\r\n<li>ការងារដទៃទៀតដែលត្រូវបានផ្តល់ឱ្យដោយប្រធានសាម៉ី ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បញ្ចប់ថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាបត្រ លើផ្នែកគ្រប់គ្រងពាណិជ្ជកម្ម ធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬគណនេយ្យ</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍ទាក់ទងនិងការរៀបចំនីតិវិធី លំហូរការងារ និងការគ្រប់គ្រងបុគ្គលិកយ៉ាងតិច ០២ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ ការដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា ការងារជាក្រុម ម្ចាស់ការ ការគិតទុកជាមុន និងមានគំនិតផ្តួចផ្តើម</li>\r\n<li>មានចំណេះដឹងកុំព្យូទ័រ៖ MS Office (Word, excel, power point); Internet, Email</li>\r\n<li>ភាសាបរទេស៖ មានជំនាញភាសាអង់គ្លេសសមធ្យម សម្រាប់ការស្តាប់ ការនិយាយ កានអាន និងការសរសេរ</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ គណនេយ្យភាព ឆន្ទៈការងារ វិន័យការងារ និងការទទួលខុសត្រូវខ្ពស់</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','12/25/2018',1,7,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2018-12-16 11:13:17','2020-05-30 05:38:14'),
	(603,20,'ប្រធានសាខា (Branch Manager) - ០១នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>ចូលរួមធ្វើផែនការទំលាក់ទុន រៀបចំផែនការយុទ្ធសាស្រ្ត និងជំរុញសកម្មភាពបុគ្គលិកលក់កម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>ដឹកនាំ គ្រប់គ្រង ចាត់ចែង និងជំរុញលើកទឹកចិត្តដល់បុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់ដើម្បីអនុវត្តការងារឱ្យមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li>ដឹកនាំការផ្សព្វផ្សាយផលិតផលដល់អតិថិជន និងតំបន់គោលដៅ ។</li>\r\n<li>សិក្សា និងវាយតម្លៃសំណើកម្ចីដើម្បីរក្សា និងគ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពផលប័ត្រប្រាក់កម្ចី ព្រមទាំងដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាផ្សេងៗនៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពនៃការបម្រើសេវាកម្មអតិថិជននៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>តាមដានពីការប្រែប្រួលនៃស្ថានភាពទីផ្សារប្រកួតប្រជែង តម្រូវការ ការពេញចិត្ត និងការត្អូញត្អែររបស់អតិថិជន ព្រមទាំងចូលរួមផ្តល់ អនុសាសន៍កែប្រែផលិតផលឥណទានក្នុងករណីចាំបាច់ ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងចំណូល និងចំណាយកម្រិតសាខាឱ្យមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li>តាមដាន និងជំរុញជាប្រចាំនូវការអនុវត្តទៅលើនីតិវិធីត្រួតពិនិត្យផ្ទៃក្នុង និងធានានូវការប្រតិបត្តិតាម ។</li>\r\n<li>រៀបចំរបាយការណ៍ប្រាក់កម្ចីជូននាយកដ្ឋានគ្រប់គ្រងសាខា និងរបាយការណ៍សំខាន់ៗមួយចំនួនទៀតតាមការស្នើសុំរបស់នាយកដ្ឋានជំនាញដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធ ។</li>\r\n<li>ចូលរួមក្នុងដំណើរការជ្រើសរើសបុគ្គលិក និងបង្វឹកដល់បុគ្គលិកកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បញ្ចប់បរិញ្ញាបត្រជំនាញធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ គ្រប់គ្រងទូទៅ ឬសញ្ញាបត្រពាណិជ្ជកម្ម</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍វិភាគ វាយតម្លៃក្នុងការផ្តល់កម្ចីតាមបណ្តាមីក្រូហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬធនាគារយ៉ាងតិចបំផុត៥ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍ក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រង ដឹកនាំ និងលើកទឹកចិត្តបុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់យ៉ាងតិច ២ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា ការគិតទុកជាមុន ទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ និងមានភាពច្នៃប្រឌិត</li>\r\n<li>មានសមត្ថភាពអាចបំពេញភារកិច្ចនៅក្រោមសំពាធការងារ និងពេលវេលាកំណត់ច្បាស់លាស់</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,20,'1','12/27/2018',1,7,6,5,14,'Khmer, English','2018-12-16 11:34:09','2020-05-31 23:25:20'),
	(604,20,'ប្រធានក្រុមទូទាត់សំណង និងអត្ថប្រយោជន៍ (Compensation & Benefits Supervisor) - ០១នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>រៀបចំគណនាប្រាក់បៀវត្សប្រចាំខែ ថ្លៃសាំង ថ្លៃសំលៀកបំពាក់ ប្រាក់បំណាច់ចុងក្រោយ និងអត្ថប្រយោជន៍ផ្សេងៗឱ្យបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ដោយអនុលោមទៅតាមគោលនយោបាយ និងនីតិវិធីរបស់ក្រុមហ៊ុន ។</li>\r\n<li>ផ្តល់ការគាំទ្រដល់សាខាតាមរយៈការសម្របសម្រួលធ្វើការជាមួយមន្ទីរការងារ និងអង្គភាពពាក់ព័ន្ធ ដើម្បីធានាថាគ្រប់សាខាទាំងអស់អនុលោមតាមច្បាប់ការងារ ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងប្រព័ន្ធគ្រប់គ្រងធនធានមនុស្ស (HR system) និងធានាថាទិន្នន័យបុគ្គលិកមានចំនួនគ្រប់គ្រាន់ និងបញ្ចូលទិន្នន័យក្នុងប្រព័ន្ធឱ្យបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ដើម្បីងាយស្រួលក្នុងការផលិតរបាយការណ៍ និងវិភាគទិន្នន័យផ្សេងៗ ។</li>\r\n<li>ផ្តល់ប្រឹក្សាដល់បុគ្គលិកទៅលើសេវាធានារ់ាប់រង បសស និងក្រុមហ៊ុន លី ហួរ អ៊ិនសួរេន និងជួយសម្របសម្រួលទាមទារសំណងពីក្រុមហ៊ុនធានារ៉ាប់រងជូនបុគ្គលិក ។</li>\r\n<li>ចូលរួមជាមួយគណៈគ្រប់គ្រងដើម្បីពង្រាង និងបង្កើតគោលនយោបាយទូទាត់ប្រាក់សំណង ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងសំណុំឯកសាររបស់បុគ្គលិក (Staff profiles) ឱ្យបានត្រឹមត្រូវដើម្បីងាយស្រួលស្វែងរក ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បញ្ចាប់ថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាបត្រគ្រប់គ្រងពាណិជ្ជកម្ម ធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬគណនេយ្យ</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍យ៉ាងតិច ០២ឆ្នាំ ពាក់ព័ន្ធនឹងការគណនា និងទូទាត់ប្រាក់សំណងជាមួយ MFI</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ ការដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា ការងារជាក្រុម ភាពម្ចាស់ការ និងការត្រៀមទុកជាមុន</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ មានការលះបង់ចំពោះការងារ វិន័យការងារ និងការទទួលខុសត្រូវខ្ពស់</li>\r\n<li>មានចំណេះដឹងកុំព្យូទ័រ៖ MS Office (Word, excel, power point)</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញទំនាក់ទំនងភាសាអង់គ្លេសកម្រិតមធ្យម</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','12/28/2018',1,6,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2018-12-16 11:52:08','2020-05-30 15:17:54'),
	(605,34,'Mobile Banking Support Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Configure and setup product parameterization/configuration and testing scenario.</li>\r\n<li>Resolve all issues or inquires raised from customers, agent and branches relevant to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support to all branches, agent/merchant any matter related to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor the performance of Mobile Banking to ensure service up to 24/7 including hardware, up time, and capacity.</li>\r\n<li>Support to onboard Agent and register customer for mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Actively &amp; timely monitor Mobile Banking operations, risk identification and detection as well as prevention.</li>\r\n<li>Periodic or ad-hoc site visits to branch/agent/merchant to identify non-compliance of policies, forms&rsquo; completion, or any other further mistakes in branches/merchant and then take action immediate to solve.</li>\r\n<li>Notify Head of Mobile Banking Unit/E-channel Manager suspicious and fraudulent transactions immediately.</li>\r\n<li>Produce daily, weekly and monthly mobile banking transaction report.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other related duties as assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with mobile Banking &amp; E-Banking is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in a systems administration and support environment</li>\r\n<li>Experience in supervising a team with sound problem solving skills, demonstrated project experience.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of various system architectures including hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in particular Customer database, Mobile Banking System, networking and other Electronic and Mobile banking technology.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with local payments systems and mobile payment.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work in Flexible time environment (night time and holiday)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent Communication and Listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification, analysis and solving problem</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability and Stress tolerance</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','12/31/2018',1,6,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:22:13','2020-05-29 09:18:35'),
	(606,34,'Branch Operation Officer - 03 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare journal entries. Assist monthly closings and preparation of monthly financial statements.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare withholding tax computations</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and resolve bank issues including customer&rsquo;s doubt and requests.</li>\r\n<li>Assist with preparation and coordination of the audit process</li>\r\n<li>Assist with implementing and maintaining internal financial controls and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring Inter-branch balance.</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance customer collateral documents with safety and good manner.</li>\r\n<li>Keep customer&rsquo;s credit files in good manner and in safe place.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up and clear prepaid expense and accrued expense.</li>\r\n<li>Produce credit report to relevant departments.</li>\r\n<li>Process any expense requesting. Purchase the inventories and equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Control inventory and fix asset.</li>\r\n<li>Manages expenditure of petty cash by following principles and procedures of CP Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Manage Contract, Record Relationship Officer&lsquo;s motor and make cash payment for them.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Accounting or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>Other relevant trainings and certification</li>\r\n<li>Previous experience of general accounting or in banking sector is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical skills with attention to details</li>\r\n<li>Excellent computer skills</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of accounting principles and practices</li>\r\n<li>Stress tolerance.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Computer &ndash; MS.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Office Location:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cana City Branch</li>\r\n<li>Kampong Chhnang Branch</li>\r\n<li>Cheong Prey Branch</li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,6,'3','12/31/2018',1,5,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:24:37','2020-05-30 09:16:16'),
	(607,34,'Business Relationship Officer - 04 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Identify and making appointment to Banking prospective customers, especially Deposit product.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct a direct sales to promote Banking products and services.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to go outside Bank frequently meeting and promoting Banking product and services.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare potential interested customers and updating to sales pipeline management system in monthly.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct a sale follow up report to interested prospective customers that have been posted in sales pipeline management system.</li>\r\n<li>Asist Head of Branch Sales/Branch Manager to provide private banking services both VIP retail and corporate Banking customers in order to enhance a good relationship and convenient services.</li>\r\n<li>Arrange sales logistics for sales team such as flyers, leaflets, and slide for direct sales.</li>\r\n<li>Develop plan of action and actively seeking referrals from the Bank&rsquo;s existing customers and other referrals from the network.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare weekly/monthly activity reports to ensure set target is achieved&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Job </span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>A university degree in marketing, business studies or related fields</li>\r\n<li>Having experience in sales or Banking/Financial services is preferred</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to motivate and lead the sales team</li>\r\n<li>Females are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>Strong negotiated and comprehensive selling skills</li>\r\n<li>Good in English/Chinese communication (both verbal and writing)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication and listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Information and task monitoring</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification and &nbsp;problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n<li>Self-starter and self-motivator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Location:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Paoy Paet</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Ponhea Kraek</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Sen Sok</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Takeo</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,57,15,27,'4','12/31/2018',1,5,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:30:08','2020-05-28 10:09:14'),
	(608,23,'Information Security Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Implement firewall solutions to properly secure WB Finance data and provide consultation on all new firewall implementations, firewall configuration changes, and IT projects requiring security operational support;</li>\r\n<li>Actively protect WB Finance company IT Assets and infrastructure from external or internal threats and ensure that the company complies with statutory and regulatory requirements regarding information access, security and privacy;</li>\r\n<li>Assist the end-user, other IT professionals, and external customers in requesting security variances and implementation of subsequent configuration change requests;</li>\r\n<li>Monitor systems for any anomalies, suspicious activity then provide proper updating, and provide patching quickly if notified from security solution provider or make recommendations for resolution;</li>\r\n<li>Maintains system documentation and configuration data for regulatory and audit purposes;</li>\r\n<li>Coach and guide Service Desk and Desk Side Support technicians in their incident response, directing incident first responder actions, and appropriately escalating issues;</li>\r\n<li>Check and collect backup log to ensure the backup job has been done and report to relevant staffs to take an immediate action in case of failure;</li>\r\n<li>Enforce the proper implementation of IT Security in order to comply with IT Security policy and procedure.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Information Technology or Computer science preferably in Information Security Management;</li>\r\n<li>At least 4 years experiences of recent professional experiences in Information Security and Compliance;</li>\r\n<li>Current experience with Network Infrastructure secured design and management;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and implementation of IDS/IPS and Syslog and operation of monitoring tools: Cacti, Nagios, SolarWind;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of information security principles, including risk assessment and management, threat and vulnerability management, incident response and identity and access management;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and experience in penetration testing and ISO 27001 standard and enforcement;</li>\r\n<li>Experience developing, documenting and maintaining security procedures;</li>\r\n<li>Experience and knowledge in Cyber Security, latest thread and attack vectors and mitigation plan;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in enforcing policy, procedure of IT across organization as well as delivery information security awareness across organization;</li>\r\n<li>In-depth knowledge of operating systems and security applications, as well as a working knowledge of network protocols and tools;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in VPN Management and Support and DPLC and MPLS;</li>\r\n<li>Previous experiences in IT Auditing is a plus.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','12/24/2018',1,6,6,5,13,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:33:44','2020-06-01 03:00:03'),
	(609,23,'Senior Research Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Develop research manuals (policy, procedures, data collection tools, data entry and analysis tools, and research report outlines and templates) which are critical and significant for microfinance practitioners;</li>\r\n<li>Initiate, review and/or refine guidelines, tools, and reporting templates of market studies/ research projects to ensure effective and efficient implementation as well as to obtain adequate data for analysis primarily information related to current needs and demands of clients, competitors&rsquo; rolling-out strategies, and industry performance trend;</li>\r\n<li>Take lead in conducting with the whole process of the research/survey projects as assigned by Business Development Manager;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze performance trend of the microfinance industry;</li>\r\n<li>Participate in reviewing existing product/ service strategies and their delivery mechanism, in consultation with operations team and other relevant stakeholders, to ensure the meet of current client&rsquo;s needs and demands;</li>\r\n<li>Report on key findings obtained from market studies/ research projects, draw conclusion and come up with recommendations to address any problems/ challenges encountered to line management and other key management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in economics, management, marketing, finance or business administration;</li>\r\n<li>At least two-year work related experience in the financial sector especially in the field of market research, product development and project management;</li>\r\n<li>Be capable to systematically and critically think on things need to be done for any specific job assignment;</li>\r\n<li>Must have a strong numeric and analytical skills; Have ability to work independently, self-managed, and proactively as a member of a small, busy team;</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding, speaking and writing in English language;</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of economics and financial topics;</li>\r\n<li>Have excellent computer knowledge &ndash; word processing, spreadsheet, power point, internet and email. Ability to use analytical database such as SPSS or Epi.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','12/24/2018',1,5,8,5,2,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:36:33','2020-06-01 06:34:00'),
	(610,23,'Office Design Specialist - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Create the office building design and highly detail drawing;</li>\r\n<li>Determine the material to be used and specify the requirement for the project;</li>\r\n<li>Assist in negotiation with landlord on decorated and design agreement;</li>\r\n<li>Assist in office set-up planning and execution;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with Office Support &amp; Marketing Team to ensure that WB Finance offices are well decorated according to standard requirement;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure effective supply of security requirement through office decoration and design;</li>\r\n<li>Seek supplier for office setup, renovation and refurbishment based on standardization;</li>\r\n<li>Assist in purchase of security equipment and other needs for all new and existing offices with budget availability and coordination with the Security Coordinator;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure security at all offices are in place (security camera, fire extinguisher) when decoration and design;</li>\r\n<li>Deal with suppliers to ensure office decoration and designs are followed the plan;</li>\r\n<li>Adapt plans according to circumstances and resolving any related problems that may arise during construction.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Graduate of an accredited architecture or design school;</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years of experience on commercial interior design or Construction Company;</li>\r\n<li>Basic Adobe Illustrator, PhotoShop and 3D software skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding and comment of English including speaking and writing;</li>\r\n<li>Working knowledge building systems, codes and ADA requirements;</li>\r\n<li>Extensive knowledge of the range of design principles and aesthetics;</li>\r\n<li>Intermediate MS Office application skills and AutoCAD/ADT skills;</li>\r\n<li>Intermediate verbal and written communication skills including presentation and graphic communication skills;</li>\r\n<li>Working knowledge of contract administration;</li>\r\n<li>Working knowledge of furnishings and equipment;</li>\r\n<li>Familiar with the concepts of furniture layout.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,53,15,17,'1','12/24/2018',1,5,7,5,12,'Khmer, English','2018-12-18 07:38:20','2020-05-30 01:17:53'),
