	(633,15,'Finance Officer, Budget and Analysis Unit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Prepare budget for all offices &amp; department </span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Design, implement and regular on budgeting module and financial analysis<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Update actual data of consolidate for budget plan<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Prepare rolling forecast to enhance reliability on financial planning and operations<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Analyze asset &amp; liability items such as loans, deposits, borrowings to enhance business productivity &amp; efficiency<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Analyze costs and benefits (profitability) for both existing and new services related to balance sheet items&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Bachelor degree in Accounting, Banking and Finance, Economics, or other related fields <br />(Pursuing for / Qualification in ACCA is preferable)<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">At least 1 year experience in tax consultant role<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Knowledge in tax accounting, tax compliance and tax returens<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Leadership and personal management skill.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Computer literacy in MS Office includes Word, Excel, Power Point, Internet and Email.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good communication in Khmer and English.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced analytical, organization, and interpersonal skill</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\"><br /></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','01/10/2019',1,7,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2018-12-30 10:53:32','2020-05-30 17:23:34'),
	(634,16,'Customer Service Consultant - 04 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Identify and action sales opportunity for new business by responding to enquiries from both new and existing customer (including individual cold call program).</li>\r\n<li>Provide consultative service in regard to banking products and services which is considered as a good solution to suite the clients&rsquo; needs.</li>\r\n<li>Keep a close eye on your local competitors &ndash; what they do and how they perform. Plan to gain market share.</li>\r\n<li>Deliver outstanding client service by executing financial transactions while maintaining an acceptable record in daily drawer balancing.</li>\r\n<li>Resolve account service issues and respond to client inquires promptly and effectively</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Organizational and time management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Negotiation and internal relationship building.</li>\r\n<li>Sound written and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>High degree of self-motivation and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Attention to details and accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy.\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>S\'ang District Branch (1 post).</li>\r\n<li>Bati District Branch (1 post).</li>\r\n<li>Pea Reang District Branch, Prey Veng (2 posts).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>',1,57,15,21,'4','12/21/2018',1,5,3,5,9,'English','2018-12-30 10:55:36','2020-05-31 17:23:32'),
	(635,16,'System Administrator - 03 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Installation, upgrade and daily maintenance of all bank&rsquo;s servers installed inside the bank&rsquo;s server room or outside.</li>\r\n<li>Keep all bank&rsquo;s servers serving 24/7, using redundancy schemas for all servers.</li>\r\n<li>Daily monitoring of all bank&rsquo;s servers, identifying and fixing performance and security breaches, weekly report of such monitoring with actions taken shall be sent to CTO to review.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor of the bank&rsquo;s servers loading and performance and taking actions to enhance (or replace). Enhancement (or replacement) reports shall be sent to CTO monthly as proposals.</li>\r\n<li>Making backups of all servers based on schedule approved by CTO. Report of backups made shall be sent to CTO each Monday for past week.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and maintenance of uninterrupted power supply of server rooms of the bank. Maintaining UPS replacement schedule due to aging of UPSs. The schedule shall be reviewed annually and approved by CTO.</li>\r\n<li>Weekly testing of take over generator. Such test shall be done weekly in cooperation with administration department.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor of cooling system of all server rooms and ordering timely maintenance from administration department. Review of cooling system shall be done monthly.</li>\r\n<li>Review list access cards allowed entering server rooms of the bank in cooperation with security department.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare annual development action plan submitted every year not later than Dec 10 to CTO for approval for the next coming year.</li>\r\n<li>Organization of &ldquo;Support team&rdquo; to communicate with other IT units of the bank over their requests.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in information technology, Computer Science or related field.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 or 3 years of working experience as a System Administrator or in banking sector.</li>\r\n<li>Holding System Administrator Certified Associate is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Be honest, quick learner, flexible and punctual.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work as a team.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn new technology and more self-motivation and self-study.</li>\r\n<li>Strong interpersonal skills and communications skills (oral and written) in English language.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent conceptual, organizational, analytical, and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good project management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to collect operational data, establish facts and draw valid conclusions as well as formulate ideas and recommendations</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'3','12/21/2018',1,6,7,5,4,'English','2018-12-30 10:57:09','2020-06-01 02:55:30'),
	(636,15,'Deputy Director of PMO, Product and Channel Development - 01 post','<p><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\"><strong>New Product and Channel Development:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Assist formulating product strategy and channel strategy roadmap<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">For new product development, participation in designing product concept, conducting feasibility study to obtain relevant approvals, collaborating with relevant functions to develop detailed end-to-end requirements and implementing new products which cover across asset, liability, and fee-based categories. Monitoring product performance post launch per agreed period<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Work closely with business development team to develop product package and client solutions</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Support implementation of new strategic/alternative channels</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\"><strong>&nbsp;Project Management:&nbsp; </strong></span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Track, analyze, and report progress of key project portfolio under responsibility</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Undertake different role(s) within project management as assigned by the head. Depending on nature of each project:</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Primary role is to support transformative project to align with corporate strategic direction; the role requires end-to-end management of project delivery which include business requirement development, activity planning, risk/benefit identification, cross functional coordination, and effective project closure monitoring</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">As and when required, perform business analyst role to support functional teams</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Facilitate necessary communication across organization to support programs or project implementation; including preparing presentation to stakeholders throughout project cycle</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Foster a collaborative working environment with functional teams.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Degree in business or related field is preferred, MBA is preferred<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good proficiency in MS. Office including Ms. Excel , Ms. PowerPoint<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">At least 4 years experiences in project/product management or relevant experiences<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Deep knowledge of specific complex financial solutions and products including the knowledge of financial markets, social-economic dynamics, and regulatory requirement relevant to the products<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Sound working knowledge of general business process and organizational framework such as goals, strategy, culture and structure<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Candidate with sound experiences in one of the following areas will have advantage, i.e. data analytics, process improvement, digital financial services, product development, and channel development<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Be very good in verbal and written English<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good time management skills and ability to multi-task<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Strong sense of urgency with high level of commitment and determination to deliver a great result<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Ability to monitor process/facilitate progress of process portfolio<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Be available to travel to rural areas if required.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\"><br /></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,85,15,17,'1','01/09/2019',1,10,9,5,13,'Khmer, English','2018-12-30 11:02:37','2020-05-29 23:13:20'),
	(637,15,'Manager, Merchant and Dealership - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Develop and manage sales finance dealership and discount partnership strategy to support company long term growth aspiration.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Establish and revise all related policies, guidelines, manual, etc.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Coordinate and work with manager of all offices to meet the set target primarily focus on sales finance dealership and discount partnership.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Build and enhance relationship with dealers and all partners.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Develop and implement marketing activities to achieve departmental target and maximize market opportunities.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Provide outstanding and consistent advice and service to improve customer experience.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Track, analyze, and report progress of key portfolio under responsibility.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Monitore upload process of discount partners in different channels.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Bacholar Degree in Marketing, Sales, Business Administration, and related field.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Minimum 3 years of experiencesin dealing with business partner and dealership management. <br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Demonstrate strong knowledge of business partnership and dealership process based on understanding of sales and marketing activities to support.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Extrovert and active personality for recruitment of discount partnership and dealership.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Be fluent in verbal and written in English (above business level).<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Able to use Microsoft office (Word, Excel, Power point) and skill analyzing and evaluating performance.<br /></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"left w100 size-content size13\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Strong customer service skills and timely management.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','01/09/2019',1,5,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2018-12-30 11:06:09','2020-05-30 17:28:32'),
	(638,20,'មន្រ្តីឥណទានណាណូ (Officer, Nano Credit) - ៦០នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>ផ្សព្វផ្សាយពីផលិតផលឥណទានណាណូដល់អតិថិជនសក្កានុពលនៅក្នុងតំបន់គោលដៅ ។</li>\r\n<li>កំណត់យុទ្ធសាស្រ្តលក់ផលិតផលឥណទានណាណូ ថែរក្សាអតិថិជន និងស្រាវជ្រាវទីផ្សារ/គូប្រកួតប្រជែង ។</li>\r\n<li>ប្រមូលព័ត៌មាន វាយតម្លៃកម្ចី និងតាមដានការប្រើប្រាស់កម្ចីរបស់អតិថិជន ។</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើការទំនាក់ទំនងល្អជាមួយអាជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋានក្នុងការផ្តល់កម្ចីរបស់អតិថិជន ។</li>\r\n<li>ដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាក្នុងករណីមានកម្ចីយឺតយ៉ាវ ។</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើរបាយការណ៍ជូនប្រធានសាខា ប្រចាំសប្តាហ៍ ប្រចាំខែស្តីពីសមិទ្ធផល និងបញ្ហាប្រឈមផ្សេងៗ ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<p><strong>សាខាប្រតិបត្តិការរួមមាន៖&nbsp;</strong>សាខាអូរឬស្សី សាខាច្បារអំពៅ សាខារតនៈគិរី សាខាខេត្តកំពង់ចាម សាខាស្រុកជើងព្រៃ សាខាស្រុកបាធាយ សាខាខេត្តត្បូងឃ្មុំ សាខាខេត្តកំពង់ស្ពឺ សាខាស្រុកអង្គស្នួល សាខាស្រុកកណ្តាលស្ទឹង សាខាស្រុកសំរោងទង សាខាខេត្តបាត់ដំបង សាខាស្រុកមោងឬស្សី សាខាស្រុករតនៈមណ្ឌល សាខាស្រុកបាកាន សាខាស្រុកភ្នំព្រឹក សាខាស្រុកបរវេល សាខាស្រុកពារាំង សាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្របែក សាខាស្រុកព្រះស្តេច សាខាស្រុកស្វាយអន្ទរ សាខាស្រុកបាទី សាខាស្រុកត្រាំកក់ សាខាស្រុកគិរីរង់ សាខាស្រុកកោះអណ្តែត សាខាស្រុកព្រៃកប្បាស សាខាស្រុកប្រាសាទបាគង សាខាក្រុងសិរីសោភ័ណ សាខាក្រុងបាវិត សាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្រាច និងសាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្រឡាច។</p>',1,71,15,28,'60','01/12/2019',1,8,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2018-12-30 11:22:27','2020-05-30 23:27:43'),
	(639,16,'iOS Developer - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Develop and maintain ABA Bank\'s iOS projects.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate with the team to define, design and ship new feature Fix existing bugs.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the performance, quality of the application.Write very high quality, efficient and testable software from given requirement.</li>\r\n<li>Doing code review.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare project technical document.</li>\r\n<li>Do R&amp;D on any new / popular (iOS platform related) technologies and tools.</li>\r\n<li>Research on new technologies and tools which can be beneficial to ABA projects.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Experience with third-party libraries and APIs.</li>\r\n<li>Familiar with Restful APIs.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of Apple\'s design principles and interface guidelines.Familiar with continuous integration.Knowledge of Unit Testing.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of architectures MVVM or VIPER.</li>\r\n<li>Solid understanding of the full iOS mobile development life cycle.</li>\r\n<li>Have experience working with Git, Git Flow and other tools such as JIRA, Confluence, Jenkin, code review, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Strong initiative and enthusiasm with mobile technologies and curiousity to learn new things.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','01/21/2019',1,8,7,5,9,'English','2018-12-30 11:25:00','2020-05-31 18:54:41'),
	(640,34,'Head of Business Relationship Unit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Support deposit manager to implement business strategies to make sure the target is achieved</li>\r\n<li>Manage, monitor and evaluate deposit team and BRO(s) to ensure the efficiency</li>\r\n<li>Support deposit manager to implement business strategies to make sure the target is achieved</li>\r\n<li>Manage, monitor and evaluate deposit team and BRO(s) to ensure the efficiency and effectiveness of their works toward the assigned goal and objectives under assigned provinces.</li>\r\n<li>Build market network and conduct sale approaches to potential clients, particularly segments of SMEs, Corporates and Key individuals.</li>\r\n<li>Make appointment and conduct sale presentation to promote commercial and superior banking services to potential customers.</li>\r\n<li>Manage and build relationship with existing customers to maximize the cross-selling opportunities on all available financial products and services of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and properly manage client base, including management of sales pipeline report for Deposit Manager.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and manage referral from both existing clients and other sources</li>\r\n<li>Keep up-to-date the competitors&rsquo; information, including their products, services and other marketing activities.</li>\r\n<li>Keep up-to-date with Bank&rsquo;s marketing activities, products &amp; services, and its product and market proposition to ensure both new and existing customers could be well educated and leveraged as much as possible the opportunities to support their businesses.</li>\r\n<li>Work with Branch Managers to effectively serve commercial and superior customers.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks assigned by Deposit Manager if required</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>A university degree in banking, marketing, business studies or related fields</li>\r\n<li>Having experience in sales or Banking/Financial services (management role) at least 1 year</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to motivate and lead the sales team</li>\r\n<li>Females are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>Strong negotiated and comprehensive selling skills</li>\r\n<li>Good in English communication both verbal and writing (Chinese speaking is a plus)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication and listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Information and task monitoring Problem identification and problem solving</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n</ul>',1,54,15,17,'1','01/14/2019',1,5,9,5,11,'English','2018-12-30 11:27:47','2020-05-27 15:40:26'),
	(641,15,'Deputy Director, ​Non Credit Product Development Department - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Formulate strategies and implement tactical plans for deposit products and other banking services.</li>\r\n<li>Deal and take lead the product and process development, enhancement, monitoring of non-credit products.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Develop the product policy, procedures, and guideline and process workflows.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor the performance of the products and propose to enhance those existing product lines to be better in the market.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure product price competitiveness and feature benefit suitability to meet needs of our target customer segments.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare business proposals for seeking validation from senior management.</li>\r\n<li>Analyzes cost &amp; benefit of non-credit products, marketing or sale activities.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares the budget plan/sale projections for non-credit product launch, sale or marketing campaign.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by supervisor.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Master degree in banking/finance or business management, or related fields</li>\r\n<li>At least 04 year experience in consumer banking, insurance or financial services industry.</li>\r\n<li>Extensive knowledge in insurance, strong analytical, quantitative, problem solving, communication (written and verbal), presentation, relationship management skills, project management skill.</li>\r\n<li>Be proficient in English both speaking and writing</li>\r\n<li>Be Innovative, dynamic and confident</li>\r\n<li>Be well time management.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,54,15,17,'1','01/20/2019',1,5,9,9,13,'Khmer, English','2018-12-30 11:31:13','2020-05-31 18:09:44'),
