	(657,34,'Legal Internship - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Preparing monthly report on license management, Branch Manager Relocation, Patent, Branch relocation.</li>\r\n<li>Following up court case and monthly reporting.</li>\r\n<li>Review and develop the contract to be in line with international laws &amp; best practice as well as national laws &amp; regulations.</li>\r\n<li>Check and verify the legality of the documents of the companies from different jurisdictions to make sure they are completed, acceptable and compliant with local laws and regulations before signing contract.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support and legal advice on the banking practice.</li>\r\n<li>Manage and update, on the timely basis, the essential reporting task.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Good communication &amp; good presentation skill</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Honest, Integrity, and professional</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of regulatory industry</li>\r\n<li>Good command of English and Khmer, for both writing and speaking.</li>\r\n<li>Undergraduate or graduate student who is majoring in law.</li>\r\n</ul>',4,68,7,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,2,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:16:57','2020-05-28 22:32:26'),
	(658,34,'Budget and Planing Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing and revising annual budget plan;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in producing report on the budget&amp; actual comparison by branch and CP bank as a whole;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing of monthly management accounting reports including a review of the various critical ratios and covenants for management, board of directors, lenders and NBC;</li>\r\n<li>To facilitate and monitor appropriate budget utilization by the departments and branches;</li>\r\n<li>To perform monthly variance analysis and forward looking projections for the businesses as required and investigate reasons for significant variances;</li>\r\n<li>To assist in preparing and updating budget user guideline and template.</li>\r\n<li>To assist in facilitating and training department and branches on how to prepare their annual budget plan</li>\r\n<li>Performs other Tasks as assigned by relevant managers.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance, Accounting, or Business Administration.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work well independently and in a team;</li>\r\n<li>Availability to start as soon as possible;</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical, communication and inter-personal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to work under pressure and deliver outputs in a timely manner;</li>\r\n<li>At least one years of finance and accounting experience preferably in a MFI or Commercial Bank;</li>\r\n<li>Very good in English with good written and oral communication skills;</li>\r\n<li>Strong computer literacy such as Microsoft Offices (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, etc.),</li>\r\n<li>Understanding the Core Banking System, Internet, E-mail, etc;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,7,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:18:10','2020-05-31 11:14:21'),
	(659,34,'Branch Manager - 05 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Run your business to deliver outstanding results across all key dimensions &ndash; Funds</li>\r\n<li>Under Management (FUM) growth, revenue growth, productivity, branch profit.</li>\r\n<li>Understand the economics of the branch and what can do to improve the branch&rsquo;s profit.</li>\r\n<li>Keep a close eye on your local competitors &ndash; what they do and how they perform.&nbsp; Plan to gain market share.</li>\r\n<li>Proactively identify and address areas of customer dissatisfaction, following up and resolving any customer complaints within your discretion or refer appropriately.&nbsp; Welcome customer complaints as an opportunity to learn, and take personal responsibility for their resolution.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the governance of branch operations in line with bank&rsquo;s governance standards.</li>\r\n<li>Take ownership of your team&rsquo;s performance and development and ensure that their behavior reflects the values and policies of the Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Embrace, drive and support changes to improve performance and provide better services/products to customers.</li>\r\n<li>Identify potential process/service enhancements, escalate as appropriate and document suggestions.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks to be assigned by line manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<p>Location:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Boeng Trabek</li>\r\n<li>Vimean Ekareach</li>\r\n<li>Reussei Keo</li>\r\n<li>Odongk</li>\r\n<li>Kampong Speu</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'5','01/31/2019',1,6,6,5,9,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:20:01','2020-05-28 08:28:39'),
	(660,34,'Network, Server and Desktop Support Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Install and maintain all applications used in the bank, firewall, antivirus and spyware protection setup for end user&rsquo;s computer and make sure all software installation are complied with software standard allowed;</li>\r\n<li>Maintain and make sure all CCTV are up and running properly</li>\r\n<li>Manage, install and monitor the cabling and workstation arrangement at head office and branch office</li>\r\n<li>Install, maintain, monitor and support file, print and email service and other resources including Active Directory, DNS, DHCP and Microsoft Exchange;</li>\r\n<li>Provide and service daily support to end user both head office and branches;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the security of the information systems, communication lines, and equipment for both head and branch offices;</li>\r\n<li>Regularly and daily support, monitor, maintenance and troubleshoot both local area network and wide area network and IT security in both head and branch offices;</li>\r\n<li>Work with administrative department in computer or/and related computer accessories acquisition and checking;</li>\r\n<li>Work and update the procurement team regularly about hardware specification and purchase order;</li>\r\n<li>Manage / oversee the capacity of the IT systems and plan way ahead for augmenting the same.</li>\r\n<li>Regularly update IT assets information and keep track of incidents;</li>\r\n<li>Travel to provincial branch offices for local area network and wide area network troubleshooting and maintenance;</li>\r\n<li>Provide and update daily or monthly report to line manager;</li>\r\n<li>Other duties and reports will be assigned by supervisor or manager</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least bachelor degree in computer science or in related discipline;</li>\r\n<li>1 year experience in computer hardware and software installation, repair and maintenance ;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledgeable in network and server installation, configuration and troubleshooting;</li>\r\n<li>Have experience and knowledge in AD, DNS, DHCP, Group Policy, TCP/IP, OSI Layer and so on;</li>\r\n<li>Have experience and knowledge in network infrastructure architecture, switching and routing and firewall appliance</li>\r\n<li>Have experience in cable management</li>\r\n<li>Ability to understand and communicate complex technical details in clear and concise manner to both technical and non-technical staff;</li>\r\n<li>Must have a good customer services towards end user;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure and self-motivation;</li>\r\n<li>Well coordination and collaboration with others to work as a team;</li>\r\n<li>Experiences in network topology and configuration;</li>\r\n<li>Some knowledge in server installation and maintenance; and</li>\r\n<li>Acceptable knowledge in network script</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,8,7,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:21:06','2020-05-31 01:59:07'),
	(661,34,'Business Relationship Officer - 04 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Identify and making appointment to Banking prospective customers, especially Deposit product.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct a direct sales to promote Banking products and services.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to go outside Bank frequently meeting and promoting Banking product and services.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare potential interested customers and updating to sales pipeline management system in monthly.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct a sale follow up report to interested prospective customers that have been posted in sales pipeline management system.</li>\r\n<li>Asist Head of Branch Sales/Branch Manager to provide private banking services both VIP retail and corporate Banking customers in order to enhance a good relationship and convenient services.</li>\r\n<li>Arrange sales logistics for sales team such as flyers, leaflets, and slide for direct sales.</li>\r\n<li>Develop plan of action and actively seeking referrals from the Bank&rsquo;s existing customers and other referrals from the network.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare weekly/monthly activity reports to ensure set target is achieved.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>A university degree in marketing, business studies or related fields</li>\r\n<li>Having experience in sales or Banking/Financial services is preferred</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to motivate and lead the sales team</li>\r\n<li>Females are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>Strong negotiated and comprehensive selling skills</li>\r\n<li>Good in English/Chinese communication (both verbal and writing)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication and listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Information and task monitoring</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification and&nbsp; problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n<li>Self-starter and self-motivator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Locations:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Kampot</li>\r\n<li>Takeo</li>\r\n<li>Sen Sok (Phnom Penh)</li>\r\n<li>Ponhea Kraek (Thboung Khmum)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,57,15,27,'4','01/31/2019',1,7,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:24:33','2020-05-28 13:24:34'),
	(662,34,'Mobile Banking Support Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Configure and setup product parameterization/configuration and testing scenario.</li>\r\n<li>Resolve all issues or inquires raised from customers, agent and branches relevant to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support to all branches, agent/merchant any matter related to mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor the performance of Mobile Banking to ensure service up to 24/7 including hardware, up time, and capacity.</li>\r\n<li>Support to onboard Agent and register customer for mobile banking.</li>\r\n<li>Actively &amp; timely monitor Mobile Banking operations, risk identification and detection as well as prevention.</li>\r\n<li>Periodic or ad-hoc site visits to branch/agent/merchant to identify non-compliance of policies, forms&rsquo; completion, or any other further mistakes in branches/merchant and then take action immediate to solve.</li>\r\n<li>Notify Head of Mobile Banking Unit/E-channel Manager suspicious and fraudulent transactions immediately.</li>\r\n<li>Produce daily, weekly and monthly mobile banking transaction report.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other related duties as assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with mobile Banking &amp; E-Banking is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in a systems administration and support environment</li>\r\n<li>Experience in supervising a team with sound problem solving skills, demonstrated project experience.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of various system architectures including hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in particular Customer database, Mobile Banking System, networking and other Electronic and Mobile banking technology.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with local payments systems and mobile payment.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work in Flexible time environment (night time and holiday)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent Communication and Listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification, analysis and solving problem</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability and Stress tolerance</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:25:45','2020-06-01 05:29:13'),
	(663,34,'Internal Auditor - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist the Head of Internal Audit in preparing the annual audit plan.</li>\r\n<li>Assists in providing training, coaching, and guidance to Internal Audit Staffs in conducting audit and other related issues.</li>\r\n<li>Performs financial, operational, credit, IT, Human Resource Department, Risk Department and other audits in order to provide assurance to Risk Department.</li>\r\n<li>Update audit programs and audit check lists.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze the weakness of operation and management processes, and provide the evidential supports for recommendations in reports.</li>\r\n<li>Develop audit programs and testing procedures relevant to risk and test the objectives.</li>\r\n<li>Supervise internal audit assignment to engagement providing guidance and overall review of deliverable and review Internal Auditors&rsquo; works.</li>\r\n<li>Obtain and review evidences ensuring audit conclusion are well documented.</li>\r\n<li>Documents the findings/issues, drafts the recommendations using unbiased opinion to submit to the Internal Audit Team Leader for reviewing.</li>\r\n<li>Builds and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staffs of areas under review.</li>\r\n<li>Take the role of Internal Audit Team Leader if he or she is on leave or absent.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors; and</li>\r\n<li>Performs related works as assigned by Head of Internal Audit and Team Leader</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in auditing or related field;</li>\r\n<li>Two years&rsquo; experience in Banking audit or related fields;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in audit standards;</li>\r\n<li>Good English proficiency, both written and spoken;</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy (MS. Office, Power point, e-mail etc.);</li>\r\n<li>Internationally recognized accounting or auditing certification, such as CISA, CIA, CFE, FCPA etc. is an advantage;</li>\r\n<li>Audit techniques (work programs, tests, sampling. documentation, reports);</li>\r\n<li>Dynamics &nbsp;and good interpersonal skill; and Willingness to travel to support business operations at provinces.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'2','01/31/2019',1,7,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:26:53','2020-05-30 13:51:54'),
	(664,34,'Information System Auditor - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Responsible for preparing &nbsp;IS/IT audit plan based on risk assessment</li>\r\n<li>Provide Business and IT management with guidance on IS/IT risk management matters, particularly on application and infrastructure security.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for developing and maintaining the IS/IT Risk Assessment; including identifying areas where business units should consider additional investment and areas internal audit should focus.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct audits or lead audit teams in performance of IS/IT audits and reviews of systems</li>\r\n<li>Designs a technology-based audit approaches, analyzes and evaluates enterprise IT processes to assess internal controls and minimize risks; perform risk analysis of the enterprise&rsquo;s information technology infrastructure and services network; evaluates the possible risks of various computer systems; prepare reports documenting findings and risk assessment; evaluates management responses to findings.</li>\r\n<li>Works independently or with together members of internal audit to review enterprise internal controls, following the COSO/COBIT internal controls framework.</li>\r\n<li>Examines the effectiveness of the information security policies and procedures; identifies inadequacies within the existing security program and possible action to be taken.</li>\r\n<li>Develops and implements computer-assisted audit tools and techniques (CAATs) to assist overall internal audit efforts and performs other IT-related tests of controls, as appropriate.</li>\r\n<li>Develops and presents training workshops for audit staff on security controls and risk concepts.</li>\r\n<li>Performs special projects and other duties as assigned by Head of Internal Audit Department.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least 1 years &ndash; experience as an IT auditor.</li>\r\n<li>International professional certificates such: Certified Information System Auditor, Certified Information System Security Professional, Certified Information Security Manager, and Certified Ethical Hacker etc.</li>\r\n<li>Bachelor in computer science, computer programming.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of auditing, information systems, network security, Key IT process control, IT Security Assurance &amp; IT Governance, Managing Business risk</li>\r\n<li>Ability to exercise good judgment, Interpersonal, communication skill</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'2','01/31/2019',1,7,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:27:51','2020-06-01 02:55:47'),
	(665,34,'Chief Sales and Distribution Officer - 01 post','<p><strong>&nbsp;Manage the establishment and delivery of business profitability target through: </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction of products and services (include fee-based service) that can be served for various customer segments including Salaried, Self-employed and Company (micro, small, medium)</li>\r\n<li>Development and implementation of customer acquisition and retention strategies</li>\r\n<li>Driving growth in loan portfolio, deposit and other fee-based incomes</li>\r\n<li>Delivery of quality customer service and customer satisfaction levels</li>\r\n<li>Coaching and mentoring of subordinate to lift capabilities<strong>Strategic Planning and Business Development &ndash; Increase overall business profits by:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Developing and articulating strategic plans for sales team and branches to deliver top down targets flowing from the overall bank&rsquo;s strategic plans or corporate scorecard.</li>\r\n<li>Developing and implementing a marketing and sales strategy to generate sales of the Bank&rsquo;s products and services, and referrals to other specialist areas of the bank to increase and retain customer relationships.</li>\r\n<li>Building a positive brand image through managing all the bank&rsquo;s marketing assets to ensure that the branding projects are positive image.</li>\r\n<li>Establishing a sales and revenue plan for the Bank</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring performance against the plan and take appropriate action to achieve or exceed the targets.</li>\r\n<li>Achieving cross-selling referrals to increase depth of relationship and share of wallet as a principle means of customer retention.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> Customer Satisfaction &ndash; Improve overall customer satisfaction and increase service levels by:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Creating an environment that promotes active selling and superior customer service by conducting regular feedback, sales coaching and development sessions with individuals and teams.</li>\r\n<li>Ensuring high levels of customer service is provided to all customers</li>\r\n<li>Leading and inspiring branch managers and other managers within the network to want to be the best in customer service.</li>\r\n<li>Effectively addressing customer complaints and disputes and addressing initial cause where necessary.</li>\r\n<li>Managing call centre and use it as the contact point for collecting and understanding about customer complaint/ customer satisfaction and improving it and as well as use it as one of an indirect selling point for the bank.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> Operational Risk Management</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure compliance with both Bank&rsquo;s policy and external regulatory requirements</li>\r\n<li>Ensure readiness of business contingency plan, detailing actions required for the restart of branch and business operations in the event of a disaster</li>\r\n<li>Drive and support adequate training to ensure all new and existing staff are adequately aware of their risk management and compliance requirements and knowledge is assessed</li>\r\n<li>Regularly communicate to staff on risk trends and issues to increase awareness and minimize loss.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> Lead and Inspire</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Proactively improve the bench strength of the team ensuring all individuals are appropriately skilled to undertake their existing roles and provide opportunities for people to develop further. This will include implementation of training programs in line with individual development plans.</li>\r\n<li>Provide leadership and direction to team and empower staff to achieve to their best capability. Develop and maintain an open, honest and satisfying team environment.</li>\r\n<li>Make time to coach team. Give honest and direct feedback on what is going well and where improvement is possible. Schedule and implement development and training plans for each of your staff. Keep records and track progress.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> Innovation &amp; Growth</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Actively embrace and demonstrate commitment to the Bank&rsquo;s Values and aspirations.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure sharing of &ldquo;best practices&rdquo; ideas.</li>\r\n<li>Embrace, drive and support changes.</li>\r\n<li>Identify potential process/service enhancements, escalate as appropriate, and document suggestions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Experience in managing a Retail and/or Business &amp; Commercial Banking environment</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience with budget responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Sound working knowledge of sales and service concepts and strategies</li>\r\n<li>Broad management experience in a financial environment / Retail Banking</li>\r\n<li>Strong leadership skills with demonstrated ability to manage diverse groups of staff with flexibility, innovation and diplomacy.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to think laterally</li>\r\n<li>Superior communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to influence outcomes</li>\r\n<li>A willingness to operate in a complex, matrix environment with multiple, often conflicting demands.</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to establish credibility and maintain and develop good business relationships with high profile customers.</li>\r\n<li>Flexible with the ability to assimilate quickly into a demanding role/environment.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,9,6,5,10,'English','2019-01-20 11:30:22','2020-05-31 00:20:02'),
	(666,34,'Head of Treasury Department - 01 post','<p><strong>Key Requirement:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure integration of the systems chosen and project manage SIT,UAT &amp; Implementation</li>\r\n<li>Ensure a strong business support team is built to support BAU (including system access control)</li>\r\n<li>Build a small production Support organization to ensure smooth running of production systems including interfacing to 3rd party / outsourced infrastructure</li>\r\n<li>Design &amp; Own IT architecture (Functional &amp; Technical) for IT MFI Landscape</li>\r\n<li>Working knowledge of Core Banking Functionalities (Product Management/Setup, Teller, FT</li>\r\n<li>Debit Cards/ATM Management/Payments, Transaction Banking, Mobile / Interface Banking etc.</li>\r\n<li>Manage IT Vendor relationships and be able to negotiate commercials</li>\r\n<li>Manage user requirements, gaps/issues, vendor management, UAT &amp; implementation</li>\r\n<li>Manage and ensure Up-Keep of Production Systems (SLA near 100%)</li>\r\n<li>Face-off to CP Bank&rsquo;s (CXOs) Senior Management team</li>\r\n<li>Ensure vendor documentations are up-to-date.</li>\r\n<li>Develop Application Roadmap for all the functional area</li>\r\n<li>Train / develop user / IT community</li>\r\n<li>Development and Up-keep of IT Policy including Information Security Policy, Procedure &amp; SOP Aligning the IT department with this Information Security policy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Key Competencies required:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">Facilitate and gather requirements / gaps against chosen systems</span></li>\r\n<li>Review and validate the System Integrators deliverable to ensure integration across systems (Customer, Product and Process)</li>\r\n<li>Ensure IT Partners provide solution to business requirements</li>\r\n<li>Keep up-to-date with the industry knowledge on the best practices and new MFI products</li>\r\n<li>Develop new analytical approaches and methodologies (find solutions for gaps in the IT landscape example: New types of Loans/ Overdrafts, Deposits &amp; Investment accounts)</li>\r\n<li>Manage vendor&rsquo;s contracts and deliverables</li>\r\n<li>Excellent verbal conversation and written communication</li>\r\n<li>Excellent vendor management</li>\r\n<li>Great negotiation skills</li>\r\n<li>Excellent leadership skills to build and develop the IT teams and face-off the management team</li>\r\n<li>Coaching &amp; Training</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Master&rsquo;s degree in Information Technology or any Engineering discipline;</li>\r\n<li>Preferably International Exposure with Multi-national banks or equivalent Top 3 MFIs (min. 5 years) Cambodian MFI/ Banking Market Exposure is must</li>\r\n<li>10-15 years of hands-on experience in MFI/banking / lending products;</li>\r\n<li>Experienced in implementing IT Core Banking platforms / conversions;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of entire landscape from channels, core banking and reporting (GL etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Must be a single point contact for the senior management for solutions related to automation / process efficiency.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,7,6,9,7,'English','2019-01-20 11:32:37','2020-05-31 13:59:28'),
	(667,34,'Finance Manager - 01 post','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To provide insight into and understanding of the Financial Performance of the Bank&rsquo;s operation along the market and regulatory environment within which we operate;</li>\r\n<li>To ensure high standards of quality and professional Financial Management is met at all times;</li>\r\n<li>To ensure that statutory, regulatory and procedures and requirements are fully complied with;</li>\r\n<li>Develop suitable MIS for various management meetings periodically;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and interpret bank&rsquo;s data and present to management for decision making;</li>\r\n<li>Liaise with Information Technology Department for setting up appropriate ledgers, proper accounting treatment through parameters and accurate reporting;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure compliance with all statutory &amp; regulatory requirements such as provisioning;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure overall accuracy of data and information which extracted from core banking system database;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure timely preparation &amp; submission of Central Bank Reports;</li>\r\n<li>Support end users to utilize MIS report or Core Banking Systems.</li>\r\n<li>To ensure that the financial statements and returns of the Bank&rsquo;s operations are prepared in compliance with statutory/regulatory requirements;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that&nbsp; adequate&nbsp; accounting&nbsp; and&nbsp; other&nbsp; supporting&nbsp; records&nbsp; and&nbsp; internal&nbsp; control&nbsp; systems&nbsp; are properly maintained;</li>\r\n<li>To monitor the capital expenditure to ensure adherence to budgeted limits;</li>\r\n<li>Upgrade the &nbsp;accounting&nbsp; policies&nbsp; and&nbsp; expense&nbsp; management&nbsp; policies&nbsp; to&nbsp; keep&nbsp; pace&nbsp; with&nbsp; the&nbsp; highly complex and changing Regulatory environment.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance, Accounting, or Business Administration.</li>\r\n<li>excellent analytical, communication and inter-personal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to work under pressure and deliver outputs in a timely manner;</li>\r\n<li>consistently approaches work with energy and a positive, constructive attitude</li>\r\n<li>At least Three years of financial management experience preferably in a MFI or Commercial Bank;</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of budget, financial analysis and assessment of financial systems and procedures;</li>\r\n<li>Fluent in English with good written and oral communication skills;</li>\r\n<li>Strong computer literacy such as Microsoft Offices (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, etc.), Core Banking System,</li>\r\n<li>Internet, E-mail, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Accuracy, attention to details, initiative and ability to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated experience&nbsp; in&nbsp; selecting,&nbsp; managing,&nbsp; and&nbsp; developing&nbsp; a &nbsp;team,&nbsp; and&nbsp; the&nbsp; ability&nbsp; to&nbsp; lead by example;</li>\r\n<li>Self-motivated, self-starter, demonstrated initiative and a strong desire to improve processes.</li>\r\n<li>Honest and patient</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,6,5,12,'English','2019-01-20 11:33:47','2020-06-01 11:12:32'),
	(668,34,'Head of Business Relationship Unit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Support deposit manager to implement business strategies to make sure the target is achieved</li>\r\n<li>Manage, monitor and evaluate deposit team and BRO(s) to ensure the efficiency</li>\r\n<li>Support deposit manager to implement business strategies to make sure the target is achieved</li>\r\n<li>Manage, monitor and evaluate deposit team and BRO(s) to ensure the efficiency and effectiveness of their works toward the assigned goal and objectives under assigned provinces.</li>\r\n<li>Build market network and conduct sale approaches to potential clients, particularly segments of SMEs, Corporates and Key individuals.</li>\r\n<li>Make appointment and conduct sale presentation to promote commercial and superior banking services to potential customers.</li>\r\n<li>Manage and build relationship with existing customers to maximize the cross-selling opportunities on all available financial products and services of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and properly manage client base, including management of sales pipeline report for Deposit Manager.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and manage referral from both existing clients and other sources</li>\r\n<li>Keep up-to-date the competitors&rsquo; information, including their products, services and other marketing activities.</li>\r\n<li>Keep up-to-date with Bank&rsquo;s marketing activities, products &amp; services, and its product and market proposition to ensure both new and existing customers could be well educated and leveraged as much as possible the opportunities to support their businesses.</li>\r\n<li>Work with Branch Managers to effectively serve commercial and superior customers.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks assigned by Deposit Manager if required</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>A university degree in banking, marketing, business studies or related fields</li>\r\n<li>Having experience in sales or Banking/Financial services (management role) at least 1 year</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to motivate and lead the sales team</li>\r\n<li>Females are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>Strong negotiated and comprehensive selling skills</li>\r\n<li>Good in English communication both verbal and writing (Chinese speaking is a plus)</li>\r\n<li>Planning and organizing</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication and listing Skills</li>\r\n<li>Information and task monitoring Problem identification and problem solving</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,9,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:35:12','2020-06-01 10:18:34'),
	(669,34,'Credit Officer - 200 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>To promote and sell the company&rsquo;s products and services.</li>\r\n<li>To process all new applications within the stipulated turnaround time.</li>\r\n<li>To build a good relationship with all levels of local authorities to get their support on loan documents processing.</li>\r\n<li>To fill in all new loan/existing loan applications with clients, and following up clients&rsquo; repayment on time.</li>\r\n<li>To manage and maintaining clients&rsquo; relationship with clients, to gain more loyalty from clients through high quality services.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum third year or graduated in Banking &amp; Finance, Management, Marketing or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Good experience in sales (Experience in Credit/ Saving is preferable)</li>\r\n<li>Commit to the core value of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical, attention to details, communication, time management, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Abilities to decision-making and problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English both speaking and writing.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'200','01/31/2019',1,6,3,5,8,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:37:12','2020-05-27 15:10:46'),
	(670,34,'Graphic Designer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>An opportunity has arisen to train as a professional graphic designer.</li>\r\n<li>Using creativity and appreciation for design to website and other graphics for digital media.</li>\r\n<li>Organize meetings and/or calls with internal staff, branch and outside vendors to support the project</li>\r\n<li>Support a variety of other design projects ranging from new packaging design, Point of Sale materials and other company initiatives as needed</li>\r\n<li>Provide weekly update progress reports to share within the department Interact with various departments throughout the organization</li>\r\n<li>Work with admin and procurement for purchase request and proposal.</li>\r\n<li>Communicate with branch for marketing material delivery and stock</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>passion and enthusiasm for design,</li>\r\n<li>a flexible approach when working in a team;</li>\r\n<li>excellent communication skills in Khmer and English</li>\r\n<li>time management skills and the ability to cope with several projects at a time;</li>\r\n<li>being open to feedback and willing to make changes to your designs;</li>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree, diploma or equivalent work experience in commercial art/design is an advantage</li>\r\n<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li>\r\n<li>Adobe Creative Suite skills a must (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign)</li>\r\n<li>Honest, responsible and hard working.</li>\r\n<li>Willingness to work extra hours as required</li>\r\n</ul>',1,53,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,7,5,9,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:38:57','2020-05-28 17:10:31'),
	(671,34,'Senior Settlement and Dispute Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Process reconciliation with CBS, NBC and card scheme</li>\r\n<li>Process settlement and Dispute with NBC and card scheme</li>\r\n<li>Process dispute with NBC and card scheme</li>\r\n<li>Prepare settlement report for booking in CBS</li>\r\n<li>Monitor unsettlement transaction from NBC and card scheme</li>\r\n<li>Actively &amp; timely monitoring transaction risk detection and identification to minimize risk, service interruption and prevention.</li>\r\n<li>Notify Head of ATM Unit/E-channel Manager suspicious and fraudulent transactions immediately.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support to all branches include daily cash transaction and reconciliation.</li>\r\n<li>Produce daily, weekly and monthly settlement, dispute report and other as required.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with Settlement and Dispute at least 1years, especially with VISA/MC &hellip;etc.</li>\r\n<li>Excellence in English communication (both verbal and writing)</li>\r\n<li>Experience with banking sector is preferred.</li>\r\n<li>Quick comprehension, hardworking, and responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Measurement and control reliability</li>\r\n<li>Good integrity, positive attitude, helpful, high commitment, competence and motivation</li>\r\n<li>Able to work in Flexible time environment (night time and holiday)</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,7,3,5,9,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:41:07','2020-06-01 16:51:57'),
	(672,15,'Market and Liquidity Risk Management Officer - 01 post','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Check the requirement of the regulatory bodies especially NBC on the financial risk exposure.</li>\r\n<li>Check the requirement of HKL business partners in term of financial risk exposure.</li>\r\n<li>Identify analyze and evaluate market and liquidity risk within HKL.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor market and liquidity and control to mitigate risk exposure.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and revise market and liquidity risk reporting template.</li>\r\n<li>Produce and update market and liquidity risk report on regular basis.</li>\r\n<li>Produce and update market and liquidity risk report to the Parent bank.</li>\r\n<li>Make recommendation to manage market and liquidity exposure.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other task assigned by manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Graduate in bachelor of Finance, Business Administration, Management, and/or Economics.<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Strong analytical skills.<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good command of Excel<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">English proficiency is an advantage<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Active and dynamic<br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Willing to travel to province</span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:45:26','2020-05-30 18:38:02'),
	(673,20,'Training Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide induction training to new staffs coming on board;</li>\r\n<li>Lead the on Boarding Training Program</li>\r\n<li>Ensure&nbsp; that&nbsp; all&nbsp; new&nbsp; staff&nbsp; attend&nbsp; the&nbsp; induction&nbsp; training&nbsp; program;&nbsp; and&nbsp; play&nbsp; as&nbsp; Training&nbsp; Facilitator&nbsp; on&nbsp; this training program;</li>\r\n<li>Prepare the report of the induction training evaluation and propose to senior management for appropriate change;</li>\r\n<li>Collect TNA once every year from all staff and make consolidation; then present to senior management to come up with the approved annually master training plan;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate&nbsp; all&nbsp; internal&nbsp; and&nbsp; external&nbsp; training&nbsp; program&nbsp; including&nbsp; preparing&nbsp; the&nbsp; training&nbsp; request;&nbsp; training recording and prepare the training contract engagement with staff in appropriate time;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate the training program for new Credit Officer at the field-based with assurance the effectiveness and efficiency of the training program;</li>\r\n<li>Work&nbsp; with&nbsp; related&nbsp; manager&nbsp; to&nbsp; design&nbsp; new&nbsp; technical&nbsp; course&nbsp; and&nbsp; experienced&nbsp; based&nbsp; course;&nbsp; then&nbsp; deliver such a course to staff;</li>\r\n<li>Assist Deputy Head of&nbsp; HR to lead and coordinate the succession&nbsp; planning program through selection the talent&nbsp; pools&nbsp; and&nbsp; build their&nbsp; capacity&nbsp; so&nbsp; that&nbsp; LH&nbsp; MFI&nbsp; staff&nbsp; have&nbsp; opportunity&nbsp; to&nbsp; improve&nbsp; their&nbsp; career advancement which is part of company investment in the long run;</li>\r\n<li>Be a focal person to confirm to Personnel Unit regarding the staff liability on the training that the company has spent for them;</li>\r\n<li>Assist Deputy Head of HR to update the training policy and procedure as needed; and</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Hold Bachelor Degree majoring in management, business administration, or other related fields;</li>\r\n<li>Experience/knowledge in talent management program is a plus;</li>\r\n<li>At least 3-year experience in Training;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in conducting and leading TNA;</li>\r\n<li>Public speaking or ToT Skill</li>\r\n<li>Have good inter personal skill, proactive, and problem solving;</li>\r\n<li>Be honest, high commitment, and flexible;</li>\r\n<li>Be good at both speaking and writing English; and</li>\r\n<li>Be willing to travel to fields or branch networks at rural areas when required.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,8,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 11:49:37','2020-06-01 13:58:36'),
	(674,41,'ហេរញ្ញិក (Teller) - ១២នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>សិក្សា និងអនុវត្តអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ច្បាស់លាស់ និងអភិវឌ្ឍអោយទាន់សម័យជានិច្ចនូវគោលការណ៍ នីតិវិធី និងសេចក្តីណែនាំនានា ដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធនឹងតួនាទីអោយមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ។</li>\r\n<li>រៀបចំ ចាត់ចែង និងត្រួតពិនិត្យ រាល់ប្រតិបត្តិទទួល-បញ្ចេញសាច់ប្រាក់ផ្ទាល់ជាមួយគណនេយ្យករ / មន្រ្តីឥណទាន ឬជាមួយអតិថិជន ក្នុងប្រតិបត្តិការសាខាអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ។</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើការកត់ត្រាបញ្ជូលទិន្នន័យក្នុងកម្មវិធីប្រព័ន្ធ នូវប្រតិបត្តិការសេដ្ឋកិច្ចកើតឡើងទាក់ទងនឹងសាច់ប្រាក់អោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ និងទាន់ពេលវេលា ។</li>\r\n<li>ថែរក្សាទុកដាក់សាច់ប្រាក់ក្នុងប្រតិបត្តិការ និងលិខិតស្នាមទាំងឡាយ ដែលមានតម្លៃស្មើ តាមលក្ខណៈបច្ចេកទេស និងសេចក្តីណែនាំ ។</li>\r\n<li>ទទួលខុសត្រូវលើការដោះស្រាយវិបត្តិបញ្ហាផ្សេងៗ ដែលកើតមានឡើងក្នុងរង្វង់តួនាទី ករណីដែលមិនអាចដោះស្រាយបាន ត្រូវរាយការន៍ជូនអ្នកគ្រប់គ្រងផ្ទាល់ ។</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើកិច្ចការផ្សេងៗទៀតតាមតម្រូវការរបស់អ្នកគ្រប់គ្រង ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>កម្រិតវប្បធម៌ចាប់ពីថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាបត្រឆ្នាំទី៣ ឡើងទៅ ពាក់ព័ន្ធនឹងធនាគារ ទីផ្សារ សេដ្ឋកិច្ច ឬជំនាញពាកើព័ន្ធផ្សេងទៀត</li>\r\n<li>ជានីតិជន ដែលមានសញ្ជាតិខ្មែរ</li>\r\n<li>មានអាយុចាប់ពី ១៨ឆ្នាំ រហូតដល់ ៣០ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>អាចប្រើប្រាស់ភាសាអង់គ្លេស និងកម្មវិធីកុំព្យូទ័រ (Ms. Office)</li>\r\n<li>មានលក្ខណសម្បត្តិសមរម្យ ការប្រាស្រ័យទាក់ទងល្អ មានភាពរួសរាយរាក់ទាក់ និងមានឥរិយាបថចេះបម្រើអតិថិជន</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ ម៉ឺងម៉ាត់ និងឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ក្នុងការងារ</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,28,'12','01/31/2019',1,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 12:02:06','2020-05-30 20:42:32'),
	(675,16,'Digital Marketing Designer - 01 post','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Design​ digital​ marketing​ multi-channel​ campaigns​ that​ range​ from​ display​ ads,​ social​ media,​ emails,​ landing​ pages,​ web​ assets,​ etc.​ including​ print​ marketing​ collaterals,​ signage,​ and​ more.</li>\r\n<li>Google​ AdWords,​ SEO,​ SEM</li>\r\n<li>Google​ Display​ Ad​ Management</li>\r\n<li>Social​ Media​ Ad​ Management</li>\r\n<li>Think​ creatively​ and​ develop​ new​ design​ concepts,​ graphics​ and​ layouts.▪Collaborate​ with​ other​ colleagues​ to​ maintain​ design​ consistency​ and​ coherence​ across​ the​ products​ and​ services.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain​ ABA​ brand​ identity​ so​ it​ remains​ consistent​ and​ is​ used​ properly​ by​ external​ parties/agencies.​</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Degree​ in​ Art/Design​ (e.g.​ interaction,​ graphic,​ visual​ communications,​ industrial),​ or​ a​ related​ field​ or​ equivalent​ practical​ experience.</li>\r\n<li>At​ least​ 2​ years&rsquo;​ experience​ in​ Graphic​ (Visual)​ Design​ with​ focus​ on​ digital​ advertising.</li>\r\n<li>Compelling​ portfolio​ that​ demonstrates​ ability​ to​ create​ great​ work​ (at​ least​ 3​ best​ samples​ of​ your​ work​ in​ each​ field​ of​ expertise).</li>\r\n<li>Thorough​ knowledge​ and​ understanding​ of​ Adobe​ Creative​ Suite​ (Illustrator,​ InDesign,​ Photoshop,​ XD,​ After​ Effect,​ etc.).</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge​ of​ Google​ Web​ Designer​ platform​ and​ main​ principles​ of​ creating​ interactive​ HTML5-based​ designs​ and​ motion​ graphics​ that​ can​ run​ on​ any​ device.</li>\r\n<li>Strong​ visual​ design​ or​ data​ visualization​ skills​ (including​ typography)​ and​ advanced​ animation/motion​ graphic​ skill.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity​ with​ Khmer​ cultural​ factor​ that​ may​ affect​ the​ brand​ or​ product​ presentation​ in​ the​ market.</li>\r\n<li>Ability​ to​ rapidly​ prototype/conceptualize​ the​ ideas.​</li>\r\n<li>Attention​ to​ details.</li>\r\n<li>Self-motivation​ to​ priorities​ and​ manage​ workload​ and​ meet​ critical​ project​ milestones​ and​ deadlines.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,53,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,10,7,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 12:04:13','2020-05-31 23:39:17'),
	(676,15,'Tele-sales Officer - 01 post','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Upsell and cross-sale existing and new customers</li>\r\n<li>Contact potential or existing customers to inform them about a HKL product and promotion based on approved scripts</li>\r\n<li>Response to customers&rsquo; inquiry on company, products or others</li>\r\n<li>Conduct small survey to understand customer requirements</li>\r\n<li>Direct prospects to the field sales team when needed</li>\r\n<li>Enter and update customer information in the database</li>\r\n<li>Handle grievances to preserve the company&rsquo;s reputation</li>\r\n<li>Keep records of calls and sales and note useful information</li>\r\n</ul>','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, Marketing or other equivalent qualification.<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">At least 1 years working experience related to Customer Service/call center<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Knowledge of customer service and selling skill principles and practices<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Ability to work independently with minimal supervision<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Communication skills for negotiation and reconciliation<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Friendly and happy to serve customer<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Computer literacy such as MS Word, Excel and Email<br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Flexibility with hours; weekends as required.</span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 12:06:21','2020-05-31 04:34:10'),
	(677,20,'Recruitment Unit Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Work&nbsp; with&nbsp; DHHR&nbsp; in&nbsp; designing,&nbsp; developing&nbsp; and maintaining&nbsp; the&nbsp; recruitment&nbsp; process&nbsp; in&nbsp; the&nbsp; organization (including&nbsp; its&nbsp; description,&nbsp; recruitment&nbsp; measurement&nbsp; definitions,&nbsp; regular&nbsp; measurement&nbsp; reporting,&nbsp; taking proper actions to close gaps);</li>\r\n<li>Work with Branch Managers and related Head of Departments to recruit staff in response to the organization business plan and up on the request made by hiring managers with assurance of quality and timeliness;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure all the staff hiring process are compliant to the recruitment policy and procedure.</li>\r\n<li>Participate&nbsp; to&nbsp; developEmployer&nbsp; Branding&nbsp; to&nbsp; build&nbsp; institutional&nbsp; awareness&nbsp; among&nbsp; well-known&nbsp; similar industries;&nbsp; Participate&nbsp; in&nbsp; job&nbsp; fairs&nbsp; and&nbsp; career&nbsp; events;&nbsp; as&nbsp; well&nbsp; as&nbsp; to&nbsp; build&nbsp; good&nbsp; relationship&nbsp; with&nbsp; related universities;</li>\r\n<li>Assist&nbsp; the&nbsp; DHHR&nbsp; and&nbsp; HHR&nbsp; in&nbsp; respect&nbsp; of&nbsp; the&nbsp; development&nbsp; of the&nbsp; HR&nbsp; Strategy&nbsp; by&nbsp; reviewing&nbsp; existing&nbsp; policies, procedures and practices detailed in the Recruitment Policies and other documents and develop proposals for amendments and/or the introduction of new policies, procedures and practices in order to ensure comply with the new Prakas or government regulation.</li>\r\n<li>Travelling to all LH MFI branches for visiting to source the candidates and build good relationship with related parties to attract the pool candidates;</li>\r\n<li>Produce weekly and monthly recruitment report in orderto submit to HHR and CEO on regularly basic;and</li>\r\n<li>Perform others tasks which assigned by DHHR.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Hold Bachelor Degree majoring in management, business administration, or other related fields;</li>\r\n<li>At least 3-year experience in recruitment;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum of 2 years managerial experience in a microfinance institution;</li>\r\n<li>Have good inter personal skill, proactive, and problem solving;</li>\r\n<li>Be honest, high commitment, and flexible;</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication skills (able to speak and write English);</li>\r\n<li>Strong leadership and motivational skills;</li>\r\n<li>Strong planning and organizing skills;</li>\r\n<li>Hard-working and able to work under pressure; and</li>\r\n<li>Excellent team-player.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 12:10:24','2020-05-31 09:58:19'),
	(678,41,'មន្រ្តីឥណទានបឋម (Junior Credit Officer) - ២៥នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>សិក្សា និងអនុវត្តអោយបានល្អ ត្រឹមត្រូវ ច្បាស់លាស់ និងអភិវឌ្ឍអោយសម័យកាលជានិច្ចនូវគោលការណ៍ នីតិវិធី និងសេចក្តីណែនាំនានា ដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធនឹងតួនាទីអោយមានប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ។</li>\r\n<li>អនុវត្តកិច្ចការឥណទានក្នុងតំបន់ដែលខ្លួនទទួលខុសត្រូវដោយធានាអនុវត្តអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ច្បាស់លាស់ប្រកបដោយប្រសិទ្ធភាពខ្ពស់ ក្នុងនោះរួមមាន៖ ការចុះផ្សព្វផ្សាយ ការបញ្ចេញឥណទាន ការប្រមូលឥណទាន និងការដោះស្រាយបំណុល ។</li>\r\n<li>ត្រួតពិនិត្យខ្លួនឯង នូវរាល់ភាពអសកម្មការងារ ដើម្បីធ្វើការកែលម្អ និងបំពេញចំណុចខ្វះខាតអោយបានទាន់ពេលវេលា ដើម្បីអនុវត្តការងារមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li>ទំនាក់ទំនងល្អជាមួយបុគ្គលិក មហានគរ អតិថិជន និងអាជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋាន ដើម្បីកសាងកេរ្តិ៍ឈ្មោះវប្បធម៌ល្អប្រពៃរបស់គ្រឹះស្ថាន ។</li>\r\n<li>ការងារពាក់ព័ន្ធផ្សេងៗទៀតត្រូវបែងចែកដោយប្រធានសាមី ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>កម្រិតវ្បធម៌ចាប់ពីថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាបត្រឆ្នាំទី២ ឡើងទៅ</li>\r\n<li>មិនទាមទារបទពិសោធន៍</li>\r\n<li>មានអាយុចាប់ពី ១៨ឆ្នាំឡើងទៅ</li>\r\n<li>ជានីតិជន ដែលមានសញ្ជាតិខ្មែរ</li>\r\n<li>អាចប្រើប្រាស់ភាសាអង់គ្លេស និងកម្មវិធីកុំព្យូទ័រ (Ms. Office)</li>\r\n<li>មានលក្ខណៈសម្បត្តិសមរម្យ ការប្រាស្រ័យទាក់ទងល្អ និងមានឥរិយាបថចេះបម្រើអតិថិជន</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ ម៉ឺងម៉ាត់ និងឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ក្នុងការងារ</li>\r\n<li>អាចធ្វើការនៅតាមបណ្តាខេត្តបាន</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'25','01/31/2019',0,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:00:40','2020-05-27 10:03:54'),
	(679,16,'IT Financial Application Support Officer - 10 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Be responsible for supporting daily core banking operation and financial applications for end users in branches and departments.</li>\r\n<li>Administrate on creating new, transferring and closing users.</li>\r\n<li>Simulate issue in test environment to find out the root cause, then update to Manager.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to perform sundry duties as assigned by supervisor or Manager.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for closing End of Day (EOD), End of Month (EOM), and End of Year (EOY), if necessary change time to night shift, Must to obey the Night Shift rule.</li>\r\n<li>Have to solve problem on day once there is an emergency issue during closing EOD.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the security of the bank information systems and reports.</li>\r\n<li>Regularly update daily and monthly report, then submit to Manager provide sub-tasks.</li>\r\n<li>Provide sub-tasks</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Graduated Bachelor Degree in field of Computer Science or Management Information System.</li>\r\n<li>At least one year experience in daily operation support in micro finance or banking sector.</li>\r\n<li>Have some knowledge of Financial/Accounting principle, Banking business operation, PL/SQL programming, ATM Features and components.</li>\r\n<li>Have experience with Core Banking system, Remittance system (Swift, IME, MoneyGram, Fast), Complaint system (Coral, Temenus), NBC system.</li>\r\n<li>It is plus Well coordination and collaboration work as team.</li>\r\n<li>High commitment to work under pressure and self-motivation, Good integrity, positive attitude and helpful.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Microsoft Offices.</li>\r\n<li>Good speaking and writing skills both in English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work at normal, evening or night time.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'10','01/31/2019',1,7,7,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:02:50','2020-05-30 09:59:43'),
	(680,34,'Senior IT Internal Audit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist in the planning of IT audit plans and understand the specific issues to be evaluated.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in performing internal system audits and risk assessments as directed by Senior IT auditor and/or Head of Internal Audit Unit (IT).</li>\r\n<li>Assist in the preparation of document request lists, testing of design and operating effectiveness of the Bank&rsquo;s IT general controls, application controls, and complimentary user entity controls over financial reporting across multiple environments.</li>\r\n<li>Document and report discrepancies and variances from controls and processes.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in identifying and recommending mitigating business process controls to reduce risks noted in system evaluations.</li>\r\n<li>Directly interface with external IT auditors by providing them with status updates and addressing comments when necessary pertaining to our work papers.</li>\r\n<li>Interact with all levels of management and Company employees.</li>\r\n<li>Assists Internal Audit Manager &amp; Head of Internal Audit Department in evaluating senior auditors and internal auditors&rsquo; performance.</li>\r\n<li>Build and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staffs of areas under review.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors.</li>\r\n<li>Performs related works as assigned by Internal Audit Manager &amp; Head of Internal Audit Department.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in information technology</li>\r\n<li>A minimum of at least 1 years&rsquo; experience in auditing information system logical access, change management, and operations.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of, and experience applying, internal control concepts for business processes from an IT compliance focus.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of internal auditing standards and regulatory legislation.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work independently as well as with team members when needed.</li>\r\n<li>Strong data analytic skills and ability to challenge existing processes and procedures when applicable.</li>\r\n<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills, to effectively present to peers and management.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in performing multiple projects and working with varying team members.</li>\r\n<li>English proficiency: Fluently both speaking and writing</li>\r\n<li>Leadership skills, work and outcome orientation.</li>\r\n<li>Polite, friendly, reflective, communicative, reliable, honest and single-minded</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,7,8,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:06:28','2020-05-29 13:12:59'),
	(681,15,'Call Center Officer - 03 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Obtain client information by answering telephone calls; interviewing clients; verifying information</li>\r\n<li>Determine eligibility by comparing client information to requirements</li>\r\n<li>Inform clients by explaining procedures; answering questions; providing information</li>\r\n<li>Maintain and improve quality results by adhering to standards and guidelines; recommending improved procedures</li>\r\n<li>Accomplish sales and organization mission by completing related results as needed</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by supervisor&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least year 4 Bachelor degree of relevant field.</li>\r\n<li>Exceptional customer service, active listening, and verbal and written communication skills, professional phone voice.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of company products, services, and policies.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency with Ms. Office</li>\r\n<li>Ability to ask prying questions and diffuse tense situations</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility with hours; weekends as required</li>\r\n</ul>',1,57,15,17,'3','01/31/2019',0,5,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:09:30','2020-05-31 11:36:02'),
	(682,34,'Compliance Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>AML System: update CP Bank Black List</li>\r\n<li>Research Webs EU OFAC UN and NBC</li>\r\n<li>Upload document on Intranet</li>\r\n<li>Support branch check AML</li>\r\n<li>FATCA System: Search US Person document , Input Data on system</li>\r\n<li>Compliance Report: Checking Transaction Daily Report</li>\r\n<li>Opening Account, Deposit, Withdrawal, Fund Transfer</li>\r\n<li>Transaction monitoring : Entity &amp; Individual</li>\r\n<li>Checking Transaction Suspicion</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>BA degree in Law.</li>\r\n<li>Good Command of both spoken and written English.</li>\r\n<li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills with an ability to work effectively as a member of a team as well as independently.</li>\r\n<li>Highly responsibility, motivated, organized, adaptable, able to work under pressure and possessing a customer focused attitude.</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated ability to manage complex issues.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,6,7,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:13:07','2020-05-31 09:47:03'),
	(683,13,'នាយកសាខា (Branch Manager) - ០៥នាក់','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">រៀបចំផែនការ យុទ្ធសាស្រ្ត ចាត់ចែង និងដឹកនាំការងារក្នុងសាខា</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ត្រួតពិនិត្យ និងដឹកនាំអនុវត្តអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ច្បាស់លាស់ជានិច្ចតាមគោលការណ៍ នីតិវិធី សេចក្តីសម្រេច និងសេចក្តីណែនាំទាំងឡាយរបស់ ហ្វូណន</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ទទួលខុសត្រូវលើការអនុវត្តផែនការការងារគ្រប់ផ្នែកទាំងការរៀបចំចាត់ចែង ការងារក្នុងរង្វង់ តួនាទីអោយបានល្អ ដឹកនាំការងារអោយមាប្រសិទ្ធភាព ត្រួតពិនិត្យវាយតម្លៃអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ដោះស្រាយរាល់បញ្ហាដែលបានកើតឡើង និងកែលម្អអោយបានទាន់ពេលវេលា ធានាធ្វើយ៉ាងណាអោយការងារប្រព្រឹត្តទៅដោយរលូន និងទទួលបានលទ្ធផលល្អប្រសើរបំផុត</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ចូលរួមក្នុងការជ្រើសរើសធនធានមនុស្ស ដោយធ្វើការចុះតាមដានសាវតា និងសម្រង់ព័ត៌មានដល់លំនៅឋាននៅក្នងតំបន់ប្រតិបត្តិការ ដែលសាខាតាំងនៅ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ធ្វើផែនការលក់ផលិតផល-សេវាកម្ម ផែនការផ្សព្វផ្សាយ និងផែនការថវិការទីផ្សារសម្រាប់សាខា ហ្វូណន អោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវ ច្បាស់លាស់ និងគ្រប់គ្រាន់</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">បញ្ចេញឥណទានអោយបានត្រឹមត្រូវតាមគោលការណ៍ និងគ្រប់គ្រងនូវចំនួនអតិថិជន បរិមាណបញ្ចេញឥណទានតាមផែនការ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ធ្វើកិច្ចការងារតាមតម្រូវការរបស់ថ្នាក់ដឹកនាំ ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">សញ្ញាបត្រផ្នែក ធនាគារ គណនេយ្យ ហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ សេដ្ឋកិច្ច ឬសញ្ញាបត្រដែលមានតម្លៃស្មើ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានបទពិសោធន៍យ៉ាងតិច ០៣ឆ្នាំជាអ្នកគ្រប់គ្រង និង០១ឆ្នាំក្នុងវិស័យមីក្រូហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានជំនាញក្នុងការប្រាស្រ័យទាក់ទង ជាពិសេសជាមួយអតិថិជនគ្រប់ស្រទាប់</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">ជាមនុស្សអំណត់ តស៊ូ ស្វាហាប់នឹងការងារ ជាមនុស្សស្មោះត្រង់ និងមានឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ក្នុងការបម្រើការងារនៅតាមតំបន់ជនបទ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានជំនាញក្នុងវិភាគ និងដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាបានល្អ ក្នុងរង្វង់ការងារទទួលខុសត្រូវរបស់ខ្លួន</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">អាចប្រើប្រាស់ភាសាអង់គ្លេសបានល្អ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានជំនាញក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រង និងដឹកនាំបានល្អ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានជំនាញក្នុងការដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា រក្សាភាពសម្ងាត់ ចេះបត់បែនប្រកបដោយលក្ខណៈអាជីព</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានសមត្ថភាពក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រងការងារចម្រុះ</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'5','02/01/2019',1,6,6,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:16:19','2020-06-01 13:00:47'),
	(684,16,'Payroll Service Officer - 10 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Calling direct to new client for make appointment</li>\r\n<li>Presentation company payroll service to prospect clients</li>\r\n<li>Follow up, convince and negotiate with prospect account to close</li>\r\n<li>Handle request document to sales support and to product team</li>\r\n<li>Gather feedback from client to develop recommended solutions</li>\r\n<li>Handle client complaint, question and other request</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining and developing relationships with existing client in person and via telephone calls and emails</li>\r\n<li>Preparing daily, weekly sale report to Line Manager</li>\r\n<li>Assist Line Manager for achievement target monthly</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with other departments within the organization</li>\r\n<li>Understand payroll competitor on the market</li>\r\n<li>Other task assigned by Line Manager</li>\r\n<li>Provide outstanding and consistent advise and service that will make our customer satisfied, using ABA&rsquo;s defined service standards as a reference point all the times.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Excellent Customer Services Skills</li>\r\n<li>Time management skills</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment</li>\r\n<li>Sales, negotiation and relationship building</li>\r\n<li>Sound written and verbal communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Very good interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'10','01/31/2019',1,4,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:18:02','2020-05-31 10:56:35'),
	(685,15,'Independent Risk Champion - 11 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Oversight the implementation of Credit Procedures, Operational Risk &amp; Fraud Events/risk incidents/operational loss at branch level.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct credit review on post-disbursement to make sure credit file maintain accurate/reliable/sufficient information &amp; match to actual.</li>\r\n<li>Involve in credit review &amp; approval committee at branch level &amp; have authority to comment &amp; risk opinion &amp; voting on loan application</li>\r\n<li>Conduct client visit as well as business assessment &amp; collateral assessment as per required for suspicious or abnormal loan application.</li>\r\n<li>Sample check &amp; review on credit file that assessed by Credit Officer &amp; review the loan application that approved by credit.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze trend of NPL in the operation area &amp; find out the routs cause for reporting to Risk Management Division.</li>\r\n<li>Perform Branch Security Self-Assessment &amp; monitor on top risk at branch level (Operational Risk only).</li>\r\n<li>Act as supporting champion at branch level to support branch staff on AML/CFT/FATCA/ABC agenda.</li>\r\n<li>Perform Compliance Testing/Check to ensure the level of non-compliance is low (base on internal audit finding).</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks as assigned by direct supervisor/management team</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Banking &amp; Finance, Business Management or Economic or other related field.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years experiences in Banking/financial institution, including some experiences in field of risk management, audit &amp; compliance function would be an advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy is a must and excellent communication in English</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical &amp; problem solving skills and willing to work with group &amp; be able to work under pressure.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'11','01/31/2019',0,4,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:21:10','2020-06-01 07:01:30'),
	(686,20,'ប្រធានសាខា (Branch Manager) - ០២នាក់','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ចូលរួមធ្វើផែនការទំលាក់ទុន រៀបចំផែនការយុទ្ធសាស្រ្ត និងជំរុញសកម្មភាពបុគ្គលិកលក់កម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ដឹកនាំ គ្រប់គ្រង ចាត់ចែង និងជំរុញលើកទឹកចិត្តដល់បុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់ដើម្បីអនុវត្តការងារឱ្យមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ដឹកនាំការផ្សព្វផ្សាយផលិតផលដល់អតិថិជន និងតំបន់គោលដៅ ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">សិក្សា និងវាយតម្លៃសំណើកម្ចីដើម្បីរក្សា និងគ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពផលប័ត្រប្រាក់កម្ចី ព្រមទាំងដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាផ្សេងៗនៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">គ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពនៃការបម្រើសេវាកម្មអតិថិជននៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">តាមដានពីការប្រែប្រួលនៃស្ថានភាពទីផ្សារប្រកួតប្រជែង តម្រូវការ ការពេញចិត្ត និងការត្អូញត្អែររបស់អតិថិជន ព្រមទាំងចូលរួមផ្តល់ អនុសាសន៍កែប្រែផលិតផលឥណទានក្នុងករណីចាំបាច់ ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">គ្រប់គ្រងចំណូល និងចំណាយកម្រិតសាខាឱ្យមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">តាមដាន និងជំរុញជាប្រចាំនូវការអនុវត្តទៅលើនីតិវិធីត្រួតពិនិត្យផ្ទៃក្នុង និងធានានូវការប្រតិបត្តិតាម ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">រៀបចំរបាយការណ៍ប្រាក់កម្ចីជូននាយកដ្ឋានគ្រប់គ្រងសាខា និងរបាយការណ៍សំខាន់ៗមួយចំនួនទៀតតាមការស្នើសុំរបស់នាយកដ្ឋានជំនាញដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធ ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ចូលរួមក្នុងដំណើរការជ្រើសរើសបុគ្គលិក និងបង្វឹកដល់បុគ្គលិកកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">បញ្ចប់បរិញ្ញាបត្រជំនាញធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ គ្រប់គ្រងទូទៅ ឬសញ្ញាបត្រពាណិជ្ជកម្ម</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានបទពិសោធន៍វិភាគ វាយតម្លៃក្នុងការផ្តល់កម្ចីតាមបណ្តាមីក្រូហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬធនាគារយ៉ាងតិចបំផុត៥ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានបទពិសោធន៍ក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រង ដឹកនាំ និងលើកទឹកចិត្តបុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់យ៉ាងតិច ២ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានជំនាញដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា ការគិតទុកជាមុន ទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ និងមានភាពច្នៃប្រឌិត</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">មានសមត្ថភាពអាចបំពេញភារកិច្ចនៅក្រោមសំពាធការងារ និងពេលវេលាកំណត់ច្បាស់លាស់</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>ទីតាំងបម្រើការងារ៖</p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">សាខាស្រុកពារាំង</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">សាខាស្រុកស្វាយអន្ទរ</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,21,'2','01/31/2019',1,5,6,5,14,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:25:05','2020-05-29 00:15:36'),
	(687,34,'Training and Development Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Facilitate internal trainings with related departments</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate external trainings with training providers</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate Standard training for new staffs</li>\r\n<li>Develop and regularly update training packages for standard trainings and other internal training</li>\r\n<li>Assist Head of Training Unit to conduct TNA and prepare training calendar</li>\r\n<li>Record all trainings, events, seminars and workshop</li>\r\n<li>Prepare monthly training report to Head of Training &amp; Development Unit</li>\r\n<li>All kind of trainings with departments are on time well-facilitated as a plan</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Business administration or English foreign language</li>\r\n<li>Have a good communication skill</li>\r\n<li>Honesty and integrity</li>\r\n<li>Punctuality and good team work</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','01/31/2019',1,5,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:26:27','2020-05-31 23:07:07'),
	(688,16,'Payroll Service Supervisor - 02 posts','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Work collaboratively with Head of Payroll Service Unit to ensure payroll officers meet/exceed their targets</li>\r\n<li>Oversee day-to-day payroll acquisition operation of the team to ensure payroll officers performance are on track</li>\r\n<li>Regularly conduct assessment to Payroll Officer on Payroll products&rsquo; knowledge are up to date to ensure that they are qualified and competent enough to approach the employer</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that Payroll team are fully followed the processes and procedures of account opening</li>\r\n<li>Closely monitor and review targets/KPIs and take necessary actions to improve team&rsquo;s performance and report to Head of Payroll Service Unit</li>\r\n<li>Keep a close monitoring and updating on competitors&rsquo; marketing campaign &ndash; what and how they do and the impact of those campaigns</li>\r\n<li>Act as a key leader to result and handle ABA&rsquo;s existing and potential customers&rsquo; feedback, suggestions, or complaints</li>\r\n<li>Identify gaps and weaknesses of the team, and initiate ideas on how to improve and breakthrough those barriers</li>\r\n<li>Provide outstanding and consistent advise and service that will satisfy our customer and make them loyal, using ABA&rsquo;s service standards as a reference point all the times.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Minimum 3years experience in relevant supervisory level (prefer sales function)</li>\r\n<li>Organizational and time management skills</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment</li>\r\n<li>Negotiation and internal relationship building</li>\r\n<li>Good written and verbal communication skills</li>\r\n<li>High degree of self-motivation and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Attention to details and accuracy</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'2','01/31/2019',1,5,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:28:19','2020-05-29 13:38:21'),
