/li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Good written and verbal communication skill in both Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Strong interpersonal and relationship building skills.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Computer literacy (Microsoft Office: Word, Excel&hellip;etc.).</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Strong organizational and interpersonal communication skill.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Willing to work at the fields.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Be honest, initiative, hard-working and committed.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">Must be full of energy, time flexible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Location</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">កៀនស្វាយ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">កំពង់ស្ពឺ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">តាខ្មៅ</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">ទឹកថ្លា</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: circle; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding: 0px; font-family: Content, sans-serif; margin: 0px;\">ទីស្នាក់ការកណ្តាល</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,7,'30','01/31/2019',1,4,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-01-20 14:59:20','2020-06-01 07:01:05'),
	(695,15,'Deputy Director, HR for Organizational Development - 01 post','<p>Organizational Development (OD):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be responsible for organization structure design, job/function scope design;</li>\r\n<li>Be responsible for succession planning &amp; talent management to make sure we have someone ready to take over the position if new position made available;</li>\r\n<li>Lead manpower planning and staff budgeting plan;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze objectives of HR based on the approval HR MTBP Plan;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Employee Relation and Communication (ERC):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Manage employee relation by focus on rule, regulation &amp; disciplinary actions;</li>\r\n<li>Handle &amp; solve employee complaints with appropriate &amp; instant actions;</li>\r\n<li>Take care exit interview to improve employee egagement;</li>\r\n<li>Manage activities for enhancing good relationship in all levels employee;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with ministry of labor for all related HR issues such as employment book, working overtime request, staff movement etc;</li>\r\n<li>Manage process of establishment of employee stewards/staff representative;</li>\r\n<li>Lead, develop &amp; manage internal employee engagement and communications strategy and execution;</li>\r\n<li>Handle the induction program for newcomer by working closely with Learning &amp; Development Department (LDD)</li>\r\n<li>Improve internal communication platform;</li>\r\n<li>Control all policies, procedures, memos, and decisions etc;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Performance Management (PM):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Revise PM policy, procedure and form for effective implementation;</li>\r\n<li>Manage process of KPI set up, mid-year and year-end performance review;</li>\r\n<li>Monitor the effective of PM system and redesign if needed;</li>\r\n<li>Manage process of PM rating report producing for HKL management;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in HR and other related field</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years of hands on HR experience</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of staff performance management, employee relations, employee engagement &amp; communication, organization development &amp; strategic initiative and planning</li>\r\n<li>Good communication &amp; interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Great service mind and good team player</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work on multi-task and highly self-motivated</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in MS. Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint), Internet and Email</li>\r\n<li>Good command in English</li>\r\n<li>Strong time management skills</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','02/07/2019',0,5,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-25 13:44:01','2020-05-28 19:56:09'),
	(696,15,'Deputy Director, HR for Compensation & Benefits Management (01 post)','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Implement branding strategy initiatives for both internal and external audiences, including corporate marketing activities.</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Compensation Management:</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Maintain payroll information by designing systeml directing the collection, calculation, and entering data;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Manage payroll record by reviewing &amp; approving changes in exemptions, insurance coverage, saving deductions, and job titles, and department/ division transfer;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Determine payroll liabilities by calculating of employee income, taxes withholding, NSSF, and workers compensation payments</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Benefits Management:</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Manage &amp; administer all HKL staff benefit &amp; making sure it&rsquo;s compliance;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Manage and administer employee welfare;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Manage health &amp; accident insurance with Forte, NSSF, and self-health insurance with HKL;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Oversee &amp; coordinate to get reimbursement from insurance companies based on staff medical claimed;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">HR System and Database Management:Develop &amp; maintain HR system and database (HriS);</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Develop database and execute report as required by management, BoD, Investors, NBC, and related ministries;<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />Ensure new hired employee&rsquo;s record are well kept in HRiS as well as in physical profile;<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />Other Tasks:</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Revise and develop all policies, procedures, and memorandum of Compensation &amp; Beneftis section;</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Produce other adhoc report as assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #333333; font-family: \'Maven Pro\', Roboto, Battambang, Hanuman; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, or other equivalent qualification.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Human Resource, Finance &amp; Banking or other related field</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">At least 3 years of hands on HR generalist experience, preferably in areas of HR administration</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Have knowledge of compensation &amp; benefits management, total reward management &amp; HR database</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good communication &amp; interpersonal skills</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Great service mind and good team player</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Ability to work on multi-task and highly self-motivated</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Computer literacy in MS. Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint), Internet and Email</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Good command in English</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Calibri Light\', sans-serif;\">Strong time management skills</span></li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','02/07/2019',0,5,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-01-25 13:47:17','2020-06-01 12:32:36'),
	(697,23,'Teller Supervisor','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide support in collecting cash and/or loan settlement to the clients and/or staff when necessary;</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for cash in transit with staff within his/her branch and posted into the system;</li>\r\n<li>Check and verify the required principle on Anti-Money Laundering (AML) &amp; Know Your Customer (KYC) policy and guideline and also counterfeit money;</li>\r\n<li>Perform daily cash count of Teller&rsquo;s cash box/Till for end of day closing and ensure cash count sheet is tied up with account statement/cash report produced from system;</li>\r\n<li>Authorize daily transactions booked in system;</li>\r\n<li>Authorize client&rsquo;s collateral within his/her branch i.e. collateral deposit, withdrawal, update etc,</li>\r\n<li>Verify and track document error, master list, repayment schedule, collection sheet, and other problems related to CSO and support in extracting new repayment/LC for concerned CSO to deliver to clients;</li>\r\n<li>Review vouchers such as transfer, interest income, exchange, etc. and ensure completeness of document;</li>\r\n<li>Control monthly rolling cash forecast to ensure sufficient liquidity to support BO;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the updated policies and guidelines issued by Finance Division and relevant departments are fully implemented with his or her own related or assigned responsibilities;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure sense of good customer services is maintained and provided to customer within his/her branch;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure effective liquidity management within his/her branch;</li>\r\n<li>Build and maintain critical relationship with local bank for smooth cooperation and support</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least 2 years of work experience in cashiering and/or accounting, Bachelor University Degree in related field;</li>\r\n<li>Strong computer skills especially on Microsoft Offices, analytical applications, PowerPoint, and other related software;</li>\r\n<li>Excellent command of Khmer language, good understanding, speaking and writing in English language preferred;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure and highly self-motivated;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,22,'1','02/08/2019',1,5,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 13:58:21','2020-05-29 12:08:09'),
	(698,23,'Loan Recovery Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Engage and approach all district branch managers and provincial branch manager to discuss and explore practical technique and strategies to incorporate into the plan;</li>\r\n<li>Formulate plan of detail actions of written off loans from previous and current years;</li>\r\n<li>Set out the detail actions and target of loan write off recoveries down to all the concerned client service officers;</li>\r\n<li>Identify and assess a recovery likelihood of loan write off clients, rating Low, Medium, or High;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with loan officer to identify loan write off clients and classify them into four different categories according to combination of their willingness to pay and capacity to pay.</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with Branch Manager (BM) and Loan Officer (LO) to execute recovery techniques and strategies including, loan write off mapping, regular home visit and chasing, and collecting;</li>\r\n<li>Try to get all the loan write off clients to have commitments with us, and to get them to follow their promise;</li>\r\n<li>Share recovery experiences and lessons learnt to BM and LO to get them better knowledge and understood for improving the loan assessment in the next loans made/originated;</li>\r\n<li>Seek ways to continuously improve performance and productivity on the job;</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with the Credit and Recovery Manager, Regional Manager,and Branch Manager to identify root cause of loan delinquency, operational weaknesses and recommend changes to improve the quality of the portfolio.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks as assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>University degree from any related fields is preferred;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum of 2 years&rsquo; experience in microfinance operations directly dealing with delinquent clients and other problem solving situations;</li>\r\n<li>Must have strong analytical and problem solving skills;</li>\r\n<li>Must have good computer literacy and email;</li>\r\n<li>Must be fluent in the local language (both written and spoken);</li>\r\n<li>Must have the ability to make fair and ethical decisions in tough circumstances;</li>\r\n<li>Must be very organized in order to handle multiple projects simultaneously;</li>\r\n<li>High self-motivation with strong interpersonal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Must have the ability to motivate and persuade others, particularly delinquent clients to repay debt;</li>\r\n<li>Abilities to communicate with local authorities and legal / court members in an articulate and professional manner;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of ethical commitment and trustworthiness.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,25,'3','02/08/2019',1,7,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:01:00','2020-05-31 18:19:15'),
	(699,23,'Senior Research Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Develop research manuals (policy, procedures, data collection tools, data entry and analysis tools, and research report outlines and templates) which are critical and significant for microfinance practitioners;</li>\r\n<li>Initiate, review and/or refine guidelines, tools, and reporting templates of market studies/ research projects to ensure effective and efficient implementation as well as to obtain adequate data for analysis primarily information related to current needs and demands of clients, competitors&rsquo; rolling-out strategies, and industry performance trend;</li>\r\n<li>Take lead in conducting with the whole process of the research/survey projects as assigned by Business Development Manager;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze performance trend of the microfinance industry;</li>\r\n<li>Participate in reviewing existing product/ service strategies and their delivery mechanism, in consultation with operations team and other relevant stakeholders, to ensure the meet of current client&rsquo;s needs and demands;</li>\r\n<li>Report on key findings obtained from market studies/ research projects, draw conclusion and come up with recommendations to address any problems/ challenges encountered to line management and other key management.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in economics, management, marketing, finance or business administration;</li>\r\n<li>At least two-year work related experience in the financial sector especially in the field of market research, product development and project management;</li>\r\n<li>Be capable to systematically and critically think on things need to be done for any specific job assignment;</li>\r\n<li>Must have a strong numeric and analytical skills; Have ability to work independently, self-managed, and proactively as a member of a small, busy team;</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding, speaking and writing in English language;</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of economics and financial topics;</li>\r\n<li>Have excellent computer knowledge &ndash; word processing, spreadsheet, power point, internet and email. Ability to use analytical database such as SPSS or Epi.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','02/08/2019',1,7,7,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:03:12','2020-05-28 04:23:40'),
	(700,23,'Saving Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Daily make appointment, client meeting and persuade customer to open account and deposit with WB Finance;</li>\r\n<li>Travel by motor or car to meet customer at field or village;</li>\r\n<li>Regular calling follow up with customers making good relationship with them and monthly call to maintain existing depositors;</li>\r\n<li>Greet customers in friendly behaviors and notice what each customer wants or needs;</li>\r\n<li>Prepare forms and help customer to fill the customer registration form and opening account forms;</li>\r\n<li>Present WB Finance&rsquo;s products and services features to the public and customers;</li>\r\n<li>Attend the events to build network with potential company &amp; people and attend promotion and sale activation campaign.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Fresh graduated or Bachelor degree in the field of Banking &amp; Finance, Marketing, Economics, Management or other related fields;</li>\r\n<li>At least 1 year experience as a sale people and customer services;</li>\r\n<li>Some knowledges of bank or Microfinance operations in Cambodia;</li>\r\n<li>Good computer skill: Ms. Word &amp; Excel, Internet &amp; Email</li>\r\n<li>Can speak Korean &amp; English for Saving Officer based in Head Office and at provinces, the language require only English &ndash; can be acceptable for fairly speaking and writing;</li>\r\n<li>Good at selling skill and sense of customer services;</li>\r\n<li>Able to travel by motor or car within targeted area.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'3','02/08/2019',1,6,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:05:57','2020-05-29 15:40:47'),
	(701,23,'Underwriting Manager','<ul>\r\n<li>Handle daily MSME/ big loans underwriting process to ensure good loan quality and compliancy and timely delivery. This includes making informed credit decision within assigned approval discretion, preparing, reviewing, submitting and providing recommendations on loan proposals exceeding own approval discretion. Conduct loan assessment at field when necessary or required;</li>\r\n<li>Provide technical support in filling in client&rsquo;s MSME/big loan application and other necessary information to support the full lending process through iPad;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and understand root causes of NPL in respective operational locations and provide reports with recommendation to management;</li>\r\n<li>Properly implement the related audits and quality assurance findings responses, and assist the supervisor in providing necessary support to related peers and colleagues;</li>\r\n<li>Actively contribute to improvement of credit-related policies, procedures and process;</li>\r\n<li>Identify prospective clients, develop profile, approach and attractively promote MSME/big loans and other integrated services (financial literacy, business advice, micro insurance, savings, transfers, exchanges, and else) to prospective clients;</li>\r\n<li>Work with the CRM and involved team to resolve delinquent loans and enhance the credit discipline of clients;</li>\r\n<li>Provide capacity building (including training, coaching, mentoring, feedback, etc) to credit operators such as junior Underwriters, DBMs, BMs and CSOs on credit underwriting skills and loan structuring.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance/Banking, Management, Accounting or other relevant equivalences;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 3 year experiences in credit assessment, loan acquisition, structuring, monitoring and/or other related functions with financial institution including bank and/or MFI;</li>\r\n<li>Must have good analytical skills both quantitatively and qualitatively.</li>\r\n<li>Sound understanding of Cambodian microfinance sector and lending practices;</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal, communication, staff supervision, training and conflict resolution skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good working proficiency of English and basic computer skills including MS Word, Excel, and Power Point;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of commitment and trustworthiness;</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to and/or reside in VFC&rsquo;s operational areas in province/district.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','02/08/2019',1,6,6,5,12,'English','2019-02-03 14:07:21','2020-06-01 04:17:47'),
	(702,23,'Specialized Credit Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>ធ្វើផែន​ការយុទ្ធសាស្រ្ត​ (ប្រាក់បញ្ញើរ ផ្តល់កម្ចី) រយៈពេលខ្លី និង វែង</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើប្រតិបត្តិ​ការ​ផ្ដល់​កម្ចី និង​សេវាប្រាក់​បញ្ញើរ​ គោរព​គោលការណ៍ នីតិវិធី បទដ្ឋានកំណត់ និងអនុវត្តតាមការណែនាំផ្សេងៗ របស់ស្ថាប័ន</li>\r\n<li>ស្វែង​យល់​ពី​បរិយាកាស​គូប្រកួតប្រជែង និង ធ្វើ​ការ​ផ្សព្វ​ផ្សាយផលិតផល និងសេវកម្មរបស់ស្ថាប័ន</li>\r\n<li>ដោះ​ស្រាយ​កម្ចី​មាន​បញ្ហា​ និង​សម្របសម្រួល​រាល់​ការ​តវ៉ា ឬ ទាមទារ​ផ្សេងៗ​របស់​អតិថិជន</li>\r\n<li>ផ្តល់ការណែនាំការហ្វឹកហាត់ ឬការបណ្តុះបណ្តាលចាំបាច់ដល់មន្រ្តីឥណទានកម្រិតចូលថ្មី</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើ​របាយការណ៍បូក​សរុប​ការអនុវត្តផែនការ និង​លទ្ធផល​ការងារ</li>\r\n<li>អនុវត្តការងារ​ផ្សេងៗ​ទៀត​ ដែល​​តម្រូវ​ដោយ​អ្នក​គ្រប់​គ្រង​។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បាន​បញ្ចប់​បរិញ្ញា​ប័ត្រ ​ផ្នែក​ធនាគារ និង ហរិញ្ញវត្ថុ គណនេយ្យ សេដ្ឋកិច្ច និង គ្រប់គ្រងពាណិជ្ជកម្ម</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍ផ្ដល់​ប្រាក់​កម្ចីយ៉ាង​តិចបំផុត​ ២​ឆ្នាំ​ ក្នុង​គ្រឹះ​ស្ថាន​មីក្រូ​ហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬ ធនាគារ</li>\r\n<li>មានចំណេះ​ដឹង​ទាក់​ទង​ទៅ​នឹង​សេវាហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ</li>\r\n<li>ត្រូវមានការប្តេជ្ញាចិត្តខ្ពស់ចំពោះការងារ និង មានសមត្ថភាពក្នុងការធ្វើការក្រោមសម្ពាធ មាន​ចំណេះ​ដឹង​អាច​អាន និង​ សរសេរ​ភាសាអង់គ្លេសបាន​ខ្លះកាន់តែប្រសើរ</li>\r\n<li>មាន​សីលធម៌ល្អ មាន​ឥរិយាបទល្អ មាន​ភាព​ស្រោះ​ត្រង់​ មាន​ការគោរព​វិន័យ</li>\r\n<li>មាន​ចំណេះ​ដឹង​អាច​ប្រើប្រាស់​កម្មវិធី Ms. Office and Ipad/Tablet</li>\r\n<li>អាចធ្វើដំណើរដោយម៉ូតូផ្ទាល់ខ្លួននៅក្នុងតំបន់ដែលបានកំណត់។​</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'50','02/08/2019',1,6,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:09:01','2020-05-29 12:59:45'),
	(703,23,'Personal Assistant & Interpreter (Korean Speaking)','<ul>\r\n<li>Assisting in the oral translation and documentation translation from English to Korean, Korean to Khmer or vice versa;</li>\r\n<li>Travel with CEO to whichever location there business meetings;</li>\r\n<li>Manage all appointments for CEO including correspondence with stakeholders and remind CEO of those appointments, meetings and other events;</li>\r\n<li>Prepare arrangements, necessary materials and logistics for CEO&rsquo;s travel and meetings;</li>\r\n<li>Key person to handle the arrangement of management team meetings and other workshop/meetings in the department including (agendas, reading materials, logistics, minute taking, and follow up with participants etc.);</li>\r\n<li>Take responsible for arrangements of visitor hosting which include calculating hosting fees, providing information, preparing visit itinerary and logistics and transportation, recommending accompanying staff to the field, and other necessary facilitations, etc;</li>\r\n<li>Act as key contact person for any visits to WB FINANACE;</li>\r\n<li>Minute Taker for Senior Management Team meeting and other CEO&rsquo;s meetings as needed;</li>\r\n<li>Effectively manage filing system including important and confidential documents like government&rsquo;s approval, policies and procedures in professional manner;</li>\r\n<li>Draft letters and email messages, memos and letters as requested.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Excellent standard of written and spoken English and Korean.</li>\r\n<li>Graduate/Bachelor degree of business administration or/and related secretarial courses;</li>\r\n<li>Excellent computer skills, especially in Microsoft Word, Excel, Power Point, and Internet and E-mail;</li>\r\n<li>At least one-year experience secretarial work.</li>\r\n<li>Good in organize skills</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal skills, adaptability and flexibility</li>\r\n<li>Good attention to details.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,83,15,17,'1','02/08/2019',1,6,7,5,11,'Khmer, English, Korean','2019-02-03 14:11:36','2020-05-31 02:59:33'),
	(704,23,'Branch HR-Admin Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure the properly arrangement of Branch Operations Team Meeting;</li>\r\n<li>Assist RM in communicating information to all staff and follow up any action point agreed in Branch meeting &hellip;etc;</li>\r\n<li>Purchasing need at Branch Level;</li>\r\n<li>Conduct quotation for purchasing process;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure Timely and adequate printing documents (passbooks, loan documents, staff ID card,&hellip;) are in place to support branch operation;</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with HO Admin Officer to ensure the Insurance for Vehicles, motorbikes and staffs;</li>\r\n<li>Deal with suppliers to do contract for preferred suppliers;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with HO HR Officer for effective employment vacancy announcement;</li>\r\n<li>Process labor books for staffs;</li>\r\n<li>Review HR documents filled &amp; submitted by the staff, regarding to police clearance form, COI, Separation Check list, child protection policy, conflict of interest, commission gift and bribe, sexual harassment, general harassment, and fraud policy;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Liaise with local lawyer and HO legal team for filing complaint&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Graduate/Bachelor degree of Business Administration;</li>\r\n<li>Good computer skills&mdash;Word processing , Spread sheet in Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Cambodian Labor Law;</li>\r\n<li>At least 1-2 years of experience in HR &amp; administrative field;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to understand vehicle/motorbike insurance policies;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to understand and apply WB Finance&rsquo;s structure , plans and strategies&rsquo;;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure and long hours with high self-motivation.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,1,'2','02/08/2019',1,6,3,5,15,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:13:03','2020-05-30 10:03:39'),
	(705,23,'Credit Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>ស្វែងរកអតិថិជនគោលដៅនៅក្នុងតំបន់ប្រតិបត្តិការរបស់ខ្លួន</li>\r\n<li>ទំនាក់ទំនង និង ផ្សព្វផ្សាយផលិតផល ទៅអតិថិជន អាជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋាន និង ភាគីពាក់ព័ន្ឋ</li>\r\n<li>ទំនាក់ទំនងជាមួយអាជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋានដើម្បីប្រមូលព័ត៌មាន និង ដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើការណាត់ជួប និង ពន្យល់អតិថិជនពីលក្ខខណ្ឌដែលអាចទទួលបានប្រាក់កម្ចី</li>\r\n<li>បញ្ចេញប្រាក់កម្ចី និង តាមដានការប្រើប្រាស់ប្រាក់កម្ចីរបស់អតិថិជន បន្ទាប់ពីទទួលប្រាក់កម្ចី</li>\r\n<li>សហការល្អជាមួយមន្រ្តីស្ថាប័នហិរញ្ញវត្ថុផ្សេងទៀត ក្នុងតំបន់ប្រតិបត្តិការរបស់ខ្លួន</li>\r\n<li>ធ្វើការយ៉ាងជិតស្និទ្ធជាមួយមន្ត្រីដោះស្រាយបំណុល ចំពោះប្រាក់កម្ចីដែលមានបញ្ហា។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>កំពុងសិក្សាឬបញ្ចប់ថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាប័ត្រ ​ផ្នែក​ធនាគារ និង ហរិញ្ញវត្ថុ គណនេយ្យ សេដ្ឋកិច្ច និង គ្រប់គ្រងពាណិជ្ជកម្ម</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញក្នុងការប្រាស្រ័យទាក់ទង ការផ្សព្វផ្សាយ ការវិភាគ និង ការគណនា</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ និង ទំនួលខុសត្រូវខ្ពស់ចំពោះការងារ</li>\r\n<li>មានភាពរួសរាយរាក់ទាក់ មានភាពច្បាស់លាស់ និង ម៉ត់ចត់ក្នុងការបំពេញភារកិច្ច</li>\r\n<li>មានការគោរព និង ឥតលំអៀងក្នុងពេលបំពេញភារកិច្ចជាមួយគ្រប់អតិថិជន</li>\r\n<li>មានឆន្ទៈក្នុងការចែករំលែក សហការណ៍ និង បំពេញការងារជាក្រុម</li>\r\n<li>អាចធ្វើដំណើរដោយម៉ូតូជាប្រចាំ និងត្រូវមានប័ណ្ណបើកបរម៉ូតូ ឬរថយន្ត</li>\r\n<li>ត្រូវមានម៉ូតូផ្ទាល់ខ្លួន ដែលម៉ូតូនោះអាចប្រើប្រាស់សម្រាប់ផ្លូវឆ្ងាយបានមានទីលំនៅក្នុងតំបន់ ឬ ខេត្តដែលប្រតិបត្តិការកាន់តែប្រសើរ។</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'50','02/08/2019',1,7,3,5,1,'Khmer','2019-02-03 14:14:30','2020-05-29 01:58:23'),
	(706,23,'Security Specialist','<ul>\r\n<li>To implement security measures and protocols (Security Risk Assessment, and Core Security Requirement especially in new building);</li>\r\n<li>Ensure availability of security equipment in all offices and ensure that it work properly, in accordance to the Office Guideline and Security Policy;</li>\r\n<li>Strengthen control of security camera in all offices, following the standard required;</li>\r\n<li>Conduct safety and security assessments of all offices and make recommendations and check implementation, accordingly;</li>\r\n<li>Review the Security Guard service contract and monitor the services provided in accordance to the protocol to the acceptable standard;</li>\r\n<li>Provide basic orientation to security guard and monitor attendant of Security Guard in all office;</li>\r\n<li>Regularly monitor on security development/concerns in the country or in WB Finance, timely issues security advises to all employees and managers;</li>\r\n<li>Conduct on site visits to assess and monitor the security implementation;</li>\r\n<li>Organize the security training/first-aid training to all staff;</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate basic training and information for visitors;</li>\r\n<li>Provide up to date analysis and information, including alerts, according to agreed criteria for communication and dissemination;</li>\r\n<li>Engage in the disciplinary action to staff who do not comply to security policy.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree of Business Administration or related field;</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years of experience in office and security management or related field;</li>\r\n<li>Be proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint;</li>\r\n<li>Be proficient in English speaking and writing;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of risk management, project management, negotiations, and legal;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to influence and lead subordinates;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to build a cooperative and friendly team;</li>\r\n<li>Good monitoring and follow-up skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good problem solving skills;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to travel to provinces often, sometime travels on weekends and holidays.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','02/08/2019',1,6,7,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:16:19','2020-05-29 17:11:55'),
	(707,23,'Underwriting Support Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Support daily MSME/ big loans underwriting process to ensure good loan quality and compliancy and timely delivery. This includes making informed credit preparing, reviewing, submitting and providing recommendations on loan proposals before submitted to next level. Conduct loan assessment at field when necessary or required;</li>\r\n<li>Provide technical support in filling in client&rsquo;s MSME/big loan application and other necessary information to support the full lending process through iPad;</li>\r\n<li>Conduct random credit quality review post loan disbursement to ensure credit is properly structured and assessed and report to HU;</li>\r\n<li>Communicate with Senior Underwriting and provide reliable information in relation to associated risks which may impact credit quality eg. Commodity price, industry risk, portfolio concentration risk, etc.;</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and understand root causes of NPL in respective operational locations and provide reports with recommendation to management;</li>\r\n<li>Conduct feasibility market/demand studies on MSME loans in respective area. Collect, update and analyze required information relating to key competitors, and clients&rsquo; feedback;</li>\r\n<li>Professionally build personalized and sticky relationship and network with involved stakeholders such as local authorities, merchants, suppliers, existing clients, prospective clients and other referrers to increase MSME/big loans sale;</li>\r\n<li>Provide capacity building (including training, coaching, mentoring, feedback, etc) to credit operators such as junior DBMs, BMs SUs and especially CSOs on credit underwriting skills.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Hold minimum bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance/Banking, Management, Accounting or other relevant equivalences;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years&rsquo; experience in credit assessment, loan acquisition, structuring, monitoring and/or other related functions with financial institution including bank and/or MFI;</li>\r\n<li>Experience with credit administration with financial institution including bank and or MFI is a plus;</li>\r\n<li>Must have good analytical skills both quantitatively and qualitatively;</li>\r\n<li>Sound understanding of Cambodian microfinance sector and lending practices;</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal, communication, staff supervision, training and conflict resolution skills;</li>\r\n<li>Good working proficiency of English and high skills of computer including MS Word, Advance Excel, and Power Point;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of commitment and trustworthiness;</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to and/or reside in WB&rsquo;s operational areas in province/district.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','02/08/2019',1,7,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:18:10','2020-06-01 09:13:48'),
	(708,23,'Branch Manager','<ul>\r\n<li>Coordinate to set up any necessary contingent plan such as growth/expansion, pilot/rollout of ABP, Mobile Banking, new product, process, staff rearrangement, and delinquency management plans;</li>\r\n<li>Regularly conduct market saturation reviews, competition analysis, and update village profile (prospective target clients identification in each village using household list by village, in urban area, and business center) for necessary expansion and acquisition;</li>\r\n<li>Perform strict loan assessment and loan quality check to ensure high loan quality. In the event of many loan requests, proper assignment for DBM, Specialized CSO (SCSO), or trusted CSO are required;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that loan, saving, and other required business transactions are properly entered into iPad and/or system;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure proper loan delinquency management implementation, such as effective follow up, timely issuing notification &amp; demand letters to delinquent clients, appropriate logbook completion and posting into the system, and specific action plan for loan recovery of BO;</li>\r\n<li>Oversee effective liquidity management at the BO, including providing timely support to authorize and/or approve the day end closing report requested by the Branch Teller/Supervisor;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure proper branch financial management;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure all systems, policies and procedures are abided by and implemented in the branch with proper monitoring and control tools;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the implementation of audits, Risk and Quality Assurance Officers, NBC, and raters recommendations/suggestions to improve overall branch performances;</li>\r\n<li>Effectively implement fraud prevention guidelines, like reviewing task rotation report and conducting observation/surprise visits to loan collection and loan disbursement, and meeting with CBMCs/focal persons, clients, and other stakeholders for feedback collection and other verification;</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the quality of information and completeness of loan and saving document prepared by staff under supervision (loan documents, PPI, reports, passbook, vouchers, official receipt, saving contract, saver ID, thumbprint/signature, etc.);</li>\r\n<li>Observe the competitive environment to see its strengths and weaknesses, and properly report to the RM for next strategy development and action;</li>\r\n<li>Review the BO expenditures and income to be more efficient and sustainably profitable.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Management, Economic, Finance &amp; Banking, Accounting, Marketing or other equivalences;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years experience in microfinance operations and management &amp; staff supervisory;</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Cambodian microfinance sector</li>\r\n<li>Good working knowledge of English and computer skills especially on MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal, communication, staff supervision, training and management skills;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure and be highly self-motivated.</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of ethical commitment and trustworthiness.</li>\r\n<li>Must be willing to work and live in the district.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp;<strong>Samrong (Siem Reap); Chul Kiri; Sangkum Thmei</strong></p>',1,36,15,28,'3','02/08/2019',1,5,6,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-03 14:21:11','2020-05-27 13:59:16'),
	(709,15,'Deputy Director of PMO, Corporate Branding Management','<p><strong>Corporate Branding Management:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Implement branding strategy initiatives for both internal and external audiences, including corporate marketing activities.</li>\r\n<li>Engage necessary research to regularly assess market trends, competitor activities, customer behavior and company brand equity.</li>\r\n<li>Oversee PR Plan, manages relevant communication strategy to strengthen public and corporate brand image.</li>\r\n<li>Develop necessary internal communication to staff and lead company culture building initiatives by working closely with Marketing and HR teams, e.g. performance-based, digital embracement culture, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Provide guideline, work closely and review with Marketing, Product, Branch support teams to ensure effective execution to deliver brand promise (culture, e.g. product, advertising, premise, customer interaction, etc,)</li>\r\n<li>Liaise with parent group company to build synergy and enable best practice sharing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Project Management:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Track, analyze, and report progress of key project portfolio under responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Undertake different role(s) within project management. Depending on nature of each project:</li>\r\n<li>Primary role is to lead/manage transformative project to align with corporate strategic direction; the role requires end-to-end management of project delivery which include business requirement development, activity planning, risk/benefit identification, cross functional coordination, and effective project closure monitoring.</li>\r\n<li>As and when required, perform business analyst role to support functional teams.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate across key stakeholders to ensure effective changes and collaboration in the organization</li>\r\n<li>Foster a collaborative working environment with functional teams.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, or other equivalent qualification</li>\r\n<li>Degree or professional qualification in marketing or , Journalism, or Business related fields (MBA is preferred)</li>\r\n<li>5 years proven working experiences, including 3 years in Management position, 3-4 years in Marketing and relevant skill)</li>\r\n<li>Experience in brand management, engagement campaign development and experiential marketing,</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication (both written and verbal), influencing and negotiation skills, required to cooperate with a wide range of internal and external stakeholders combined with driven and assertive personality</li>\r\n<li>Experience in customer segmentation and successful communication campaigns, supported by data-analysis and market insight, required to deliver successful customer communication campaign</li>\r\n<li>Experience in people management, leading and directing multiple team members in a busy task-oriented environment,</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and understanding of mass/marketing-communication systems</li>\r\n<li>Evidence of strong management, planning, project management and organizational skills</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility with work location.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,85,15,17,'1','02/15/2019',0,11,6,5,14,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:09:52','2020-05-31 00:28:35'),
	(710,15,'Officer, Credit Administration','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Coordinate loan application processing from branches to Head Office</li>\r\n<li>Controle and monitor Credit Committee Resolution</li>\r\n<li>Prepare loan contract and other required document for branches to signofff with clients</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with clients for loan review, insurance renewal, and other legal documents</li>\r\n<li>Input loan applications into system through data entry process</li>\r\n<li>Adminstrate approved loan file including loan application, collateral and securities documents</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks assigned by supervisor</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, or other equivalent qualification</li>\r\n<li>At least 1 years working experience related to credit and/or financial analysis</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding and knowledge of microfinance and banking sector</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal communication, team work, and result-oriented</li>\r\n<li>Sound computer literacy, particularly in Word, Excel, Internet, and Email</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English is a plus advantage.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'3','02/15/2019',0,5,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:11:33','2020-05-28 01:56:13'),
	(711,16,'IT Support Officer','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Prepare and maintain IT operation, application and IT planning.</li>\r\n<li>Managing corporate IT infrastructure includes VPN connectivity, Router, Switch and LAN maintenance, virus protection, phone system, power management, and camera security.</li>\r\n<li>Perform minor repairs to hardware, software and equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Set up equipment for employee use, performing or ensuring proper installation to investigate and resolve problems and to provide technical assistance and support.</li>\r\n<li>Develop training materials and procedures, and/or train user in the proper use of hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li>ATM &amp; POS terminal installation and maintenance.</li>\r\n<li>ATM cash loading.</li>\r\n<li>Provide POS terminal training.</li>\r\n<li>Support other POS &amp; ATM related task as required by Terminal Team.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in IT, networking or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years working experience in managing operation of IT operation, maintenance and database.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Windows operation under CISCO, VB 6.0 or VB.NET, MS Access, MS SQL Server, Phone System.</li>\r\n<li>Have experienced with MFI or Bank would be advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to understand banking procedures, regulation and business.</li>\r\n<li>Good command of Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li>Good communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'4','03/01/2019',1,6,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:17:24','2020-05-31 06:29:48'),
	(712,16,'ATM/POS Terminal Officer','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>IT task to support card system working smoothly.</li>\r\n<li>Fix and repair (if possible) for any PC problem, printer, and other equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Installation POS, ATM, PC, Server and some other equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Support and fix some issue from terminal team or IT.</li>\r\n<li>Instruction customer or internal employee to operation well with the terminal or PC.</li>\r\n<li>Support customer request related to technology requirement.</li>\r\n<li>POS terminal training when new pos deploy or when customer (in-house or merchant) request a new training session.</li>\r\n<li>Schedule visiting merchant to make strong relationship and get info update from merchant requirement and improvement poor services.</li>\r\n<li>ATM controlling and monitoring, status, connection and other support.</li>\r\n<li>Visit ATM when requested by branch or other department of problem occurred at the terminals.</li>\r\n<li>On site visit merchant when problem occur sometime at night time not only working hours.</li>\r\n<li>Troubleshooting with card system &amp; terminal team of any issue occurred with technical issue.</li>\r\n<li>ATM cash loading, ATM cash reporting and refill receipt delivery.</li>\r\n<li>ATM maintenance and fix issue that come from dusty.</li>\r\n<li>Collect captured card and return to customer representative.</li>\r\n<li>Installation, maintenance and update ATM &amp; POS application and also PC.</li>\r\n<li>Configuring ATM application parameters and POS terminal parameters.</li>\r\n<li>Installing new connection and connect with new installation for ATM, POS and PC.</li>\r\n<li>Troubleshooting with connection provider when connection down took place.</li>\r\n<li>Report immediately of any case urgent needed to be fix due to bank operation or customer needs.</li>\r\n<li>Report to card system, terminal team or clearing regarding to customer complain about POS terminal or ATM machine failure or merchant account is not credit and more.</li>\r\n<li>Arrange schedule for ATM maintenance, merchant&rsquo;s side visit.</li>\r\n<li>Support customer via call or direct visit.</li>\r\n<li>Training how to use POS/ATM in-house and customer.</li>\r\n<li>Come to check and fix problem at office or at merchant site when issue came from technical issue.</li>\r\n<li>Site visit ATM every week at night time and create report for improvement.</li>\r\n<li>Other ad-hoc tasks to be sure the system working smoothly, testing.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul class=\"bullet-red\">\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in business, communications, computer science, IT or equivalent work or educational experience.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in ATM switching system, card management system and card personalization software.</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge in ATM and POS implementation and management.</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge in credit card, debit card and prepaid card operation.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of financial/accounting principles, banking operation, e-banking features and components.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum two years working experience in ATM switching/card management system or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Very good interpersonal skills and communications skills (oral and written) in English language.</li>\r\n<li>Good project management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good integrity, positive attitude, helpful, high commitment, competence and motivation.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,23,'1','03/01/2019',1,8,7,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:20:47','2020-05-30 07:55:21'),
	(713,20,'Branch Manager','<ul>\r\n<li>ចូលរួមធ្វើផែនការទំលាក់ទុន រៀបចំផែនការយុទ្ធសាស្រ្ត និងជំរុញសកម្មភាពបុគ្គលិកលក់ក្នុងកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>ដឹកនាំ គ្រប់គ្រង ចាត់ចែង និងជំរុញលើកទឹកចិត្តបុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់ដើម្បីអនុវត្តការងារអោយមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li>ដឹកនាំការផ្សព្វផ្សាយផលិតផលដល់អតិថិជន និងតំបន់គោលដៅ ។</li>\r\n<li>សិក្សា និងវាយតម្លៃសំណើកម្ចីដើម្បីរក្សា និងគ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពផលប័ត្រប្រាក់កម្ចី ព្រមទាំងដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាផ្សេងៗនៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងគុណភាពនៃការបម្រើសេវាកម្មអតិថិជននៅកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n<li>តាមដាននៃការប្រែប្រួលនៃស្ថានភាពទីផ្សារប្រកួតប្រជែង តម្រូវការ ការពេញចិត្ត និងការត្អូញត្អែររបស់អតិ់ថិជន ព្រមទាំងចូលរួមផ្តល់អនុសាសន៍កែប្រែផលិតផលឥណទានក្នុងករណីចាំបាច់ ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងចំណូល និងចំណាយកម្រិតសាខាអោយមានប្រសិទ្ធភាព ។</li>\r\n<li>តាមដាន និងជំរុញជាប្រចាំនូវការអនុវត្តលើនីតិវិធីត្រួតពិនិត្យផ្ទៃក្នុង និងធានានូវការប្រតិបត្តិតាម ។</li>\r\n<li>រៀបចំរបាយការណ៍ប្រាក់កម្ចីជូននាយកដ្ឋានគ្រប់គ្រងសាខា និងរបាយការណ៍សំខាន់ៗមួយចំនួនទៀតតាមការស្នើសុំរបស់នាយកដ្ឋានជំនាញដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធ ។</li>\r\n<li>ចូលរួមក្នុងដំណើរការជ្រើសរើសបុគ្គលិក និងបង្វឹកដល់បុគ្គលិកកម្រិតសាខា ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បញ្ចប់បរិញ្ញាបត្រជំនាញធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ គ្រប់គ្រងទូទៅ ឬសញ្ញាបត្រពាណិជ្ជកម្ម</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍វិភាគ វាយតម្លៃក្នុងផ្តល់កម្ចីតាមបណ្តាហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ ឬធនាគារយ៉ាងតិចបំផុត ៥ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍ក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រង ដឹកនាំ និងលើកទឹកចិត្តបុគ្គលិកក្រោមបង្គាប់យ៉ាងតិច ២ឆ្នាំ</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា ការគិតទុកជាមុន ទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ និងមានភាពច្នៃប្រឌិត</li>\r\n<li>មានសមត្ថភាពអាចបំពេញភារកិច្ចនៅក្រោមសំពាធការងារ និងពេលវេលាកំណត់ច្បាស់លាស់</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>ទីតាំងបម្រើការងារ៖</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>សាខាស្រុកពារាំង</li>\r\n<li>ស្រុកស្វាយអន្ទរ</li>\r\n<li>ស្រុកបាកាន</li>\r\n<li>សាខាខេត្តរតនគីរី</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'4','02/15/2019',1,6,6,5,14,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:40:18','2020-05-27 23:51:01'),
	(714,20,'Officer, Nano Credit','<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ផ្សព្វផ្សាយពីផលិតផលឥណទានណាណូដល់អតិថិជនសក្កានុពលនៅក្នុងតំបន់គោលដៅ ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">កំណត់យុទ្ធសាស្រ្តលក់ផលិតផលឥណទានណាណូ ថែរក្សាអតិថិជន និងស្រាវជ្រាវទីផ្សារ/គូប្រកួតប្រជែង ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ប្រមូលព័ត៌មាន វាយតម្លៃកម្ចី និងតាមដានការប្រើប្រាស់កម្ចីរបស់អតិថិជន ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ធ្វើការទំនាក់ទំនងល្អជាមួយអាជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋានក្នុងការផ្តល់កម្ចីរបស់អតិថិជន ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ដោះស្រាយបញ្ហាក្នុងករណីមានកម្ចីយឺតយ៉ាវ ។</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: disc; font-size: 13px; border-color: #0dc2c9; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; font-family: Content, sans-serif;\">ធ្វើរបាយការណ៍ជូនប្រធានសាខា ប្រចាំសប្តាហ៍ ប្រចាំខែស្តីពីសមិទ្ធផល និងបញ្ហាប្រឈមផ្សេងៗ ។</li>\r\n</ul>','<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">សាខាប្រតិបត្តិការរួមមាន៖&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;\">សាខាអូរឬស្សី សាខាច្បារអំពៅ សាខារតនៈគិរី សាខាខេត្តកំពង់ចាម សាខាស្រុកជើងព្រៃ សាខាស្រុកបាធាយ សាខាខេត្តត្បូងឃ្មុំ សាខាខេត្តកំពង់ស្ពឺ សាខាស្រុកអង្គស្នួល សាខាស្រុកកណ្តាលស្ទឹង សាខាស្រុកសំរោងទង សាខាខេត្តបាត់ដំបង សាខាស្រុកមោងឬស្សី សាខាស្រុករតនៈមណ្ឌល សាខាស្រុកបាកាន សាខាស្រុកភ្នំព្រឹក សាខាស្រុកបរវេល សាខាស្រុកពារាំង សាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្របែក សាខាស្រុកព្រះស្តេច សាខាស្រុកស្វាយអន្ទរ សាខាស្រុកបាទី សាខាស្រុកត្រាំកក់ សាខាស្រុកគិរីរង់ សាខាស្រុកកោះអណ្តែត សាខាស្រុកព្រៃកប្បាស សាខាស្រុកប្រាសាទបាគង សាខាក្រុងសិរីសោភ័ណ សាខាក្រុងបាវិត សាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្រាច និងសាខាស្រុកកំពង់ត្រឡាច។</span></p>',1,71,15,28,'60','02/15/2019',1,9,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:44:49','2020-05-31 19:28:50'),
	(715,34,'Operationals Risk Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Check compliance of Risk Policies: Make sure CPB is following exactly what policies written and propose and changes to update policies in conformity with new conditions or new market practices.</li>\r\n<li>Report discrepancies and mistakes: Report to board of management any significant discrepancies or deficiency in policies and in implementing policies amongst departments.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Operational Risk activities: Coordinate with Operational Risk team to follow activities in ORM framework including RCSA programs, finding out root causes of incidents in Operational Risk reports, review and updating KRIs from operational functions in the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Working with Branch Managers: Coordinate with branch managers under operational risk program in terms of collecting loss incidents, holding RCSA workshops.</li>\r\n<li>Consolidate and maintain ORMU&rsquo;s data: Coordinate with team works and the Risk Owners to collect RCSA &amp; KRI Report then input onto System and keep update as per required by line manager.</li>\r\n<li>Working with HR, Heads of Departments to collect KRIs.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Others: to be assigned by line manager</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Be able to travel to Provinces</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work as TEAMWORK</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','02/15/2019',1,7,3,5,1,'English','2019-02-05 10:49:08','2020-06-01 15:37:55'),
	(716,34,'Senior Operationals Risk Officer','<ul>\r\n<li>Check compliance of Risk Policies: Make sure CPB is following exactly what policies written and propose and changes to update policies in conformity with new conditions or new market practices.</li>\r\n<li>Report discrepancies and mistakes: Report to board of management any significant discrepancies or deficiency in policies and in implementing policies amongst departments.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Operational Risk activities: Coordinate with Operational Risk team to follow activities in ORM framework including RCSA programs, finding out root causes of incidents in Operational Risk reports, review and updating KRIs from operational functions in the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Working with Branch Managers: Coordinate with branch managers under operational risk program in terms of collecting loss incidents, holding RCSA workshops.</li>\r\n<li>Consolidate and maintain ORMU&rsquo;s data: Coordinate with team works and the Risk Owners to collect RCSA &amp; KRI Report then input onto System and keep update as per required by line manager.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor KRI Reports: Coordinate with Risk Owners across Branches &amp; HQ to ensure that the KRI Reports are working effective and fluently at a timely manner.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare Master Plan for ORMU Trip: Work with the team to initiate the Branch visit plan by month/semester.</li>\r\n<li>Others: to be assigned by line manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Be able to travel to Provinces</li>\r\n<li>Concern for Quality &amp; Standards</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrates Initiative</li>\r\n<li>Developing People</li>\r\n<li>Results Orientation</li>\r\n<li>Develops and Applies Business Knowledge</li>\r\n<li>Planning &amp; Co-coordinating</li>\r\n<li>Influences Outcomes</li>\r\n<li>Supporting &amp; Managing Change</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','02/15/2019',1,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-02-05 10:50:39','2020-05-29 06:38:56'),
	(717,31,'Branch Manager - 03 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Manage the operational plan, internal control system, and sufficient fund maintenance at branch to&nbsp; &nbsp;be effectively&nbsp; &nbsp;implemented,&nbsp; &nbsp;executed&nbsp; &nbsp;followed&nbsp; &nbsp;by&nbsp; &nbsp;policies&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;ensuring&nbsp; &nbsp;all&nbsp; &nbsp;financial transactions&nbsp; are&nbsp; authorized&nbsp; at&nbsp; the&nbsp; right&nbsp; time,&nbsp; the&nbsp; utilization&nbsp; of&nbsp; financial&nbsp; assets&nbsp; is&nbsp; made&nbsp; in&nbsp; the manner&nbsp; of&nbsp; minimizing&nbsp; cost,&nbsp; and&nbsp; maximizing&nbsp; profit&nbsp; including&nbsp; financial&nbsp; data&nbsp; is&nbsp; always&nbsp; updated properly</li>\r\n<li>Manage&nbsp; all&nbsp; income&nbsp; and&nbsp; expense&nbsp; transactions&nbsp; by&nbsp; reviewing&nbsp; strictly&nbsp; and&nbsp; authorizing&nbsp; all&nbsp; sufficient support&nbsp; documents&nbsp; of&nbsp; transactions&nbsp; possess,&nbsp; and&nbsp; ensure&nbsp; that&nbsp; all&nbsp; accounting&nbsp; documents&nbsp; are always&nbsp; ready&nbsp; for&nbsp; internal&nbsp; and&nbsp; external&nbsp; check&nbsp; with&nbsp; all&nbsp; transactions&nbsp; are&nbsp; recorded&nbsp; into&nbsp; the&nbsp; right accounting code when generating reports are required</li>\r\n<li>Manage&nbsp; the&nbsp; fixed&nbsp; assets&nbsp; by&nbsp; ensuring that&nbsp; the&nbsp; development&nbsp; and&nbsp; implementation&nbsp; of&nbsp; systems tracking and controlling the utilization and movement of assets at branch are effectively and efficiently used</li>\r\n<li>Review, analyze, and approve loan disbursement with maintaining portfolio in a very good quality by ensuring a proper documentation which is used for client&rsquo;s collateral to meet the minimum requirement</li>\r\n<li>Manage&nbsp; and&nbsp; lead&nbsp; the&nbsp; operation&nbsp; on&nbsp; the&nbsp; marketing&nbsp; campaign&nbsp; by&nbsp; promoting&nbsp; the&nbsp; products&nbsp; and services&nbsp; to&nbsp; ensure&nbsp; that&nbsp; the market&nbsp; share&nbsp; and&nbsp; expanding&nbsp; its&nbsp; operation&nbsp; without&nbsp; encountering&nbsp; risks&nbsp; are&nbsp; effectively executed at the under control area</li>\r\n<li>Manage&nbsp; actively&nbsp; in&nbsp; facilitating&nbsp; the&nbsp; general&nbsp; process&nbsp; of&nbsp; government&nbsp; relation&nbsp; at&nbsp; branch&nbsp; level&nbsp; by ensuring&nbsp; &nbsp;the&nbsp; &nbsp;efficient&nbsp; &nbsp;coordination&nbsp; &nbsp;with&nbsp; &nbsp;local&nbsp; &nbsp;authority&nbsp; &nbsp;in&nbsp; &nbsp;processing&nbsp; &nbsp;paper work,&nbsp; &nbsp;legal compliance and coping with problem solving</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration, Management, and other related fieldsAt least 3-year-experience in banking industry related to credit loan management</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of industry rules, regulations, and good at results driven attitude</li>\r\n<li>Good at management skills, outstanding organization, strong customer service, written and oral communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Good at both English user and computer literacy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Angk Snuol District Branch-Baek Chan Commune</li>\r\n<li>Tuol Kouk Branch</li>\r\n<li>Chraoy Chongvar Branch</li>\r\n</ol>',1,36,15,28,'3','03/08/2019',1,10,6,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-02-23 11:39:33','2020-05-29 18:59:54'),
	(718,31,'Relationship Management Supervisor - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Review, analyze and examine loan decision making in accordance with Sathapana bank\'s policy and&nbsp; procedure&nbsp; to&nbsp; ensure&nbsp; the&nbsp; quality&nbsp; of&nbsp; both&nbsp; credit&nbsp; and&nbsp; loan&nbsp; disbursement&nbsp; against&nbsp; all&nbsp; types&nbsp; of risks</li>\r\n<li>Monitor&nbsp; the&nbsp; settlement&nbsp; of&nbsp; loans&nbsp; repayments&nbsp; and&nbsp; analyze&nbsp; the&nbsp; credit&nbsp; reports&nbsp; including&nbsp; clients&rsquo; collateral&nbsp; with&nbsp; individual&nbsp; Relationship&nbsp; Management&nbsp; Assistant&nbsp; by&nbsp; ensuring&nbsp; the&nbsp; accurate&nbsp; credit quality reporting</li>\r\n<li>Lead the RMA team in reviewing, analyzing, and making the decision on the amount of clients&rsquo; loan&nbsp; attached&nbsp; with&nbsp; asset&nbsp; to&nbsp; ensure&nbsp; the&nbsp; effectiveness&nbsp; of loan&nbsp; disbursement&nbsp; that&nbsp; not&nbsp; adversely affect the communities</li>\r\n<li>Oversee and managing branch performance on credit loan by strengthening an individual credit agent&rsquo;s productivity and support all challenges RMAs and RMOs face at the real practice</li>\r\n<li>Participate, observe, and study the credit loan market in the operational areas by analyzing the strengths,&nbsp; weaknesses,&nbsp; opportunities&nbsp; and&nbsp; constraints&nbsp; of&nbsp; branch\'s&nbsp; operations&nbsp; to&nbsp; ensure&nbsp; the effective leading of promoting activities of Sathapana Bank&rsquo;s services and products</li>\r\n<li>Assist&nbsp; branch&nbsp; manager&nbsp; in&nbsp; distributing&nbsp; information&nbsp; both&nbsp; internally&nbsp; and&nbsp; externally&nbsp; to&nbsp; Relationship Management Assistants and Officers through meetings</li>\r\n<li>Support branch manager by observing, planning and coaching the poor performers at branch to ensure the employees&rsquo; capacity development</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration, Management, and other related fields</li>\r\n<li>At least 3-year-experience in banking industry related to credit loan management</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of industry rules, regulations, and good at results driven attitude</li>\r\n<li>Good at management skills, outstanding organization, strong customer service, written and oral communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Good at both English user and computer literacy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Location:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Phnom Penh Thmey Branch -Boeng Chhouk</li>\r\n<li>Main Branch</li>\r\n</ol>',1,71,15,17,'2','03/08/2019',1,10,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-02-23 11:42:43','2020-05-31 15:46:13'),
