	(725,31,'Senior IT Network Administration Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Coordinate&nbsp; &nbsp;the&nbsp; &nbsp;design,&nbsp; &nbsp;installation,&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;connectivity&nbsp; &nbsp;of&nbsp; &nbsp;computer&nbsp; &nbsp;systems&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;network infrastructure to ensure the stable operation of the bank&rsquo;s IT assets</li>\r\n<li>Develop,&nbsp; configure,&nbsp; maintain,&nbsp; support,&nbsp; and&nbsp; optimize&nbsp; all&nbsp; new&nbsp; and existing&nbsp; network&nbsp; hardware, software, and communication links</li>\r\n<li>Design&nbsp; and&nbsp; implement&nbsp; the&nbsp; strategic&nbsp; plans&nbsp; on&nbsp; the&nbsp; varying&nbsp; terms&nbsp; to&nbsp; make&nbsp; a&nbsp; certain&nbsp; network capacity meets existing and future requirements</li>\r\n<li>Provides &ldquo;ownership&rdquo; of problem through final resolution</li>\r\n<li>Plan, acquire, and coordinate installation of in-house and remote hardware and software across the bank&rsquo;s network</li>\r\n<li>Conduct&nbsp; research&nbsp; and&nbsp; make&nbsp; recommendations&nbsp; on&nbsp; network&nbsp; products,&nbsp; services,&nbsp; protocols,&nbsp; and standards in support of network procurement and development efforts</li>\r\n<li>Perform cost-benefit and return of investment analysts for proposed systems to aid management in making implementation decisions</li>\r\n<li>Test&nbsp; network&nbsp; performance,&nbsp; develop&nbsp; strategies&nbsp; for&nbsp; maintaining&nbsp; network&nbsp; infrastructure,&nbsp; and provide network performance statistics and reports</li>\r\n<li>Direct and administrate a contingent of network analyst and technicians, and where necessary, conduct performance reviews and corrective action</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor in computer science,certifications of CCNA, CCNP, CCIE, CCNA and other related fields</li>\r\n<li>At least 2-year-experience in managing and configuring enterprise-wide, LANs, WANs, WLANs, VPNs, and 2 years of a successful leadership