	(759,19,'Software Developer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Develop, maintain, enhance and troubleshoot existing applications.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute in all phases of the development lifecycle.</li>\r\n<li>Build reusable code and libraries.</li>\r\n<li>Write well designed, testable, efficient code.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent. Fresh graduate is encouraged to apply</li>\r\n<li>Good with logical analysis, data structure and algorithms</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge and understanding on OOP and design patterns</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Relational Databases and ORM technologies</li>\r\n<li>Experience in Java and Spring Framework is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Quick learner and passionate about IT</li>\r\n<li>Good inter-personal and communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Capability to work independently, creatively and good teamwork</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','04/19/2019',1,5,7,5,9,'English','2019-04-06 10:05:47','2020-05-29 21:44:30'),
	(760,19,'BI Report Developer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Understand the business requirements and design reports for Business.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in business analysis activities to gather requirement.</li>\r\n<li>Provide training and assistance to users for generation of adhoc report.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support as required to ensure the availability and performance of developed report.</li>\r\n<li>Performance tuning experience related to reporting queries.</li>\r\n<li>Develop/enhance report reports based on Jasper Report and Oracle BI.</li>\r\n<li>Translate business requirement into specifications that will be used to implement the reports and dashboards.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in computer science or equivalent</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical, conceptual and problem-solving ability</li>\r\n<li>Strong skill in SQL, PL/SQL and knowledge of Relationship Databases (Oracle, PostgreSQL and SQL Server)</li>\r\n<li>Strong Skills in query tuning</li>\r\n<li>Understand key Financial and Banking concepts</li>\r\n<li>Basis understanding with Data Warehouse concepts</li>\r\n<li>Creative, good problem solving and research skills</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','04/19/2019',1,7,7,5,9,'English','2019-04-06 10:08:27','2020-05-31 18:05:51'),
	(761,19,'Chief Credit Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Take the lead in promoting Company&rsquo;s products and services to potential clients and local authorities.</li>\r\n<li>Liaise and build good cooperation with local authority, partner, and all stakeholder.</li>\r\n<li>Study to understand policy, procedure, and guidelines related to providing and collecting loans, and guide credit officer regularly.</li>\r\n<li>Assess local market conditions and identify current and prospective sales opportunities for Loan and none loan services.</li>\r\n<li>Train Credit officer how to inspect and analyze record and attitude of loan application in order to ensure that such borrowers are truly adequately qualified for loan, as stated in the loan policy, and that they can perform all requirements for loan security.</li>\r\n<li>Take part with Credit officers in explaining and educating the loan application about the credit policy and procedure in a way that the loan applicants are aware that the loan including principal and interest shall be repaid regularly according to the schedule in the loan contract.</li>\r\n<li>Review all loan documents which a Loan officer has made in order to ensure good, clear, accurate, and adequate implementation of the credit policy and guidelines of the higher management before submitting them to higher management for approval.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and follow up customer repayment reports daily. In cases where there is a customer later repayment, it is necessary to arrange a credit officer responsible for accessing the client\'s residential or business premises so that they can study and solve the problem in a timely manner, avoiding the debt being a serious debt.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in staff performance appraisal under its direct supervision.</li>\r\n<li>Advise Credit officers to be aware and take responsibilities to monitor the situation and the borrowers and properties mortgaged, at least once within 6 months.</li>\r\n<li>Day-to-day manage Credit Officers at the branch by follow up the individual staff Performance, Identify the Training need, provide supporting to improve their performance, and participate of the capacity building.</li>\r\n<li>Address customer and employee satisfaction issues promptly.</li>\r\n<li>Adhere to high ethical standards and comply with all regulations/applicable laws.</li>\r\n<li>Approve the loan by given authorization.</li>\r\n<li>Review loan reports and others.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other duties assigned by superiors.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor of Business Administration in Management or Finance and Banking or in any related field.</li>\r\n<li>At least three years&rsquo; experience in Microfinance or banking industry or other related field.</li>\r\n<li>Honesty, Initiative, creatively, high commitment and good inter-personal skill, and able to manage and lead team for success.</li>\r\n<li>Ability and effectively communicate in both Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li>Sound working knowledge of Computer (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, Flexcube, Email).</li>\r\n<li>Good commitment in fieldwork and strong willing to work with rural people.</li>\r\n<li>Good faith in Christianity.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Cambodian MFI/banking rules and regulations.</li>\r\n<li>Good Judgment and decision-making skill.</li>\r\n<li>Salary can be negotiable.</li>\r\n<li>NOTE: Internal staff who can apply such as RIA, RIT, OT, FT, COs who meet Breakeven Point (Zone01: 125 clients or 340,000$; Zone02:155 clients or 320,000$; Zone03: 160 clients or 270,000$; និង CB-CO: 400 clients or 180,000$), PAR30+&lt;1.5% (End of March 2019).</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,26,'1','04/19/2019',1,7,9,5,12,'English','2019-04-06 10:13:03','2020-05-29 05:32:41'),
	(762,19,'Operation Internal Auditor - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Perform on operational audits such; loan, saving, remittance, HR management, fixed asset/inventory management, administration, cash management and other controls.</li>\r\n<li>Check whether all KREDIT policies procedures and memos were officially approved by management or the Board of Director.</li>\r\n<li>Assist to develop audit procedure/program.</li>\r\n<li>Perform audit activity planning and audit executing with effective manner.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare/do draft audit report with prior verification from senior auditor before doing the exit meeting to branch/sub branch manager.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up/review the appropriateness of management&rsquo;s responses/feedback in the draft audit report then send to direct supervisor in timely manner.</li>\r\n<li>Do monthly activity audit report to direct supervisor in a timely manner.</li>\r\n<li>Comply with audit Code of Ethics.</li>\r\n<li>Learn and adapt well with policies and procedures, law and regulation, updated MEMO and every principle of KREDIT.</li>\r\n<li>Accountable for the duties and obligation to achieve the vision, mission and core values of KREDIT through God&rsquo;s will.</li>\r\n<li>Participate and keep the reputation, honorary and the cultural of KREDIT.</li>\r\n<li>Keep track and manage all hard and soft of audit documents.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other urgent tasks as necessary and required by supervisor/company.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>BBA field in Accounting or Banking and Finance or Auditing.</li>\r\n<li>Fresh graduate which having more knowledge in auditing, risk and internal control is encouraged to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in accounting, auditing and/or other related field in microfinance is more preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal skill, hardworking, teamwork.</li>\r\n<li>Proven analytical and problem solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good interviewing and presenting skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to write in clear and concise report in English and Khmer and communicate effectively.</li>\r\n<li>Dynamic and pleasant personality.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in the use of office software products (MS Word, Excel, Power Point, graphs, etc.) and in the compilation of statistical data.</li>\r\n<li>Strongly support the vision and mission of KREDIT.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to travel and stay in province at least 40%.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,10,'1','04/19/2019',1,5,3,5,9,'English','2019-04-06 10:18:55','2020-05-30 21:27:08'),
	(763,19,'Financial Internal Auditor - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Manage the own yearly plan with both quality and quantity as assigned.</li>\r\n<li>Manage timeframe for each the audit mission as agreed in order to achieve both quality and quantity.</li>\r\n<li>Do audit pre-plan before audit execution through data collection to follow the audit policy/procedure and guideline.</li>\r\n<li>Submit the pre-plan to senior auditor/audit unit manager for review and comment.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the audit executions are followed with the policy, procedure, and audit program in order to ensure all kinds of risk are covered and managed.</li>\r\n<li>Discuss and clarify the finding with auditee/stakeholders in order to find a clear root cause.</li>\r\n<li>Keep more concerns in each process to ensure that the internal control is in place and effective.</li>\r\n<li>Quick update to a supervisor if there is any suspicious case is discovered.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the audit documents are fully completed information and stored on the server after finish audit mission.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure constant capacity building and up to the date of KREDIT business performance.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks required by Senior/Manager/Head of IA.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Finance/Accounting, Economic, MBA, ACCA/CAT or related field.</li>\r\n<li>Experiences at least 1 years in audit field and especially MFI/Banking sector/financial management or others related.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of internal control, process and risk analysis.</li>\r\n<li>Good teamwork and audit ethic.</li>\r\n<li>Good computer skills (i.e. Microsoft Office) and a good understanding of CBS system or other specific MIS for MFIs are more advantageous.</li>\r\n<li>Good written and spoken English, communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>High motivation and ability to work without supervision.</li>\r\n<li>Good written and spoken English, Communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','04/11/2019',1,5,3,5,11,'English','2019-04-06 10:23:13','2020-06-01 10:25:13'),
	(764,19,'Recruitment Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist recruitment&amp; selection unit manager to implement the recruitment process on time and follow human resource policy.</li>\r\n<li>Arrange the interview and writing test schedule and receive application.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare recruitment forms such as interviewing questionnaires, insurant interview form, pre-interview form, announcement form&hellip;etc.</li>\r\n<li>Shortlist the candidate and prepare the list of them for writing test and interviewing and send it out.</li>\r\n<li>Inform to candidates who have been shortlisted and be an invigilator and interviewer in writing test and interviewing.</li>\r\n<li>Contact the recruitment committee for conducting interview and select final candidate.</li>\r\n<li>Check references and get more information by home visit and calling to make final decision for selection</li>\r\n<li>Make sure that all new candidates need to sign on insurance contract form which had been signed by their parents and knowledgeable by local authority before attending training and signing employment contract.</li>\r\n<li>Organize the other standard form to be used for recruiting employee.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare the strategy to support the recruitment process to complete the need.</li>\r\n<li>Contact with universities to propagate our job announcement.</li>\r\n<li>Interview the resigned employee (Exit Survey) from KREDIT through direct supervisor.</li>\r\n<li>Manage the recruitment documents, soft and hard copy such shortlist, shortage, resign, compensation contract, and final list.</li>\r\n<li>Other duties and obligation will be assigned by superior.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Business, HRM or other related certificate.</li>\r\n<li>One-year working experience in this position with company or NGO or MFI and bank.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Cambodian labor law.</li>\r\n<li>Good communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Proficient with Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.</li>\r\n<li>Good command in English, both oral and written.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to work in the provinces (for mission).</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','04/11/2019',1,7,3,5,11,'English','2019-04-06 10:26:13','2020-06-01 02:26:52'),
	(765,19,'Credit Portfolio Analysis Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Continuously seek for improvement of loan reporting standard if there is a need of new reports to be created and coordinate with IT or relevant department to prepare such report.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and translate the report to management with the suggestions and recommendation.</li>\r\n<li>Check the correctness of the new developed reports and properly implement it with information to all relevant departments.</li>\r\n<li>Verify the data in our FC and correct all errors occurred.</li>\r\n<li>Work, discuss, and handle with CBC to clients if there is a mismatch in data between CBC and our record.</li>\r\n<li>Verify the CBC fee in our system and the fee reports (invoices) and submit to Senior Credit Portfolio Analysis Officer.</li>\r\n<li>Be a KREDIT Representative to follow up branch issues to CBC (Credit Bureau Cambodia)</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Hit of CBC by uploading in Hit System and alert to Branch staff for the bigger loan.</li>\r\n<li>Train and provide CBC (Credit Bureau Cambodia) guideline to all branches and related staff.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and record the operations issues in the Help Desk System both KREDIT and CBC.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the correctness of all reports prepared for CMA, NBC, Lenders, Credit Committees, related departments, and stakeholder requirement.</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate with HR and IT on providing data for incentive calculation to field and office staff and submitting to Senior Credit Portfolio Analysis Officer/Deputy/Head of Micro Lending Department for checking.</li>\r\n<li>Keep all related data to be confidential and preventing to avoid leakage and make sure they are complied with policies, procedures, guidelines, and memos.</li>\r\n<li>Complete projects on a timely basis as assigned by management.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other various duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor of Business Administration in Management or Finance and Banking or IT or in any related field.</li>\r\n<li>Honesty, Initiative, creatively, high commitment and good inter-personal skill, and able to manage and lead team for success.</li>\r\n<li>Report Analytical about the excel skill.</li>\r\n<li>Able to use Computer program (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel (Advanced), Ms. Access, Internet, and E-mail).</li>\r\n<li>Good commitment in fieldwork and strong willing to work with rural people.</li>\r\n<li>Good faith in Christianity.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','04/11/2019',1,7,3,5,9,'English','2019-04-06 10:32:18','2020-05-30 03:50:28'),
	(766,19,'MSME Lending Evaluation Manager - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Assess and analyze the loan application submitted by branches and recommend by MSME Loan Evaluation Officer/Senior MSME Loan Evaluation Officer and has to ensure the enough data, information, and relevant documents/references.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze and comment to loan cases in liaison with loan policy and forward to concerned department/committee.</li>\r\n<li>Verify and clarify the loan before submitting to Department/ MSME Credit Committee.</li>\r\n<li>Verify accuracy of loan approval resolution before its delivery to branches.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate and conduct site visiting.</li>\r\n<li>Control the implementation of imposed conditions of approving loan.</li>\r\n<li>Present the loan to Department/MSME Credit committee.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare proper loan meeting agendas for designated credit committees.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare the approved loan resolutions and its deliveries to branches.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate and Conduct the site visit of collateral/ properties, businesses, and other information of the MSME loans.</li>\r\n<li>Act as a risk coordinator in identify credit risk for Micro Loan and MSME lending.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare MSME lending report including lending trend, market competition (price &amp;loan conditions), PAR &amp; solving progress, risk and risk mitigation.</li>\r\n<li>Onside coach and train to credit operator staff to help them to do loan assessment and able to complete loan forms.</li>\r\n<li>Collect and control errors of loan proposals submitted by branches.</li>\r\n<li>Review and implement target planning of Micro Lending Department and relevant departments effectively and in a responsible manner.</li>\r\n<li>Train to staffs related Micro/MSME Lending and ensure that all trained staffs will be able to perform their duties well.</li>\r\n<li>Set up and control as yearly, monthly, and daily plan of disbursement and collection to growth quality of loan portfolio.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up the subordinates&rsquo; performance, identify the training need, provide supporting to improve their performance, and participate the capacity building.</li>\r\n<li>Do refreshment to staffs on guideline, procedure, and improve weakness points timely or at least once within 06 months.</li>\r\n<li>Raise up all lending issues from branches/ subordinates and suggest the ways for improving to Deputy/Head of Micro Lending Department.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other various duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum age 25 years old.</li>\r\n<li>Bachelor of Business Administration in Management or Finance and Banking or in any related field.</li>\r\n<li>At least three years&rsquo; experience in Microfinance or banking industry or another related field.</li>\r\n<li>Honesty, Initiative, creatively, high commitment and good inter-personal skill, and able to manage and lead team for success.</li>\r\n<li>Ability and effectively communicate in both Khmer and English.</li>\r\n<li>Sound working knowledge of Computer (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, Flexcube, Internet, and Email).</li>\r\n<li>Good commitment in fieldwork and strong willing to work with rural people.</li>\r\n<li>Good faith in Christianity.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Cambodian MFI/ banking rules and regulations.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','04/11/2019',1,7,6,5,12,'English','2019-04-06 10:36:49','2020-05-31 17:18:08'),
	(767,19,'Customer Service Manager/Deputy Branch Manager - 03 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Be responsible for all aspects of the operational activities of the Bank branches to ensure that it is properly control and running smoothly.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure bank system running proper based on management&rsquo;s requirement.</li>\r\n<li>Respond for overall customer service and customer dispute resolution over frontline operations.</li>\r\n<li>Make sure all operational functions are in compliance with the relevant laws and regulations and adherence to the Delegation of Authority for counter transactions, General Ledger and P&amp;L matters.</li>\r\n<li>Assist Branch Manager in the development of human resources, financial performance and growth of the branch.</li>\r\n<li>All other matters ancillary to the above and to perform any other related duties will be required by superior from time to time.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Degree/Professional qualifications or equivalent.</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 2 years practical working experience in banking operations with hands-on experience in frontline operational procedures, customer handling, credit and lending processing, trade finance activities and accounting functions.</li>\r\n<li>Good organization skills to ensure effective and efficient implementation of business strategies.</li>\r\n<li>Good negotiation skills to maintain interpersonal customer relationships.</li>\r\n<li>High level of analytical ability to provide good solutions in customer problem solving.</li>\r\n<li>Attentive and devoted to deliver good quality works.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,57,15,17,'3','04/11/2019',1,7,6,5,2,'English','2019-04-06 10:40:45','2020-05-29 02:57:00'),
	(768,19,'Sale and Customer Service Officer - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Perform sale activities on savings and other financial products</li>\r\n<li>Establish personal contact of potential clients</li>\r\n<li>Collect feedback and complaint from clients related sale and customer service care and service providing then report to Deputy Head Sale &amp; Customer Service Department</li>\r\n<li>Analyze the market in order to identify new product growth opportunities</li>\r\n<li>Provide support, monitor the work performance of front line staff related to service providing and products selling, and identify points to be improved.</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with Customer Relationship Officer (CRO) to help boost the sales performance at each branch.</li>\r\n<li>Provide support to regional, branch, and sub branch and training to branch staff</li>\r\n<li>Resolve customer queries and issues related to sale and services</li>\r\n<li>Maintain sale reports and call follow up</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks will be assigned by supervisor</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor in Marketing or equivalent</li>\r\n<li>At least one year experience in sales, marketing, or microfinance/banking sectors</li>\r\n<li>Excellent oral and written English</li>\r\n<li>Good communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Interpersonal skills and professional appearance</li>\r\n<li>Telephone manner</li>\r\n<li>Capacities and flexibilities of sale and marketing</li>\r\n<li>Responsibility, logical thinking and results oriented in role</li>\r\n<li>Problem solving skill</li>\r\n<li>Honesty and neutrality in work</li>\r\n<li>Ability to travel to province branches</li>\r\n</ul>',1,57,15,17,'2','04/11/2019',1,5,3,5,11,'English','2019-04-06 10:43:58','2020-06-01 06:39:51'),
	(769,19,'Corporate Sales Executive - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Participate in developing policies, procedures, guidelines, sale strategies and setting sales plan and execute the strategies on non-credit services</li>\r\n<li>Select potential prospective such as business owners, NGOs, churches, companies and other partners for business activities</li>\r\n<li>Prepare slides to present to corporate clients and make direct sale, appointment with potential prospective to sell non-credit services/other products or services of KREDIT</li>\r\n<li>Provide direct support to the braches on corporate sales activities, present the services/products to potential prospective, &hellip;</li>\r\n<li>Maintain good relationship with existing and potential prospective</li>\r\n<li>Follow up market information, competitors&rsquo; product information then report to direct</li>\r\n<li>Prepare the corporate sale report and monitor the corporate sale performance across the country</li>\r\n<li>Work with branch staff, CSOs and CREs, to ensure the quality and timely preparation of corporate sales report and corporate sale performance</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate liaison corporate sales activity between branched and sales and customer service department.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure that all corporate sales activities are in accordance with policies and guidelines.</li>\r\n<li>Understand all risks in corporate selling process on all KREDIT service/product by reporting to related manager for finding the way to prevent and solving problem on time.</li>\r\n<li>Other Activities will be assigned by superior.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least bachelor degree in marketing, business management or similar disciplines equivalent and one year of corporate sale experience with banks, MFI or relevant fields</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency of English language (Third language: Mandarin or Thai is more advantage and priority)</li>\r\n<li>Have a skill of identifying, evaluating, presenting and selling to the target corporate client and ability to approach to the right person or high level officer of the target firm</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge on analyzing and convincing corporate target clients and on business concept/process/flow and value chain of corporate sector</li>\r\n<li>The sense of transforming the business activities to match with the financial products and provide the solution to the corporate client and capacity to enlarge the corporate reference to another firm and a professional and protocol behaviors to match with the corporate client</li>\r\n<li>High level of communication and negotiation skills with the corporate client</li>\r\n<li>Confidentiality of KREDIT branding in front of the corporate target</li>\r\n<li>Ability to communicate, present and influence credible and effectively at all levels of the organization including executive level</li>\r\n<li>Strong networking in the corporate sectors</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to all KRET&rsquo;s operation areas in provinces</li>\r\n<li>Both genders are encouraged.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'2','04/11/2019',1,8,3,5,1,'English','2019-04-06 10:47:59','2020-06-01 04:45:22'),
	(770,19,'Creative Designer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>With brand and communication unit manager based on the approval from authorized people on the printing projects, initiate and perform different designs for KREDIT as needed</li>\r\n<li>After doing work art, call different suppliers for quotations by giving them same specs.</li>\r\n<li>Do quality control before handing over to admin counter- part staff to distribute to related offices.</li>\r\n<li>Update the website as needed</li>\r\n<li>Check with the suppliers or producers about progress of project movement to make sure that the final products will be on time sent to the related offices.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in the development of branding and communication plan and budget.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in establishing and providing training as needed</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by Branding and Communication Unit Manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Any bachelor degrees in the field of design, IT, marketing and other related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years experiences in web and graphic design.</li>\r\n<li>Skillful in using design software such as Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Flash, Adobe In design, web-design (Microsoft Expression web, Joomla . .) - related program.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding written and spoken skills, both English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure, independently and highly self-motivated.</li>\r\n<li>Having good inter-personal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work creatively and be initiative.</li>\r\n<li>Able to travel throughout the country.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,53,15,17,'1','04/11/2019',1,5,7,5,2,'English','2019-04-06 10:51:45','2020-06-01 05:55:24'),
	(771,15,'មន្រ្តីរដ្ឋបាល (Administrative Officer) - ០៣នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងឯកសារបុគ្គលិក ឯកសារឥណទាន ឯកសារប្រាក់បញ្ញើសន្សំ​និង ឯកសារទ្រព្យតម្កល់ធានា។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រង និង រៀបចំការិយាល័យ កិច្ចប្រជុំ កំណត់ត្រា របាយការណ៍ប្រជុំ និង ពិធីការផ្សេងៗ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងការងារលទ្ធកម្ម និង ការគ្រប់គ្រងទ្រព្យ។</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងការងារសនិ្តសុខ សណ្តាប់ធ្នាប់ និង អនាម័យការិយាល័យ</li>\r\n<li>គ្រប់គ្រងការងារដឹកជញ្ជូន និង ធ្វើរបាយការណ៍</li>\r\n<li>បំពេញកិច្ចការងារផ្សេងៗ ទៀតដែលចាត់តាំងដោយថ្នាក់គ្រប់គ្រង។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>ជានិសិ្សតកំពុងសិក្សាឬបញ្ចប់ថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញាបត្រ&nbsp; ជំនាញគ្រប់គ្រង រដ្ឋបាលទូទៅ ឬសញ្ញាបត្រដែលមានតម្លៃស្មើ។</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍លើការងារ រដ្ឋបាល កាន់តែប្រសើរ។</li>\r\n<li>មានជំនាញក្នុងការគ្រប់គ្រង ដោះស្រាយបញ្ហា និងការ ប្រាស្រ័យ​​ទាក់ទងល្អ។</li>\r\n<li>មានសមត្ថភាព ផ្នែភាសាអង់គ្លេស ទាំងការនិយាយ និងសរសេរ។</li>\r\n<li>មានសមត្ថភាពផ្នែកកុំព្យូទ័រ លើកម្មវិធី Ms. Word, Ms. Excel,&nbsp; Internet និង Email ។</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,23,'3','04/26/2019',0,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-04-14 11:29:32','2020-05-30 18:39:43'),
	(772,15,'Manager, ISA for IT Operations - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Manage team for running EOD/EOM operation</li>\r\n<li>Manage team to monitor on Oracle database backup and restoration</li>\r\n<li>Control and manage the existing system on Core Banking System, ATM &amp; Mobile Banking System and Internal Application System and troubleshoot</li>\r\n<li>Administrate and manage resources of servers, storages and troubleshoot</li>\r\n<li>Administrate on securities of database system/operating system and perform regular securities monitoring&nbsp; to identify any possible intrusions</li>\r\n<li>Administrate and perform patching on the system (Database and Weblogic)</li>\r\n<li>Implement the Disaster Recovery, Data Continuity Plan and new system administration procedure</li>\r\n<li>Manage team to complete the tasks assigned by management and establish the activities plan</li>\r\n<li>Manage user access rights on Database system</li>\r\n<li>Ensure system is running 24/7 without interruption.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree of Computer Science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least three years experiences in Database Administration</li>\r\n<li>Working experience at MFI or Bank is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of Oracle Database, Oracle BI Report, Oracle SQL tuning and Oracle Database security</li>\r\n<li>Oracle Certified Associate (OCA) is preferable</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of SQL language and dot net is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Commitment and self-motivated</li>\r\n<li>Able to work at night for solving critical issue or other tasks assigned by management</li>\r\n<li>Good at oral and written communication skills both English and Khmer</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn new business application and new technology.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','04/30/2019',0,6,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-04-14 11:34:07','2020-05-31 01:09:36'),
	(773,15,'Manager, ISA for System Admin - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Administrate and manage resources of servers, storages and troubleshoot</li>\r\n<li>Administrate on securities of operating system and perform regular securities monitoring to identify any possible intrusions</li>\r\n<li>Administrate and perform patching on the system (OS, Server, and Storage)</li>\r\n<li>Utilize resources efficiency on Server and Storage for production, DR, and UAT environment and monitor performance</li>\r\n<li>Projection on resources allocation of Server and Storage</li>\r\n<li>Manage user access rights on System</li>\r\n<li>Implement the Disaster Recovery, Data Continuity Plan and new system administration procedure</li>\r\n<li>Manage team to complete the tasks assigned by management and establish the activities plan for System Administration Unit</li>\r\n<li>Assist deputy and director of IT to plan for hardware sizing and capacity planning</li>\r\n<li>Ensure system is running 24/7 without interruption.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree of Computer Science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least three year experiences as System Administrator especially on Oracle Hardware</li>\r\n<li>Working experience at MFI or Bank is a plus</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of Oracle Solaris, Oracle Linux, Oracle VM for x86 and SPARC</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of Oracle Server and Oracle Storage</li>\r\n<li>Commitment and self-motivated</li>\r\n<li>Able to work at night for solving critical issue or other tasks assigned by management</li>\r\n<li>Good at oral and written communication skills both English and Khmer</li>\r\n<li>Willing to learn new business application and new technology.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','04/30/2019',0,6,9,5,12,'Khmer, English','2019-04-18 09:50:40','2020-05-31 03:31:56'),
