	(819,31,'Financial Reporting Officer - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare reports for management such as monthly consolidated Balance Sheet,Income Statement, Financial&nbsp; Covenant, Management Ratio, BS&amp;IS by branch, and Internal Transfer Pricing).</li>\r\n<li>Prepare Consolidation and submitting reports (daily, weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly, quarterly, yearly) to NBC.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and submit monthly, quarterly, and yearly report to creditors.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in facilitating and consolidating budget.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare annual budget for NBC.</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate and consolidate business plan for NBC.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare regular ALCO meeting materials on financials.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare documents and assist in audit works with external auditors and prepare audit financial statements.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor banking/finance, accountingand related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Cambodian bankingrules and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Law of Taxation,Taxation on Profit in Cambodia, and Carry Certified Tax Agent is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent computer skills (include Excel Advance, Excel VBA, the accounting &amp; MIS software, Word, and PowerPoint)</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years experienced in financial management and reporting in the bank or micro-finance sector</li>\r\n<li>Personal management and development ability</li>\r\n<li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Good management and leadership skills</li>\r\n<li>Hard-working, fast learning, honest and high responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Be Patient and able to work under pressure</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',1,7,3,5,2,'English','2019-05-13 11:22:36','2020-05-31 01:02:18'),
	(820,31,'Tax Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure all tax reporting is declared on time&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Screening GL to calculate and verify withholding tax</li>\r\n<li>Verify all related tax transaction in order to comply with the taxation law.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare monthly and yearly tax declaration with supporting document to tax department.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate audits by various taxation authorities, External and Internal Audits.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare soft copy and hard copy of transactions related to tax for taxation authorities checking</li>\r\n<li>Prepare document for external audits.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for technical support for tax-related transactions:</li>\r\n<li>Properly and effectively provide support for tax-related transactions.</li>\r\n<li>Handle the issue and ensure availability to meet the need and comply with taxation law.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for providing and refresh training on taxation law</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and update materials for training related to taxation law.</li>\r\n<li>Provide training to new staff and refresh training to staff if require.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor banking/finance, accounting and related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Cambodian banking rules and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding of Law of Taxation,Taxation on Profit in Cambodia, and Carry Certified Tax Agent is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent computer skills (include Excel Advance, ExcelVBA, the accounting &amp; MIS software, Word, and PowerPoint)</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years experienced in tax from bank or micro-finance sector</li>\r\n<li>Personal management and development ability</li>\r\n<li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Good management and leadership skills</li>\r\n<li>Hard-working, fast learning, honest and high responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Be Patient and able to work under pressure</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',1,8,3,5,2,'English','2019-05-13 11:26:20','2020-05-31 17:59:48'),
	(821,15,'Director, Channel Banking Department - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Deployment, implementation and maintenance services: (a). Budget and schedule for supporting deployment of ATM station, POS terminal, Mobile Device. (b). Implementation and software configuration to adapt to changes of businesses. (c). Ensure proper maintenance and user inquires.</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring cash balance, ATM custodian and book reconciliation</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing monitoring ATM, POS, Mobile Banking both operations and risk identification function to minimize down-time and to identify suspicious cardholders / transactions including also on site inspection.</li>\r\n<li>Dealing with vendors for both hardware and software to ensure 24/7 of services</li>\r\n<li>Dealing with Central bank and other related regulatory authorities to maintain full compliance at all areas of the businesses and to ensure highly level of security for clients.</li>\r\n<li>Take ownership of the team performance, lead and develop staff under supervision to support long term growth ATM, POS &amp; Mobile Banking service.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in a systems administration and support environment</li>\r\n<li>Experience in supervising a team with sound problem solving skills, demonstrated project experience.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of various system architectures including hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in particular Customer database, ATM Switch systems, networking and other Electronic and Mobile banking technology.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with local payments systems and mobile payment.</li>\r\n<li>Good at oral and written communication skills both English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Working experience at MFI or Bank is a plus</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','05/24/2019',0,6,6,5,14,'English','2019-05-14 10:30:53','2020-05-27 21:26:33'),
	(822,15,'Officer, Credit Analysis - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare credit/loan proposals submitted by branches.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze financial statements and credit worthiness of borrowers.</li>\r\n<li>Identify borrowers&rsquo; business risks and propose corresponding mitigations.</li>\r\n<li>Interact with branch staff to solicit and verify borrower&rsquo;s information.</li>\r\n<li>Propose credit decisions and negotiate with branch staff accordingly.</li>\r\n<li>Liaise with Management Credit Committee in presenting loan proposal and responding to query/suggestion from the committee.</li>\r\n<li>File reports of turnaround time of loan process at Head Office.</li>\r\n<li>Performs Other tasks assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, or other equivalent qualification.</li>\r\n<li>At least 1 year working experience related to credit and/or financial analysis. Fresh graduate is also encouraged to apply.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical, decision-making, and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding and knowledge of microfinance and banking sector.</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal communication, team work, and result-oriented.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate, particularly in Word, Excel, Internet, and Email.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English is a plus advantage.</li>\r\n<li>High commitment with strong work ethics and integrity.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,17,'1','05/24/2019',0,6,3,5,11,'English','2019-05-14 10:33:24','2020-06-01 14:13:33'),
	(823,15,'Officer, Support Function Audit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Execute audit field work for business support functions exclude IT functions.</li>\r\n<li>Review and evaluate adequacy and effectiveness of internal control policies &amp; procedures and workflow process of company or business function.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare draft audit report during field work, and submit to Head Unit or team Leader.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare supporting and properly document.</li>\r\n<li>Assist Head Unit to provide feedback on risk control matrix,&nbsp; audit program guide and working papers.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other tasks assigned by direct supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in accounting or equivalent degree is required of accounting, Audit, or Finance qualification.</li>\r\n<li>Working experiences in related field.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of financial or business analysis, internal control system, organizational structure, works flow and operating procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of ethical commitments and trustworthiness.</li>\r\n<li>Good written and verbal English and writing skills.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate in MS Office (Word, MS Excel, Power Point, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Be available to travel in rural areas.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',0,4,3,5,11,'English','2019-05-14 10:54:38','2020-05-30 08:37:25'),
	(824,15,'Officer, Business Application Development - 02 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Manage and facilitate programmers to support end users or business team for new request.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain and Follow up to issues from log of application system.</li>\r\n<li>Design process flow and table structures and submit for approval before writing codes and interface.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure BI reports smoothly running and supporting to end users.</li>\r\n<li>Share common practices and experiences to subordinators for knowledge improvement.</li>\r\n<li>Supported&nbsp; and maintain business applications and system.</li>\r\n<li>Performance other taste assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree or engineer in Computer Science.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to apply technical standards, principles, theories and techniques for software development.</li>\r\n<li>Some experience programming and development of any application.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in programming languages such as VB.Net, ASP.NET, Java, PHP,&hellip;</li>\r\n<li>Basic Knowledge on MS SQL Server or Oracle Database</li>\r\n<li>Good written and spoken English</li>\r\n<li>Be able to work under pressure</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'2','05/31/2019',0,7,3,5,9,'English','2019-05-14 10:59:21','2020-05-29 23:35:21'),
	(825,15,'Manager, Mobile App Development - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Take lead in mobile app development project including Prototyping (UX/UI), designing, and developing mobile applications</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with related department and stakeholders to translate ideas, high level specifications into new or enhanced mobile application solutions</li>\r\n<li>Work with product owners across the businesses to understand market needs &amp; vision; quickly translate that vision into demonstrable applications</li>\r\n<li>Lead internal resources and provide guidance ensuring all development standards and practices are adhered to pursues continuous improvement in development processes, standards and quality ; to coach, mentor, and lead a diverse group of lean/agile software engineers</li>\r\n<li>Communicate effectively with immediate team and leadership, ensuring team receives consistent messages and has clear understanding of business direction, strategy, and results.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Proven work experience as a Mobile Developer with proven portfolio of released applications.</li>\r\n<li>In-depth knowledge of programming languages like Swift, Java, Flutter, React.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with third-party libraries and APIs.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with OOP design principles.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical skills with good problem-solving attitude.</li>\r\n<li>working experience with Microfinance or commercial bank is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Fluency in spoken and written English.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',0,6,9,5,12,'English','2019-05-14 11:03:30','2020-06-01 13:22:35'),
	(826,15,'Team Leader, Branch Audit for Deposit & Transfer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Leads deposit &amp; transfer auditor to executes the auditing of Remittance &amp; Fund Transfer, Saving Account, Fixed Deposit Account, AML/CFT &amp; FATCA, and ATM &amp; Mobile Banking activities.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares and reviews the audit planning and budgeting to conducts internal auditing activities.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares and Reviews pre-audit analysis checklist before conducting audit to finds suspicious transactions and audit posed engagement.</li>\r\n<li>Checks and observes the saving transactions process, Remittance &amp; Fund Transfer, Saving Account, Fixed Deposit Account, AML/CFT &amp; FATCA, and ATM &amp; Mobile Banking.</li>\r\n<li>Fill and review the audit working papers, summary finding sheet and its supporting documents as the evidence.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares and reviews a draft audit reports and supporting documents/ evidences.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in designing and developing/updating Remittance &amp; Fund Transfer, Saving Account, Fixed Deposit Account, AML/CFT &amp; FATCA, and ATM &amp; Mobile Banking and audit procedures and programs for branch auditors.</li>\r\n<li>Identify all significant emerging risk related to audit Deposit &amp;&nbsp; Remittance &amp; Fund Transfer Process.</li>\r\n<li>Performs other tasks assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in&nbsp; finance, banking, Business Management or Economics or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Work experience in different areas of the institution or bank at least 1 year related to Banks and Financial Institutions.</li>\r\n<li>A good understanding of the bank/financial institution&rsquo;s lending policies and procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent interpersonal and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Highly acquainted with computer systems and programs, such MS Word, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, Email &amp; Internet and core banking system is an advantage.</li>\r\n<li>Good in written and spoken English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Honest, reliable people and strong working under pressure.</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work in the field (around 80% to 90% in the field work) including weekends.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',0,7,3,5,11,'English','2019-05-14 11:06:17','2020-06-01 00:33:28'),
	(827,15,'Trainer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide training on core banking system and all HKL products, policies, and procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Provide orientation, foundation training and other refreshment training courses to related staff.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct other complementary training courses (accounting, small business, communication)</li>\r\n<li>Develop and improve training courses, training manuals, and training materials.</li>\r\n<li>Support operational staff to implement relevant products principles and core banking system.</li>\r\n<li>Prepared to ensure the quality of each training course.</li>\r\n<li>Support trainees, coaching, follow up, and accessing training need.</li>\r\n<li>And provide collaboration in administrative jobs for unit.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other task by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree banking finance or business management or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge and experience in MFI or bank is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>At least 1 year experience in audit training.</li>\r\n<li>Good moral communication, Honest and Creative.</li>\r\n<li>Good command English of writing, speaking and listening skill.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate in MS Word, MS Excel, PowerPoint, Internet and E-mail.</li>\r\n<li>Creative and Dynamic.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of conducting TNA is preferred.</li>\r\n<li>Be available to travel to rural areas.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',0,6,3,5,11,'English','2019-05-14 11:08:30','2020-05-30 06:07:35'),
	(828,15,'មន្រ្តីដោះស្រាយវិវាទ (Litigation Officer)​​ - ០១នាក់','<ul>\r\n<li>ទទួលបន្ទុកដោះស្រាយវិវាទទាំងឡាយដែលទាក់ទងនឹងផ្លូវច្បាប់របស់ ហត្ថាកសិករ លីមីតធីត នៅក្នុង និងក្រៅប្រព័ន្ធតុលាការ។</li>\r\n<li>ប្រឹក្សាយោបល់ផ្នែកច្បាប់ដល់បុគ្គលិក និងថ្នាក់គ្រប់គ្រង ហត្ថាកសិករ លីមីតធីត នៅ ពេលមានការស្នើសុំ។</li>\r\n<li>ពិនិត្យ និងតាមដាននូវរាល់វិវាទទាំងឡាយដែលមាននៅក្នុង និងក្រៅប្រព័ន្ធ តុលាការ ដែលពាក់ព័ន្ធជាមួយ ហត្ថាកសិករ លីមីតធីត និងរៀបចំរបាយការណ៍ ជូនថ្នាក់គ្រប់គ្រង។</li>\r\n<li>ទំនាក់ទំនង និងសម្របសម្រួលជាមួយស្ថាប័នតុលាការ មេធាវី អាជ្ញាធរ និងភាគី ពាក់ព័ន្ធដើម្បីដោះស្រាយវិវាទទាំងឡាយដែលកើតមាន។</li>\r\n<li>ស្រាវជ្រាវ ចងក្រង និងអភិវឌ្ឍកិច្ចការផ្នែកដោះស្រាយវិវាទ ជាពិសេសទាក់ទងនឹង វិស័យ ហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ និងធនាគារឱ្យទាន់សម័យ ដើម្បីទទួលបាននូវគំនិតថ្មីស្រប តាមតម្រូវការរបស់ ហត្ថាកសិករ លីមីតធីត។</li>\r\n<li>បំពេញកិច្ចផ្សេងៗតាមការចាត់តាំងរបស់ថ្នាក់គ្រប់គ្រង។</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>បញ្ចប់ ឬកំពុងសិក្សាថ្នាក់បរិញ្ញបត្រផ្នែកនីតិសាស្រ្ត ឬជំនាញ ប្រហាក់ប្រហែល។</li>\r\n<li>មានចំណេះដឹងផ្នែកក្រមរដ្ឋប្បវេណី ក្រមព្រហ្មទណ្ឌ ច្បាប់ ពាណិជ្ជកម្ម ច្បាប់ការងារ និងក្រមនីតិវិធី។</li>\r\n<li>មានបទពិសោធន៍ផ្នែកច្បាប់ក្នុងវិស័យធនាគារ និងហិរញ្ញវត្ថុ។</li>\r\n<li>មានចំណេះដឹង ឬមានបទពិសោធន៍ទាក់ទងនឹងការចរចា ការសម្រប សម្រួល និងការដោះស្រាយវិវាទតាមផ្លូវតុលាការ និងក្រៅប្រព័ន្ធ តុលាការ។</li>\r\n<li>និយាយ និងសរសេរភាសាអង់គ្លេសបានល្អ និងចេះប្រើប្រាស់។</li>\r\n<li>កុំព្យូទ័រ&nbsp; Word, Excel និង Power Point។</li>\r\n<li>ជំនាញក្នុងការប្រាស្រ័យទាក់ទងល្អ និងអាចចុះខេត្តបាន។</li>\r\n</ul>',1,68,15,17,'1','05/31/2019',0,7,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-05-14 11:11:00','2020-06-01 08:17:28'),
