	(862,34,'Branch Operations Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare journal entries.</li>\r\n<li>Assist monthly closings and preparation of monthly financial statements.</li>\r\n<li>Assist with implementing and maintaining internal financial controls and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring Inter-branch balance.</li>\r\n<li>Control inventory and fix asset.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare water snake and other supplies for meeting.</li>\r\n<li>Manages expenditure of petty cash by following principles and procedures of CP Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Manage contract of Relationship Officer&rsquo;s Motor.</li>\r\n<li>Record (Kongtor) of relationship Officer&lsquo;s motor and make cash payment for them.</li>\r\n<li>Control for cleaner security and driver.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Accounting or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>Other relevant training and certification</li>\r\n<li>Previous experience of general accounting or in banking sector is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical skills with attention to details</li>\r\n<li>Excellent computer skills</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of accounting principles and practices</li>\r\n<li>Stress tolerance.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Computer &ndash; MS. Office</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Location:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sampov Lun District</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,4,'1','06/30/2019',1,7,3,5,8,'English','2019-06-09 09:49:13','2020-06-01 15:52:29'),
	(863,34,'Internal Auditor - 01 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Assist Senior Internal Audit in preparing the internal audit reports,</li>\r\n<li>Performs financial, operational, credit, IT, departments audit and other audits in order to provide assurance to risk department,</li>\r\n<li>Update audit check lists,</li>\r\n<li>Analyze the weakness of operation and management processes, and provide the evident supports for recommendations in reports,</li>\r\n<li>Develop audit programs and testing procedure relevant to risk and test the objectives,</li>\r\n<li>Obtain and review evidences ensuring audit conclusion are well-documented,</li>\r\n<li>Documents the findings/issues, drafts the recommendations using unbiased opinion to submit to Senior Internal Audit for reviewing,</li>\r\n<li>Builds and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staffs of areas under review,</li>\r\n<li>Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors,</li>\r\n<li>Performs related works as assigned by Senior Internal Audit.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in auditing or related fields,</li>\r\n<li>Good English proficiency, both written and spoken,</li>\r\n<li>One year&rsquo;s experience in related field,</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy (MS, Office, Ms, Excel, Power Point, e-mail etc.),</li>\r\n<li>Plans and organizes workload properly with infrequent exception</li>\r\n<li>Makes good decision; timing and presentation of the decisions are acceptable</li>\r\n<li>Work consistently accurate, complete, and precise; rarely makes errors and/or omissions</li>\r\n<li>Responds to criticism in a constructive fashion; exhibits more initiatives than most in taking steps to correct problem areas as identified</li>\r\n<li>Building relationships &amp; networks</li>\r\n<li>Willing to travel to support business operations at provinces.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,6,3,5,8,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 09:52:18','2020-05-29 23:39:21'),
	(864,34,'MIS Support Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare all daily portfolio report</li>\r\n<li>Prepare all monthly portfolio reports (performance report, average DPD, collections efficiency, late/paid off penalties, report by due days, SMS sending and so on.)</li>\r\n<li>Prepare loan portfolio of credit officer for HR on credit officer salary appraisal</li>\r\n<li>Prepare NBC report</li>\r\n<li>Other requirements from Risk Analytics Manager</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>A university degree in Finance and Banking and related field</li>\r\n<li>Minimum of 1 year of experiences in Financial Institution</li>\r\n<li>Excellence in Ms. Excel spread sheet and SQL language.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>English communication (both verbal and writing) is preferred.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,6,7,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 09:54:38','2020-06-01 01:54:47'),
	(865,34,'Branch Teller - 20 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>Make warm welcome to all customers and good communication with them</li>\r\n<li>Deliver to customers with effective and efficient banking products and services</li>\r\n<li>Ensure proper data entries and transactions of products and services provided to customers</li>\r\n<li>Cash handling</li>\r\n<li>Prepare routine records and reports required by supervisor and/or manager</li>\r\n<li>Do report to Head of Branch Teller and follow by introduction and manual of teller work flow.</li>\r\n<li>Directly meet and process with customers.</li>\r\n<li>Count and verify money clearly before cash in-out with document. Teller has to work closely with cash and customers.</li>\r\n<li>When doing cash flow in-out process, we must check denomination note clearly and avoid transferring or receiving counterfeit note.</li>\r\n<li>Entry data in system correctly.</li>\r\n<li>Must perform other duties as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Accounting or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>Broad understanding how bank operates</li>\r\n<li>Experience with cash holding, CBS system</li>\r\n<li>Good in English communication (both verbal and writing)</li>\r\n<li>Pleasant and friendly personality</li>\r\n<li>Honesty</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work under pressure and over time</li>\r\n<li>Problem Solving</li>\r\n<li>Flexibility &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n<li>Resilience</li>\r\n<li>Understands all bank services</li>\r\n<li>Past relevant working experience will be an advantage, but fresh from university are also welcome</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Location:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Phnom Penh</li>\r\n<li>Sa Ang</li>\r\n<li>Preah Sihanouk</li>\r\n<li>Other provinces</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,10,'20','06/30/2019',1,10,3,5,8,'English','2019-06-09 09:58:53','2020-06-01 16:44:40'),
	(866,34,'Project & Property Management Team Leader - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Set-up project for new branches, renovation and office relocation</li>\r\n<li>Overseeing projects in progress and directing facilities staff</li>\r\n<li>Call for the meeting and chase-up with stakeholders to ensure project time line is met</li>\r\n<li>Administers of both Projects activities within agreed budget</li>\r\n<li>Provide superior property support and co-ordinate recovery activities in event of any property related incident as subject matter experts to key business stakeholders</li>\r\n<li>Control and monitor (periodic physical count and check) on fixed assets status to ensure it&rsquo;s workable or properly used, including property maintenance</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with the branches or immediately contact to the vendors such as mechanic, mason, carpenter, blacksmith, constructor, craftsman, etc. to fix the problem occurrence as soon as possible.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure all assets are properly stick assets code</li>\r\n<li>Responsible to fulfill the compliance, policies especially contract management, supplier management and all guidelines. Where deviations are detected, take appropriate action to rectify and prevent re occurrence</li>\r\n<li>Contracts with tenants by negotiating leases/rental and negotiating terms and conditions of contacts with outside contractors for subsequent approval</li>\r\n<li>Provides all trainings to head of branches operation, branch operation officers and new recruitment.</li>\r\n<li>Do other tasks which is assigned by supervisor/manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Understand about vision, mission, regulations, and other ethical, principles of Cambodia Post Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Hold Bachelor degree of Finance and Banking, Engineering, or Business Administration and other designing skill</li>\r\n<li>Good background in engineering or property management</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years&rsquo; experiences relate to the skill</li>\r\n<li>High proficiency in English knowledge.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of Ms. Office Word, Excel, PowerPoint and other civil construction design programs</li>\r\n<li>Self-Driven, good communication, reporting, decision making, solving problem and interpersonal.</li>\r\n<li>High commitment, confidence and able to travel.</li>\r\n<li>Competencies: Focuses on the Customer, Broadens Perspective, Results Oriented, and strong Exercises Sound Judgment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,85,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,4,9,5,12,'English','2019-06-09 10:04:50','2020-05-29 03:33:46'),
	(867,34,'Head of Admin Unit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Work with finance department to ensure payments on time for the organization</li>\r\n<li>Arrange the banking vehicles for supporting daily operations</li>\r\n<li>Work with branches and departments for facilitate the document of request pass to procurement team to proceed buying materials or fixed assets.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate activities among the team</li>\r\n<li>Provide feedback to higher level managements</li>\r\n<li>Manage on stock and stationeries for HQ and help the branch to solve the issue relate to stock and stationeries</li>\r\n<li>Manage all fixed assets of all branches of Cambodia Post Bank Plc and help the branch to solve the issue relate to fixed assets and report to admin and procurement manager on timeline basis</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for tracking all rental buildings of CP Bank and make payment on time.</li>\r\n<li>Assist admin and procurement manager for all operation expenses requests from H.Q staffs and branches and submit to authorized level for approval.</li>\r\n<li>Oversee HQ and all branches image such as room, toilets, and others</li>\r\n<li>Manage on the security team and office cleaning</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for delivery all the message, announcement, policy, and procedure from H.Q to all branches on time</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for preparing for meeting of H.Q such as room, foods, snack, and attendant on time</li>\r\n<li>Provides all trainings to head of branches operation/branch operation officers for new recruitments and continue trainings for all bank policy</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for delivery all the email/mail that received from/to branches and managements</li>\r\n<li>Assist admin and procurement manager for all requested from the branches of CPBank Plc</li>\r\n<li>Do other tasks which is assigned by supervisor/manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Understand about vision, mission, regulations, and other principles of Cambodia Post Bank.</li>\r\n<li>Hold Bachelor degree of Finance and Banking, Accounting, or Business Administration.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years experiences in Admin affairs.</li>\r\n<li>High proficiency in English knowledge.</li>\r\n<li>Skills in managing, communicating, reporting, decision making, solving problem, and interpersonal skill.</li>\r\n<li>High commit to work.</li>\r\n<li>High confident and talent to work.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,6,9,5,2,'English','2019-06-09 10:08:08','2020-05-29 20:54:13'),
	(868,34,'Head of Internal Audit Unit (IT) - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Identifies and evaluates risk areas and provides key input to the development of the annual audit plan.</li>\r\n<li>Assists Head of Internal audit in preparing the annual audit plan</li>\r\n<li>Plan, perform and follow-up on assigned projects in line with the annual internal audit plan, particularly compliance and information technology audits, focusing on primary business risks.</li>\r\n<li>Oversees a staff of IT auditors responsible for auditing information systems, platforms, and operating procedures in accordance with established corporate standards for efficiency, accuracy and security.</li>\r\n<li>Develop risk-based audit programs to assess and test controls in accordance with the audit objectives, especially in topics of Logical Access, Network Infrastructure, Database Security, Cloud Computing, General Information Security, SDLC, Architecture, Project/Program Management, IT Operations, and Change Management.</li>\r\n<li>Provides trainings, coaching and guidance to internal audit team leader, senior internal audit and internal auditors in conducting audit and other related issues.</li>\r\n<li>Prepares, participates in team and leads the group audit.</li>\r\n<li>Drafts and delivers the audit report to Internal Audit Manager &amp; Head of Internal Audit Department for review undertaking the agreed timeframe.</li>\r\n<li>Communicates and/or assists in communicating the results of audit via written reports and oral presentations to managements and ensures management response and action to audit findings and recommendations as agreed timeframe.</li>\r\n<li>Reviews audit programs, audit check list, working paper and other related documents in order to fit with the situations,</li>\r\n<li>Assists Internal Audit Manager &amp; Head of Internal Audit Department in evaluating senior auditors and internal auditors&rsquo; performance.</li>\r\n<li>Build and maintain respectful and effective communication and relationship with teams, managements and staffs of areas under review.</li>\r\n<li>Maintains confidentiality of bank and customer affairs in accordance with standards of professional conduct of auditors.</li>\r\n<li>Performs related works as assigned by Internal Audit Manager &amp; Head of Internal Audit Department.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in accounting, finance, technology or the equivalent combination of Education, training, and work experience.</li>\r\n<li>A minimum of at least 2 years audit experience is required as well as one or more relevant professional certifications (i.e. CPA, CIA, CISA, CFE) is preferred</li>\r\n<li>English proficiency: Fluently both speaking and writing</li>\r\n<li>Leadership skills, work and outcome orientation</li>\r\n<li>Polite, friendly, reflective, communicative, reliable, honest and single-minded</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Other Information This position is demanded and outcome sharpening which confront a lot more challenges with the auditees and business partners; therefore, it needs to sacrifice times and endeavor in order to achieve this position, as in the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ability to give and follow instructions accurately and efficiently; proactive in asking clarifying questions to ensure work effort is directed wholly toward desired outcome</li>\r\n<li>Ability to apply audit standards through practical application</li>\r\n<li>Ability to observe and understand business processes ensuring processes are documented completely and accurately</li>\r\n<li>Solid listening skills and ability to identify gaps in logic &ndash; inquisitive</li>\r\n<li>Strong organization and follow up skills including the ability to handle competing priorities and meet all deadlines and commitments</li>\r\n<li>Possess an appropriate combination of technical expertise in fields such as auditing, finance, technology, operations, or investigations</li>\r\n<li>Ability to flourish in a fast-paced, complex environment and willing to adapt to change</li>\r\n<li>Ability to recognize when learned theoretical concepts should be applied</li>\r\n<li>Ability to identify underlying cause of an issue raised.</li>\r\n<li>Good communication skills along with good or developing negotiation skills</li>\r\n<li>Ability to identify sensitive issues and facilitate communications in a proactive manner to avoid surprises</li>\r\n<li>Willingness and ability to adapt to new circumstances, information, and challenges</li>\r\n<li>Executes effective and thorough application of all internal audit standards within assigned responsibility</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate a positive, can-do attitude</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,4,9,5,2,'English','2019-06-09 10:14:03','2020-05-29 03:09:37'),
	(869,34,'Senior Operations Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare journal voucher for business transaction</li>\r\n<li>Check payment request &amp; advance request from branches &amp; HQ</li>\r\n<li>Key transaction into T24 system</li>\r\n<li>Support and follow up branch related to loan reschedule, pre-close and any update with system for loan, scan and email to feedback to all branches.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up branches monthly collateral outstanding report</li>\r\n<li>Collect monthly collateral report from branches</li>\r\n<li>Prepare journal entries for business transaction</li>\r\n<li>Journal entries for fund transfer</li>\r\n<li>Scan and Send approved request to branches</li>\r\n<li>Copy daily and monthly documents</li>\r\n<li>Entries for daily and monthly closing</li>\r\n<li>Daily and monthly report for management</li>\r\n<li>Cooperate with IT department to solve all issues from branches.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks will be directed by operation unit manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in accounting &amp; Finance Banking or related skill</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years&rsquo; experience in Bank</li>\r\n<li>Strong facilitate skill.</li>\r\n<li>Good English and Communication skills (Writing and Verbal).</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of computer such as Ms Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Internet.</li>\r\n<li>Self-starter and self-motivator</li>\r\n<li>Problem identification, initiative and adaptability</li>\r\n<li>High responsibly and strong commitment.</li>\r\n<li>Be honesty and patient</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,6,8,5,2,'English','2019-06-09 10:18:26','2020-06-01 10:17:14'),
	(870,34,'Senior Procurement Officer - 01 post','<p>1. Treasury Management:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Manage the bank&rsquo;s asset and liabilities in line with the Strategic Plan.</li>\r\n<li>Review and manage the balance sheet in terms of size, composition, and liquidity and exposure level to off-balance sheet items ensuring currencies risks are well managed.</li>\r\n<li>Manage daily money market and Foreign Exchange (FX) dealing.</li>\r\n<li>Analyse FX market and develop FX pricing of products.</li>\r\n<li>Identify and manage the market risk embedded in retail products.</li>\r\n<li>Build and maintain banking relationships with local and foreign bankers and FX business partners in coordination with Operations and Sales Teams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>2. Asset Liability Committee (ALCO):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set up ALCO term of reference and frameworks</li>\r\n<li>Be an active member of ALCO</li>\r\n<li>Develop report pack and present to ALCO</li>\r\n<li>Take action and respond to ALCO&rsquo;s recommendations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>3. Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop FTP policy and procedures to ensure efficient internal price transfer within business and treasury to optimize funding productivity and help track department P/L effectively to drive growth.</li>\r\n<li>Measure the cost of capital in the formulation of the FTP curve for use by the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Take into account for the bank&rsquo;s asset and liability book over different tenors and recognize the issue of interest rate risk in bank&rsquo;s current portfolio.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>4. Investment Management:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop the investment policy and procedures</li>\r\n<li>Invest the surplus funds and capital to enhance yield to achieve a risk/reward ratio acceptable to the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Control the Bank&rsquo;s counter party, position limits and any excesses.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor balances of Bank&rsquo;s Nostro accounts and optimize the Bank&rsquo;s free capital</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>5. Provide support to ad hoc projects/transactions and other tasks as may be assigned CFO and Senior Management Team.</p>','<ul>\r\n<li>At least Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Finance, Accounting or Business Administration.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical, communication and inter-personal skills;</li>\r\n<li>Proven ability to work under pressure and deliver outputs in a timely manner;</li>\r\n<li>Consistently approaches work with energy and a positive, constructive attitude;</li>\r\n<li>Minimum 7 years of experience in bank/MFI; of which 3 to 5 years experiences in treasury, ALCO, FTP and investment function.</li>\r\n<li>A sound knowledge and solid experience of treasury function and reporting techniques in banks/MFI.</li>\r\n<li>Understand Cambodian legal framework including money and capital market in Cambodia</li>\r\n<li>Sound, strong numeric and analytical skills.</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication and negotiating skills combined with the ability to deal with all seniority levels within the line of business. Strong computer literacy such as Microsoft Offices (Ms. Word, Ms. Excel, etc.), Core Banking System, Internet, E-mail, etc;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrated experience in selecting, managing, and developing a team, and the ability to lead by example;</li>\r\n<li>Self-motivated, self-starter, demonstrated initiative and a strong desire to improve processes;</li>\r\n<li>Fluent in English with good written and oral communication skills;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrates integrity and ethical standards;</li>\r\n<li>Promotes the vision, mission, and strategic goals of CP Bank.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,66,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,4,8,5,7,'English','2019-06-09 10:25:53','2020-06-01 06:53:04'),
	(871,34,'Operationals Risk Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Check compliance of Risk Policies: Make sure CPB is following exactly what policies written and propose and changes to update policies in conformity with new conditions or new market practices.</li>\r\n<li>Report discrepancies and mistakes: Report to board of management any significant discrepancies or deficiency in policies and in implementing policies amongst departments.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor Operational Risk activities: Coordinate with Operational Risk team to follow activities in ORM framework including RCSA programs, finding out root causes of incidents in Operational Risk reports, review and updating KRIs from operational functions in the bank.</li>\r\n<li>Working with Branch Managers: Coordinate with branch managers under operational risk program in terms of collecting loss incidents, holding RCSA workshops.</li>\r\n<li>Consolidate and maintain ORMU&rsquo;s data: Coordinate with team works and the Risk Owners to collect RCSA &amp; KRI Report then input onto System and keep update as per required by line manager.</li>\r\n<li>Working with HR, Heads of Departments to collect KRIs.</li>\r\n<li>Others: to be assigned by line manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Be able to travel to Provinces</li>\r\n<li>Willing to work as TEAMWORK</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','06/30/2019',1,4,3,5,1,'English','2019-06-09 10:28:47','2020-05-31 10:17:30'),
	(872,34,'Credit Officer - 200 posts','<ul>\r\n<li>To promote and sell the company&rsquo;s products and services.</li>\r\n<li>To process all new applications within the stipulated turnaround time.</li>\r\n<li>To build a good relationship with all levels of local authorities to get their support on loan documents processing.</li>\r\n<li>To fill in all new loan/existing loan applications with clients, and following up clients&rsquo; repayment on time.</li>\r\n<li>To manage and maintaining clients&rsquo; relationship with clients, to gain more loyalty from clients through high quality services.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum third year or graduated in Banking &amp; Finance, Management, Marketing or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Good experience in sales (Experience in Credit/ Saving is preferable)</li>\r\n<li>Commit to the core value of the company.</li>\r\n<li>Good analytical, attention to details, communication, time management, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Abilities to decision-making and problem-solving</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English both speaking and writing.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,71,15,28,'200','06/30/2019',1,6,3,5,1,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 10:32:40','2020-05-31 21:11:33'),
	(873,15,'Credit Analyst Officer for Unsecured Loans Product - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Conduct site visit of borrower&rsquo;s resident, business premise and/or working place to collect information to verify and support loans proposal.</li>\r\n<li>Assess and Analyze financial statements and credit worthiness of borrowers.</li>\r\n<li>Identify borrowers&rsquo; business risks and propose corresponding mitigations.</li>\r\n<li>Propose credit decisions and negotiate with PC officer accordingly.</li>\r\n<li>Liaise with Management Credit Committee in presenting loans proposal and responding to query/suggestion from the committee.</li>\r\n<li>File reports of turnaround time of loans process at Head Office.</li>\r\n<li>Other tasks assigned by supervisor.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in banking/finance, business, economics, or other equivalent qualification.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 year working experience related to credit and/or financial analysis.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical, decision-making, and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good understanding and knowledge of microfinance and banking sector.</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal communication, team work, and result-oriented.</li>\r\n<li>Sound computer literacy, particularly in Word, Excel, Internet, and Email.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in English is a plus advantage.</li>\r\n<li>High commitment with strong work ethics and integrity.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,3,3,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:06:06','2020-06-01 07:18:49'),
	(874,15,'Manager, Support Function Audit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Review risk control matrix and audit program guide.</li>\r\n<li>Link pre-audit checklist to risk control matrix.</li>\r\n<li>Lead team to conduct pre-audit &amp; audit field work on the business support function exclude IT functions.</li>\r\n<li>Review and finalize the draft report, and submit to DHAD.</li>\r\n<li>Lead to perform audit post engagement.</li>\r\n<li>Follow up audit finding reports of audited departments exclude IT audit report.</li>\r\n<li>Lead team to perform surprise cash count and prepare cash count report.</li>\r\n<li>Provide training to subordinates and other IA staff if required</li>\r\n<li>Review staff performance appraisal.</li>\r\n<li>Assist direct supervisor to perform other tasks.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor or Master degree in Accounting or quivalent qualifications.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years working experiences in related field.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of financial/business analysis, internal control system, organizational structure, works flow and operating procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Strong interpersonal, communication and management skills.</li>\r\n<li>Advance written and verbal communication skills.</li>\r\n<li>Advanced analytical, organization, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate in MS Office (Word, Excel, Power Point, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work independently.</li>\r\n<li>Be available to travel in rural areas.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,4,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:08:45','2020-05-30 12:56:23'),
	(875,15,'Head Unit, Support Function Audit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Perform pre-audit and audit field work for business support functions exclude IT functions.</li>\r\n<li>Review and evaluate adequacy and effectiveness of&nbsp; internal control&nbsp; policies &amp; procedures and workflow process of company/business function.</li>\r\n<li>Provide feedback on risk control matrix, audit program guide and working papers.</li>\r\n<li>Support to subordinates in performing the audit tasks.</li>\r\n<li>Prepare and review the draft audit report of subordinates during field work.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in audit post engagement with Skill manager.</li>\r\n<li>Review staff performance appraisal.</li>\r\n<li>Assist DHAD &amp; Skill manager in performing other tasks.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Accounting, Finance or equivalent qualifications.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 years working experiences in related field.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in financial or business analysis, internal control system, organizational structure, works flow and operating procedures.</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of ethical commitments and trustworthiness.</li>\r\n<li>Advance written and verbal skills with excellent English.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate in MS Office (Word, MS Excel, Power Point, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Be available to travel in rural areas.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,3,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:11:06','2020-05-27 17:20:58'),
	(876,15,'Head Unit, Liquidity Management - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Consolidate daily liquidity sent to management.</li>\r\n<li>Daily Monitor Branch liquidity.</li>\r\n<li>Daily Monitor internal fund transfer.</li>\r\n<li>Cheque clearing and settlement.</li>\r\n<li>Update tool and Guideline.</li>\r\n<li>Perform job tasks assigned by director of treasury.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Banking and Finance, Accounting, or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>Experience in banking and micro finance sector.</li>\r\n<li>Solid knowledge in Account and Finance skills.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literate in MS Office (Word, MS Excel, Power Point, etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>',1,28,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,6,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:13:34','2020-06-01 08:11:38'),
	(877,15,'Team Leader, Operational Risk - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Conduct risk assessment on business initiative/service/policy procedure and product development.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain recording mechanism of operational risk register, risk incident report register, operational loss event database and fraud control plan register.</li>\r\n<li>Assist risk owners to create strategies recommendation and solution to response the operational risk incidents.</li>\r\n<li>Design a business continuity planning and crisis management plan for managing the unexpected risk event.</li>\r\n<li>Assist Department Director to produce report dashboard and other requirement.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Management, Banking and Finance, Economics, or other related field. English degree is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>At least 2 year experience on operational risks and fraud risk management, Audit and Compliance.</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience in areas of risk management, compliance or related field.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of control issues</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Sound understanding of financial/banking business operation.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,4,9,5,2,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:15:40','2020-05-31 18:07:18'),
	(878,15,'Officer, Branch Communication - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Provide timely, smooth and effective communication and collaboration with branch staff and cross-functional stakeholders to contribute to achieving department&rsquo;s goals and objectives.</li>\r\n<li>Actively contribute to developing and improving effective communication channels to support loan growth with quality.</li>\r\n<li>Gather and consolidate information from branches in relation to operational challenges, policy/procedure implementation in the market, complaints, competition status, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Communicate loan portfolio performance or any common findings or errors in relation to credit information collections.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure appropriate records, files and documentations are well maintained.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Banking &amp; Finance, Business Management or Economic or equivalent degree.</li>\r\n<li>At least 1 year working experiences involved credit management or data management.</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate high level of ethical behavior and trustworthiness.</li>\r\n<li>Good written and verbal communication skills in English speaking.</li>\r\n<li>Be honest, friendly, active ,and creative.</li>\r\n<li>Computer literacy in MS. Word, Excel, Internet and E-mail.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to work under pressure and highly self-motivated.</li>\r\n<li>High level of commitment.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','06/22/2019',0,5,3,5,11,'Khmer, English','2019-06-09 12:18:03','2020-05-28 03:29:47');
