5:59','2020-05-29 00:20:44'),
	(971,31,'Digital Product Champion Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Be responsible for branch support, product training, marketing support, sale and strategy</li>\r\n<li>Support to develop and grow of the bank&rsquo;s digital products</li>\r\n<li>Increase penetration rates of digital customers (Card, Internet and Mobile Banking) as well as</li>\r\n<li>channel usage and activities</li>\r\n<li>Conceptualize and run campaigns and promotion driven by portfolio analysis</li>\r\n<li>Assist to create and maintain digital banking penetration, brand awareness, unique positioning in</li>\r\n<li>the market, with the aim of building transaction volumes and gaining enhanced transactions</li>\r\n<li>account balances</li>\r\n<li>Collect customer feedback and issues relating to these channels</li>\r\n<li>Be a Subject Matter Expert and Go to person for branches in the area of digital products (Card,</li>\r\n<li>Internet and Mobile Banking)</li>\r\n<li>Develop the necessary material and provide training/refreshment to branches and other related</li>\r\n<li>departments on existing/new digital products</li>\r\n<li>Other duties as assigned.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree Finance and Banking and relate field</li>\r\n<li>Ability read and understand purchase processing</li>\r\n<li>Working knowledge of digital banking product, sale and marketing</li>\r\n<li>Ability to multi-task and support daily BANK needs</li>\r\n<li>1 years up of experience in purchasing and procurement</li>\r\n<li>Proficient computer skills, including Microsoft Suite (Word, Power point, outlook, and Excel)</li>\r\n<li>Good communication skills</li>\r\n<li>Networking skills</li>\r\n<li>Problem-solving</li>\r\n</ul>',1,41,15,17,'1','07/30/2019',1,8,3,5,11,'English','2019-07-14 10:39:38','2020-05-31 00:34:36'),
	(972,31,'Senior IT Data Center Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Participate in key strategic planning processes and project to ensure plans meet business aims.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for the quality of IT services provided to end users on a day-to-day basis.</li>\r\n<li>Closely monitor the system error log and enhancement log to ensure no long outstanding issue left unattended/unresolved.</li>\r\n<li>Daily monitor of server health and performance, server space, backup jobs and respond to support issue.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure Data Center is always secured and protected from any illegal both physical and logical access.</li>\r\n<li>Manage projects to upgrade, replace or alter systems in response to actual or anticipated demand from the business using IT project management delivery mythologies.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure all IT incidents reported are recorded properly on the IT incident / Problem log report.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to prioritize, manage, and track open cases at all relevant stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure availability of systems and infrastructure by pro-active monitoring, maintenance and management of system</li>\r\n<li>Supervise, monitor and follow up on all tickets assigned to vendor IT Data Center support team</li>\r\n<li>Ensure cleanliness, tidiness, and environment control of Data Center and Disaster Recovery Site</li>\r\n<li>Perform others task as assigned by manager.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor or Master Degree in computer science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>3 to 5 years of experienced in management information systems with at least 3 years of experience in financial settings.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of the IT infrastructure in banking industry is preferred.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent technical diagnostic and analytical skills and a consultative and collaborative approach to problem solving.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to lead team of direct and in-indirect reports to deliver projects and system upgrades.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in managing Microsoft, Linux SUN Solaris and AIX platforms.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of the underlying operation banking system.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical and English communications skills (verbal/written).</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','07/30/2019',1,7,8,5,5,'English','2019-07-14 10:48:45','2020-05-29 19:45:15'),
	(973,31,'Senior AML/CFT Compliance Officer - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Verify and ensure the completeness of AML/CFT Questionnaire to/from other financial institution as well as preparing the requirement along with the questionnaire.</li>\r\n<li>Lead in preparing the Cash Transaction Report (CTR), Suspicious Transaction Report (STR) and Data Collection on ML/FT report to regulator on the effective and timely manner.</li>\r\n<li>Assist line manager in designing and developing training program and material on regulations related to Financial Institution and AML/CFT.</li>\r\n<li>Provide induction/refreshment training to new/existing staff at all level on compliance related topics including but not limited to the AML/CFT Awareness and KYC/CDD.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor transaction of high risk customer including but not limited to transaction of PEPs and Top Depositor.</li>\r\n<li>Assist line manager in monitoring/maintaining/upgrading the AML/CFT System.</li>\r\n<li>Support all frontline staff in any inquiry regarding KYC and AML/CFT System.</li>\r\n<li>Report to line manager about the issues or difficulties on how to manage/control regarding AML/CFT.</li>\r\n<li>Perform other task assigned based on the requirement of the actual situation.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree in Law, Accounting, Finance and Banking, Business Laws and related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least 3 years experienced in Legal, Compliance and audit within Banking Industry and related association sectors.</li>\r\n<li>Good at interpersonal, communication, critical thinking, and complex problem solving skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of reporting procedure and record keeping.</li>\r\n<li>Good in analysis skills.</li>\r\n<li>Good at both Microsoft Office and English user.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,78,15,17,'1','07/30/2019',1,8,3,5,12,'English','2019-07-14 10:53:42','2020-05-28 00:22:29'),
	(974,31,'Manager of IT Audit Unit - 01 post','<ul>\r\n<li>Join and contribute to Audit&rsquo;s change initiative and implementing action plans related to risk assessment and annual planning, audit execution, audit reporting.</li>\r\n<li>Lead and initiate digital innovation in audit approach/digital audit working paper.</li>\r\n<li>Lead team and perform field audit base on annual work plan.</li>\r\n<li>Review audit working papers and works performed to ensure satisfactory completion to reach conclusions and reporting.</li>\r\n<li>Draft Internal Audit reports ensuring the reports are clear, concise, identify root causes with practical&nbsp; solutions, and ultimately provide value to auditees, management and relevant stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to Internal Audit&rsquo;s participation in critical business and technology initiatives and projects&nbsp; ensuring that audit&rsquo;s perspective is effectively voiced and appropriate controls are designed and implemented on a proactive basis.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and improve in audit administration matters, including update of audit programs with new or revised policies, procedures and applicable rules, regulations and guidelines issued by the Bank and regulatory authorities.</li>\r\n<li>Provide career coaching, counselling and mentoring to help staff to develop professionally and personally.</li>\r\n<li>Proactively inform and report to head of department of significant risks or exposures related to internal controls, compliance, and/or governance requiring prompt attention.</li>\r\n<li>Perform others task as assigned by head department.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Auditing or other related fields</li>\r\n<li>At least 2-year-experience in IT and internal audit from banking sectors, MDIs and MFIs</li>\r\n<li>Good at software development, IT audit, operational risk management and compliance check</li>\r\n<li>Good at policy development, guidelines composition and process improvement</li>\r\n<li>Good at communication skill both written and spoken</li>\r\n<li>Ability to manage multi-task and working pressure</li>\r\n</ul>',1,77,15,17,'1','07/30/2019',1,7,9,5,2,'English','2019-07-14 11:01:17','2020-05-30 03:46:40'),
	(975,36,'Credit Officer 10 Post(មន្ត្រីឥណទាន ១០នាក់)','<p>+លក្ខខណ្ឌជ្រើសរើស</p>\r\n<p>&bull; កំរិតវប្បធម៌បញ្ចប់ថ្នាក់ទី១២ ឡើងទៅ(ជាប់ឬធ្លាក់)</p>\r\n<p>&bull; មានទំនាក់ទំនងល្អ មានគំនិតច្នៃប្រឌិត និង បង្កើតថ្មី</p>\r\n<p>&bull; មានភាពស្មោះត្រង់ មានឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ចំពោះការងារ&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; អាចធ្វើការជាក្រុម និង ម្នាក់ឯងបាន</p>\r\n<p>&bull; យល់ព្រមបម្រើការងារតាមការចាត់តាំង</p>\r\n<p>&bull; មានម៉ូតូផ្ទាល់ខ្លួន។</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>+អត្ថប្រយោជន៍ដែលផ្តល់ជូនបុគ្គលិករួមមាន៖</p>\r\n<p>​​​​​​​&nbsp; &nbsp;១. មានធានារ៉ាប់រងលើគ្រោះថ្នាក់ការងារ ២៤ម៉ោង&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;២. ប្រាក់បៀវត្សគោល ប្រាក់ឧបត្ថម្ភ និងអត្ថប្រយោជន៍ដែលទទួលបានចាប់ពី $៣០០-$៥០០</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៣. របបប្រេងសាំងម៉ូតូ (មិនកំណត់ចំពោះ CO)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៤. កាតទូរស័ព្ទ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៥. ប្រាក់ជួលម៉ូតូ ប្រចាំខែ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៦. ថ្លៃប្តូរប្រេងម៉ាស៊ីនម៉ូតូ ប្រចាំខែ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; ៧. ប្រាក់លើកទឹកចិត្ត ប្រចាំខែ និង ប័ណ្ណសរសើរ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៨. ប្រាក់ឧបត្ថម្ភតួនាទី</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;៩. ប្រាក់ឧបត្ថម្ភសំលៀកបំពាក់</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;១០.មានច្បាប់ឈប់សម្រាក ១៩ថ្ងៃ/ឆ្នាំ</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;១២. មានផ្តល់ជាប្រាក់កម្ចីដល់បុគ្គលិក (Staff Loan)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; បញ្ជាក់៖បេក្ខជនមានបទពិសោធន៍ត្រូវបានផ្តល់អតិភាពជូន</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ភារកិច្ចនិងការទទួលខុសត្រូវ (ភ្នាក់ងារឥណទាន CO )</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ផ្សព្វផ្សាយលក់ផលិតផលឥណទាន</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ទាក់ទាញអតិថិជន និងពង្រីកតំបន់ប្រតិបត្តិការ</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ធ្វើការទំនាក់ទំនងអជ្ញាធរមូលដ្ឋាន</p>\r\n<p>&bull; បញ្ចេញឥណទានជូនអតិថិជនឲ្យស្របតាមបចេ្ចកទេស</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ប្រមូលប្រាក់សំណង ត្រួតពិនិត្យតាមដានការសងត្រឡប់វិញ</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ធ្វើការដោះស្រាយការយឺតយ៉ាវរបស់អតិថិជន។</p>\r\n<p>បញ្ចក់ផុតកំណត់ថ្ងៃទី ៣១ កក្កដា ២០១៩</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>​​​​&nbsp; &nbsp;បេក្ខនារីនិងបេក្ខជនដែលមានចំណាប់អារម្មណ៍ត្រូវដាក់ពាក្យសុំជាមួយនិងឯកសារពាក់ព័ន្ធមានដូចជា៖ ប្រវត្តិរូបភ្ជាប់ជាមួយ រូបថត ៤ X ៦ (០១សន្លឹក) ប័ណ្ណគ្រួសារ សំបុត្រកំណើត អត្តសញ្ញាណប័ណ្ណ ឬ សញ្ញាប័ត្រផ្សេងៗ (ថតចំលងតែប៉ុណ្ណោះ) មកកាន់ទីស្នាក់ការ កណ្ដាលដែលមានអាសយដ្ឋាននៅ អគារលេខ ៦៩-៧១A&nbsp; ផ្លូវបូរីភ្នំពេញថី្ម ភូមិត្រពាំងឈូក សង្កាត់ទឹកថ្លា ខណ្ឌសែនសុខ ក្រុងភ្នំពេញ។</p>\r\n<p>សំរាប់ព័ត៌មានបន្ថែម សូមទាក់ទងមកការិយាល័យកណ្ដាល : Tel : 010362066 / 095600130&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>អ៊ីម៉ែលៈ maiveasnaitled@gmail.com រៀងរាល់ម៉ោងធ្វើការងារ ។</p>','<p>+លក្ខខណ្ឌជ្រើសរើស</p>\r\n<p>&bull; កំរិតវប្បធម៌បញ្ចប់ថ្នាក់ទី១២ ឡើងទៅ(ជាប់ឬធ្លាក់)</p>\r\n<p>&bull; មានទំនាក់ទំនឆន្ទៈខ្ពស់ចំពោះការងារ&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; អាចធ្វើការជាក្រុម និង ម្នាក់ឯងបាន</p>\r\n<p>&bull; យល់ព្រមបម្រើការងារតាមការចាត់តាំង</p>\r\n<p>&bull; មានម៉ូតូផ្ទាល់ខ្លួន។</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,28,10,17,'10','08/30/2019',1,12,3,1,1,'English','2019-07-18 08:24:10','2020-05-31 01:31:18'),
