	(1000,15,'Unit Manager of ISA for Database Administration (01 post.)','<ul>\r\n<li>Monitor and configure Active Data Guard configuration, Real Application Cluster (RAC), Golden Gate, and troubleshooting the issue.</li>\r\n<li>Install and configure Oracle Database software and create new database system as business requirement.</li>\r\n<li>Control and manage the existing database on Core Banking System, ATM, Mobile Banking System, LOS, Data Warehouse and troubleshoot especially database backup and restoration.</li>\r\n<li>Administrate and perform patching on the database system and SQL Tuning, performance tuning.</li>\r\n<li>Manage and control data masking on critical database is properly done.</li>\r\n<li>Work with support team to solve the database issue.</li>\r\n<li>Administrate on security of all databases system and perform regular securities monitoring to identify any possible intrusions.</li>\r\n<li>Support other related units, branches or departments to resolve the issue on critical system.</li>\r\n<li>Implement the Disaster Recovery, Data Continuity Plan on Database with other related critical system.</li>\r\n<li>Verify the existing procedure/guideline or new system deployment procedure/guideline to meet up to date.</li>\r\n<li>Manage team to complete the tasks assigned by management and establish the activities plan.</li>\r\n<li>Administrate and monitor jobs performance on all database to meet SLA.</li>\r\n<li>To ensure all databases system with high security, high availability and ensure database system is running 24/7 without interruption.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree of Computer Science or related fields.</li>\r\n<li>At least 4 years working experience in Database Administration / IT.</li>\r\n<li>Experience on loading huge data (ETL), transforming, and Analyzing the data and experience in Data warehouse performance tuning and analysis.</li>\r\n<li>Working experience with Microfinance or Commercial Bank is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Oracle Certified (OCA, OCP)&nbsp; is preferable.</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge of RDBMS, system Integration, database backup &amp; recovery technology, database high availability technology and database security.</li>\r\n<li>Good knowledge on database tuning for Oracle Database, SQL Server, MySQL,&hellip;</li>\r\n<li>Good at spoken and written communication skills both English and Khmer.</li>\r\n<li>Able to work at night for solving critical issue or other tasks assigned by management.</li>\r\n</ul>',1,59,15,17,'1','05/24/2020',0,9,9,5,13,'English','2020-05-07 15:20:36','2020-06-01 02:30:33'),
